gismu rafsi: bav x1 is in the future of/later than/after x2 in time sequence; x1 is latter; x2 is former. Also sequel, succeed, successor, follow, come(s) after; time ordering only (use lidne otherwise); aorist in that x1 may overlap in time with x2 as long as it extends afterwards; non-aorist future (= cfabalvi); (default x2 is the space time reference, whereupon:) x1 will occur. See also lidne, cabna, purci, farna.

gismu rafsi: bac x1 exceeds/is beyond limit/boundary x2 from x3 in property/amount x4 (ka/ni). On the other side of a bound, but not necessarily directly 'across' nor at the shortest plausible distance (per ragve); also not limited to position in space. See also dukse, ragve, zmadu, kuspe.

gismu rafsi: bal ba'i x1 is great/grand in property x2 (ka) by standard x3. Indicates a subjective greatness, as compared to the objective standard implied for barda; (synonyms, possibly requiring tanru:) extraordinary, illustrious, magnificent, impressive, awesome, grandiose, august, inspiring, special, majestic, distinguished, eminent, splendor, stately, imposing (all generally zabna); terrible (mabla). See also barda, nobli, se sinma, pluja, misno, vajni, fasnu, cizra, traji, mutce, se manci.
lujvo s1 is psycholinguistics based on methodology s2. Cf. banjikske, banpliske.
lujvo s1 is pragmatics based on methodology s2. The science of how language interacts with the world. Cf. banjikske, banmenske.
fu'ivla x1 is the language with ISO 639-3 code ''pol'' (Polish). Cf. bangrpolska.
fu'ivla x1 is the language with ISO 639-3 code ''por'' (Portuguese). Cf. razbau, potybau.
lujvo s1 pertains to language of s2=b2 Cultural gismu replacement lujvo for languages: From gismu bangu and srana

gismu rafsi: ba'o x1 grows/expands [an increasing development] to size/into form x2 from x3. Also rising, developing; x1 gets bigger/enlarges/increases. See also farvi, zenba, jmina, barda, makcu, ferti.

fu'ivla x1 is the language with ISO 639-3 code ''spa'' (Spanish). Cf. sanbau, getybau.

gismu rafsi: bax x1 is a bank owned by/in banking system x2 for banking function(s) x3 (event). See also sorcu, zarci, canja, kagni.

gismu rafsi: bap bai x1 [force] (ka) forces/compels event x2 to occur; x1 determines property x2 to manifest. Also constrains; requires success, unlike the physics term (better expressed by danre). See also fanta, rinju, jimte, jitro, rinka, krinu, zukte, randa, danre, cmavo list bai, marxa, tinsa, xarnu.
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: will have been; (tense/modal).
lujvo x1 exports x2 to x3 from x4 via x5.

lujvo f1 is inside-out, with part(s) b1 currently on the outside.
lujvo x1 is a stream of x2 flowing out of x3.

lujvo x1 is an exit/outlet/way out of x2 for x3. Cf. li'avro.

lujvo x1 projects/extends out of x2. Cf. bartu, kuspe.
lujvo x1=c1 leaves/exits/goes outside of x2=c2=b2 via route x3=c3. Cf. barkla.
gismu rafsi: ba'a x1(s) is a/are mark(s)/spot(s) on x2 of material x3. ba'armo'a for a pattern of marks. See also sinxa, pixra, se ciska, se prina.
lujvo x1 is a sense organ used to observe x2 which is outside the observer x3 under conditions x4.
gismu rafsi: bar x1 is on the outside of x2; x1 is exterior to x2. See also jibni, nenri, sruri, lamji, korbi, calku, vasru.
lujvo b1=c1 is a pseudonym of c2 to/used-by namer/name-user c3 (person). Cf. cmebasti.
gismu x1 emphasizes/accentuates/gives emphasis/stress/accent to x2 by (action) x3. Also: say forcefully. See also pandi.
gismu rafsi: bas x1 replaces/substitutes for/instead of x2 in circumstance x3; x1 is a replacement/substitute. Also: x1 trades places with x2. See also cmavo list ba'i, binra.
lujvo g1 (agent) replaces/substitutes b1 for/instead of b2 in circumstance b3.
lujvo x1 replace/trade places with one another in circumstance x2. Cf. basti, simxu.
lujvo v1=b1 is an anaphora/pronoun/pro-word in language v2 replacing word b2 under conditions b3.
gismu rafsi: bat x1 bites/pinches x2 on/at specific locus x3 with x4. Bite through (= ka'arbatci, batygre); pinch (= cinzybatci). See also denci, jgalu, guska, citka.
lujvo b1=f1 (agent) bites apart b2=f2 into sections/partitions f3 with bite locus b3.

fu'ivla x1 is Bulgarian in aspect x2. Cf. slovo, nanslovo.

lujvo j3 is a soccer match/game with j1=t1 playing/competing against j2 for prize/title j4. Cf. bolci, tikpa, jivna, boltipyjvi, boltipyboi. For American/Canadian football match/game see bemboiterjvi.
lujvo x1 is a soccer ball made from material x2. Cf. bolci, tikpa, boltipyjvi, boltipyterjvi.
lujvo j1=t1 plays soccer against j2 in competition j3 for prize/title j4. Cf. bolci, tikpa, jivna, boltipyboi, boltipterjvi. For American/Canadian football see bemboijvi.
lujvo xa1=b1 is the fist of xa2. Cf. fegboixa'e, demxa'e, jairxa'e, xanse'agle.
lujvo xa1 is a hemisphere of sphere b1=xa2, of material b2, halfness standard xa3. Cf. bolci, xadba, plinyxadba.

gismu rafsi: bog bo'u x1 is a/the bone/ivory [body-part], performing function x2 in body of x3; [metaphor: calcium]. x2 is likely an abstract: may be structure/support for some body part, but others as well such as the eardrum bones; the former can be expressed as (tu'a le ); cartilage/gristle (= ranbo'u), skeleton (= bogygreku). See also greku, denci, jirna, sarji.

lujvo t1=d1=b1 is a surfingboard of material/property t2. From tanbo, djacu, boxna (b2-b5 subsumed). See also jacta'o, windsurfingboard (=fanjacta'o), kitesurfingboard (=volfanjacta'o), wakesurfingboard (=blobonjacta'o).
lujvo p1=j1 is corrugated cardboard from source p2. Cf. jarple, tanxe.
lujvo m1 is an antenna emitting/receiving wave b2=m2 with wave-form b3, wave-length b4 and frequency b5.
lujvo k1 is k2 (quantifier, default: one) bottlefuls in quantity. Cf. botpi, klani.
gismu rafsi: bot bo'i x1 is a bottle/jar/urn/flask/closable container for x2, made of material x3 with lid x4. See also baktu, lante, patxu, tansi, tanxe, vasru, gacri.
gismu rafsi: bof bo'o x1 is a sheet/foil/blanket [2-dimensional shape/form flexible in 3 dimensions] of material x2. See also plita, cinje, polje, slasi, tinci.
gismu rafsi: bon bo'a x1 is a wave [periodic pattern] in medium x2, wave-form x3, wave-length x4, frequency x5. See also slilu, dikni, cinje, polje, morna, canre.
lujvo bar1=bak1 is a swimming pool filled with bak2, made of material bak3. Cf. barda, baktu, djacu, litki, limna, fulta, jinru.
lujvo bi1=ba1 grows in size/becomes big to bi2 under conditions bi3. Cf. verba, spati, pinji, cmalu.
lujvo ba1=bl1 is a ship for carrying bl2, propelled by bl3, big by standard ba3.
lujvo b1 is huge/enormous/very big in property b2 with criterion b3.
lujvo c1=b1 is a giant of mythos/religion c2, huge as compared with standard/norm b3. Cf. brabra, clapre, claselxadni, torcrida.
lujvo bl1=ba1 is a battleship of type/carrying bl2, propelled by bl3. Cf. barda, jamna, bloti, ni'ablo, brajamblo, cmajamblo, badjamblo, vijblo.
lujvo x1=b1=c1 is huge/enormous/colossal/immense in property x2=b2 to observer x3=b3=c3
lujvo c1 is a boot for covering/protecting (feet/hooves) c2, and of material c3. Cf. tupcutci.
gismu x1 is an enemy/opponent/adversary/foe of x2 in struggle x3. See also damba, jamna, darlu, pendo, fapro, gunta, sarji, jivna, jinga.
lujvo f1=b1 is an abyss in f2, large as compared with standard/norm b3.
lujvo f1=b1 is a novel about plot/theme/subject c2 by author c3. Cf. barda, cfika, lisri, cukta, cmafi'a.
lujvo bl1=ba1 is a cruiser of type/carrying bl2, propelled by bl3. Cf. barda, jamna, bloti, ni'ablo, brabrajamblo, cmajamblo, badjamblo, vijblo.
lujvo g1 causes j1=b1 to decrease in property/dimension b2 (ka) by amount j3. Cf. barda, jdika, gasnu, cmazengau.
lujvo c1 is the nail of the big toe of body d3. Cf. jmatajycalku, brajmadegji, jgalu.
lujvo k1 amply overlaps with k2 at locus k3, amply as compared with standard/norm b3.
lujvo k1 is numerous on a scale of k3. Cf. barda, klani, so'imei.
lujvo b1=c1 is a mountain in terrain c2, big by standard b3. Cf. barda, cmana, cmama'a.
lujvo z1 is bigger than z2 in dimension b2 by margin z4. Cf. barda, zmadu, brarai, mecybrarai, brame'a, clamau.
lujvo m1 is smaller/[less big] than m2 in dimension b2 by margin m4. Cf. barda, mleca, cmamau, bramau, brarai, mecybrarai, tolba'o.
lujvo x1 is a grapefruit/shaddock/pomelo of variety x2. Cf. nimre, barda, pelnimre, najnimre, ri'ornimre.
lujvo p1 is a cauldron/big pot for contents p2, of material/properties p3, big as compared with standard/norm b3. Cf. bravau.
lujvo d1=b1 is a continent in ocean/on planet d3.
lujvo t1=b1 is the biggest among set/range t4 in property/dimension b2 (ka). Cf. barda, traji, bramau, mecybrarai, brame'a, mecycmarai.
lujvo r1 is a boulder/big rock of type/composition r2 from location r3, big as compared with standard/norm b3. Cf. cmana, derxi.
lujvo x1 is a greater noctule bat (Nyctalus lasiopterus)
lujvo s1 is steep with angle s2 to horizon/frame s3. Cf. tcesa'o.
lujvo m1=b1 is very big/great/huge/enormous in the property of b2(ka) as compared with standard/norm b3. Cf. barda, mutce.
lujvo t1 is a tone high in pitch/frequency from source t3. Cf. barda, tonga, cladu.

gismu x1 is hail/sleet/freezing rain/solid precipitation of material/composition including x2. This is the substance, not the act or manner of its falling, which is carvi. See also carvi, snime, bisli, tcima.
lujvo v1 is a large container, containing v2, large as compared with standard/norm b3. Cf. brapatxu.
lujvo x1=b1 is an ocean on planet x2 (default Earth) of fluid x3. Cf. barda, xamsi, braplu, bisma'a, arktik.
lujvo x1=b1 is a cart/dray/draft horse of breed x2. Cf. barda, xirma.
fu'ivla j1 is a crab of species/section j2.
lujvo z1=b1 grows in property b2 (ka) by amount z3. Cf. barda, zenba, cmaze'a, brabi'o.
lujvo g1 causes z1=b1 to increase in property/dimension b2 (ka) by amount z3. Cf. barda, zenba, gasnu, cmajdikygau.
gismu rafsi: raz x1 reflects Brazilian culture/nationality/language in aspect x2. See also porto, ketco.
fu'ivla x1 is Breton in aspect x2. Syn. fasko'o.
gismu rafsi: red bre x1 is ready/prepared for x2 (event). See also spaji, jukpa.
lujvo j1=b1 is almost ready for b2 (event). Cf. bredi, jibni.
fu'ivla x1 is a patent on invention x2 by inventor x3 valid in jurisdiction x4 for time interval x5.

gismu rafsi: bri x1 (text) is a predicate relationship with relation x2 among arguments (sequence/set) x3. Also: x3 are related by relation x2 (= terbri for reordered places). (x3 is a set completely specified); See also sumti, fancu.
gismu rafsi: bif bi'e x1 is a breeze/wind/gale from direction x2 with speed x3; x1 blows from x2. See also tcima.
gismu rafsi: bij x1 is an office/bureau/work-place of worker x2 at location x3. See also jibri, gunka.
lujvo x1 is a pro-bridi representing predicate relationship x2 with relation x3 among arguments x4. Cf. bridi, krati, sumka'i, cei.
lujvo x1 is a prenex of bridi/predicate relationship x2 with relation x3 among arguments x4. Cf. zo'u.
lujvo x1 is a bridi-tail of predicate relationship x2 with relation x3 among arguments (sequence/set) x4. Cf. bridi, rebla.
gismu rafsi: rit x1 reflects British/United Kingdom culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also glico, skoto, merko, ropno.

lujvo v1 is a morphologically defined predicate word signifying relation b2 in language v3. Derived from bridi and valsi, deleting b3, as we are speaking of the relationship independent of particular arguments. In Lojban, such words must end in a vowel and contain a consonant cluster within the first five letters (not counting y). Not all words that can be used as a selbri (for instance members of GOhA) are brivla.
gismu rafsi: rod 1st assignable variable predicate (context determines place structure). See also cmavo list bu'a.
gismu rafsi: bo'e 2nd assignable variable predicate (context determines place structure).
gismu 3rd assignable variable predicate (context determines place structure).
gismu 4th assignable variable predicate (context determines place structure).
gismu 5th assignable variable predicate (context determines place structure).
lujvo g1 is Israel with people g2 and land g3. Cf. gugde'ilu, sra'eli.
lujvo m1 is a synagogue at location/serving area m3. Cf. lijda.
fu'ivla x1 is a bromeliad/pineapple of species x2. Cf. grutrxananase.
cmene Brunei. full name bruNAIS.darusLAM. Cf. xrabo, gugde.
lujvo l1 (agent) sweeps/brushes l2, removing soil/contaminant l3 with brush l4=b1. Cf. denburcu.
gismu rafsi: bun bu'a x1 is brother of/fraternal to x2 by bond/tie/standard/parent(s) x3; [not necess. biological]. See also mensi, tunba, tamne, famti, bersa.
cmene Brooklyn, New York: a borough of New York City, at the western tip of Long Island. Cf. merko, tcadu.
cmavo rafsi: bus bu'i BU convert any single word to BY.
cmavo rafsi: bul GOhA logically quantified predicate variable: some selbri 1.
cmavo GOhA logically quantified predicate variable: some selbri 2.
cmavo GOhA logically quantified predicate variable: some selbri 3.
cmavo UI7 attitudinal contour: start emotion - continue emotion - end emotion.
cmavo cluster UI*7 attitudinal contour: start emotion - continue emotion - end emotion.
cmavo cluster UI*7 attitudinal contour: start emotion - continue emotion - end emotion.
cmavo FAhA3 location tense relation/direction; coincident with/at the same place as; space equivalent of ca.
lujvo z1 is an awning over z2, made of b2.
lujvo z1 is a tent inhabited by z2, made of b2. Cf. bukmra, bukydi'u, bu'udru.
gismu rafsi: buj bu'o x1 pertains to the Buddhist culture/religion/ethos in aspect x2. See also latna, lijda.
lujvo n1 is the Vesak celebrated by s1 with activities s3. Cf. budjo, jbena, nu, salci.
lujvo c1 is a thread of fabric material c2=b2. Cf. skori, silka, marna, mapni, sunla, fenso.
lujvo f1 parachutes to f2 from f3 using parachute of type/material b2. Cf. falbu'u, santa, vofli, bukyvoi.
lujvo f1 is a tear in cloth f2=b1 of type/material x3=b2. Cf. tafyfe'a.
lujvo g1=b1 is a carpet/rug for covering floor g2=l1 of x3=l2, of type/material x4=b2. Cf. lolgai.
lujvo m1 is a tent sheltering m2 from m3, made of cloth b2. Cf. bu'uzda.
gismu rafsi: buk bu'u x1 is an amount of cloth/fabric of type/material x2. See also mapni, matli, sunla, slasi, silka.
lujvo z1 is a tent for purpose z2, made of b2. Cf. bukmra, bu'uzda.
lujvo v1 paraglides, using paraglider of type/material b2. Cf. bukyvoikla, bukfa'u, falbu'u.
lujvo x1 is fog/mist of liquid/composition x2 covering x3. Cf. bumru, gapci.
gismu rafsi: bum x1 is foggy/misty/covered by a fog/mist/vapor of liquid x2. See also djacu, carvi, danmo, lunsa, tcima, gapci.
cmene Brother Cf. bruna, mes, mam, paf, bes, tix.

gismu rafsi: bud x1 is x2 (def. 1) local weight unit(s) [non-metric], standard x3, subunits [e.g. ounces] x4. (additional subunit places may be added as x5, x6, ...); See also grake, junta, tilju, rupnu, fepni, dekpu, gutci, minli, merli, kramu.
gismu rafsi: bur bu'e x1 is brown/tan [color adjective]. See also skari, blabi, xekri, kandi, carmi.
lujvo s1 is a sister-in-law (brother's spouse) of m2 under law/custom/tradition/system/convention sp3. Omit x4=s2=m1. Cf. speni, me'ispe, tubyspe.
gismu rafsi: bru x1 is a brush for purpose x2 (event) with bristles x3. See also komcu, pinsi.
gismu x1 is embarrassed/disconcerted/flustered/ill-at-ease about/under conditions x2 (abstraction). See also cinmo.
lujvo n1 is brown bread made from grains n2. Cf. labnanba.
lujvo g1 (agent) embarrasses/disconcerts b1 about/under conditions b2 (abstraction).
cmavo PU time tense relation/direction: is [selbri]; during/simultaneous with [sumti]; present tense.
cmavo cluster PU* sumti question asking for a time/date/event; simultaneous with what?.
cmavo rafsi: caz CAhA modal aspect: actuality/ongoing event.
lujvo cl1 is unaided by/without apparatus/mechanism/device/equipment ca1=cl2 for function ca2 controlled/triggered by ca3 (agent).
cmavo UI2 evidential: I define. See also mitcu'a, mitsmu.
lujvo b1=c2 is a wind from direction b2 with speed b3, shoving/pushing c2 at locus c3. Cf. bloti.
lujvo car1=cat2 is a pushcart/wheelbarrow for carrying car2. Cf. catke, carce.
lujvo g1=c1 pushes m1=c2 to destination m2 from origin m3 over path/route m4. Cf. catke, muvgau, danre.
lujvo s1 is a valve/piston of material s2, shoving/pushing c2 at locus c3. Cf. matra, karce.
cmavo BAI catni modal, 1st place by authority of ...
lujvo cp1=ca2 demands cp2=ca2 from cp3. Cf. catni, cpedu, e'o, camcpe, mi'ecpe.
lujvo cu1=ca1 (agent) permits/lets/allows cu2 (event) under conditions cu3, derived from authority on basis ca3.
lujvo j1 is a charge of service j2 to consumer j3=c2 set and levied by authority j4=c1. Cf. jdima, catni, selfu, pleji.
lujvo z2 is official, approved by authority z1=c1 over sphere/people c2. Cf. zanru, catni, jdice, curmi.

lujvo x1=v1 is an authoritative document of x2=v2 (data/facts/du'u) about x3=v3 (object/event) preserved in medium x4=v4, by authority x5=c1 over matter/sphere/persons x6=c2 derived on basis x7=c3. Cf. ca'icru catni vreji.
cmavo ZAhO interval event contour: during ...; continuative |-----|.
cmavo FAhA2 location tense relation/direction; forwards/to the front of ...
cmavo cluster ZAhO* time tense: has been, is now in the aftermath of; (tense/modal).
lujvo d1=c1 is today; d1=c1 is the day occuring at the same time as c2, day standard d3. Cf. prulamdei, bavlamdei.
lujvo m1=c1 is the current month by month standard m3, simultaneous with c2 in time. Cf. cabna, pavmasti.

gismu rafsi: cab x1 is current at/in the present of/during/concurrent/simultaneous with x2 in time. (default x2 is the present resulting in:) x1 is now; time relationship only, 'aorist' claiming simultaneity does not mean one event does not extend into the past or future of the other. See also zvati, balvi, purci, cmavo list ca, cmavo list ca'a.
lujvo n1 is the current year by standard n3, simultaneous with c2 in time. Cf. cabma'i, cabdei.

gismu rafsi: ca'a x1 is apparatus/mechanism/device/equipment for function x2 controlled/[triggered] by x3 (agent). Form determined by/from function; does not imply automated/automatic action - requires an external agent/trigger (a minji may be a zmiku cabra if it requires an external agent to trigger or control the functions that it performs automatically). (cf. tutci, minji, finti; girzu, ganzu for organizational apparatus, pilno)
lujvo ce1 is the modern era. Cf. citri.
lujvo c1=f1 is live (experienced as it happens) to experiencer c2. Cf. cabna, fasnu, tivni.
lujvo k1=c1 ranges through time/has duration k2=c2. x2 is the complete duration as the amount of time or an interval specification and is non-aorist. Cf. temci.
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: present actuality; modal aspect.
cmavo cluster ZAhO* time tense: is now/simultaneously, is now in the middle of; (tense/modal).

lujvo k1=t1 is a tradition/practice/custom of traditional culture t2=k2 under conditions t3 This is similar to ritli, but the emphasis is not necessarily on particular rituals, but customs (ex. wearing of a particular type of clothing or hairstyle) associated with a group.
gismu x1 is x2 hours in duration (default is 1 hour) by standard x3. See also junla, mentu, snidu, tcika, temci.
lujvo x1 is x2 hours in angular measure of right ascension RA (default is 1). Cf. cacra, radno, julra'o, sostartai. pi'e used in x2 indicates a base of 60.
lujvo j1=t1 is a convention prescribing j2 (event/state) within community j3=t2. Cf. ritli, lijda, malsi.
lujvo c1=t2 customarily expresses c2 to c3 via medium c4 under conditions t3. Cf. tcaci, cusku, ritli.
lujvo cat1=can1 is a lurker/inactively watches cat2 See also: bebzunpre, irci
lujvo k1=c1 (agent) idly plays with plaything/toy k2. Cf. lazni.
lujvo s1=c1 (agent) ceases and rests from activity/process/state s2 (not necessarily completing it). Cf. lazni.
gismu rafsi: dzu x1 walks/strides/paces on surface x2 using limbs x3. See also stapa, bajra, klama, litru.
lujvo l1 is liquid at room temperature/at standard temperature and pressure, and consists of composition/material l2. Cf. djacu, margu, xalka, sligu, kelvo.
gismu rafsi: caf x1 (event) often/frequently/commonly/customarily occurs/recurs by standard x2. See also rirci, fadni, kampu, rapli, krefu, lakne, cmavo list piso'iroi and similar compounds.
lujvo r1 is a frequently-asked question about subject r2
lujvo di1 is a barn for storing/sheltering grains/livestock/tools/machinery da1. Cf. grutersro, xirzda, cange, sorcu.
lujvo g1 is a/the agricultural industry/sector producing g2=c4 from farms c1 located in c2 farmed by c3. Omit g3. Cf. cange, gundi.
lujvo p1 is a farmer associated with farm c1 producing c4. Cf. te, cange, tercange, pudykurji.
lujvo z1 is a farmer's market selling z2, operated by farmers z3=c3. Cf. nurma, grute, spati, xarju, bakni, ladru, sovda.
cmavo CAI attitudinal: strong intensity attitude modifier.
lujvo b1=c1 is huge/enormous/colossal in property b2=c2 to observer b3=c3.
lujvo cat1 stares at cat2 as received by observer car3. Cf. zgana.
lujvo d1 craves/intensely wishes d2 (event/state) for purpose d3. Cf. toldji, caitcu.
lujvo n1 desperately needs/is desperate for n2 for purpose/action/stage of process n3. Cf. djica, caidji.
lujvo s1=c1 is roaring/blinding to s2 via sensory channel s2=c3.
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: during and after; (tense/modal).
lujvo g1 is a/the wholesale/retail industry sector in which c1 trades/barters c2 for c3 by process g3. Omit c4, g2. Cf. canja, gundi.
lujvo s1 (set) mutually exchange/trade/barter commodity c2 for c3 with c4. Cf. canja, simxu.
lujvo x1 is a beetle of species x2. Not to be confused with ckacinki; Cf. kokcinela, kurkuli, gusycinki.
lujvo x1 is a mollusk/clam/mussel/snail of species x2. Cf. skargolu, sedjmacurnu, ostreda.
lujvo x1 is malacology based on methodology x2. Cf. cakcurnu, dalske, mivyske, xamsi.
gismu x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of chocolate/cocoa. See also ckafi.
lujvo p1=j3=c3 is mother of pearl from source p2=c2. Cf. boijme, tercakyjme.
lujvo j1 is a crustacean of species/class j2. Cf. calku, jukni, braxiura, nerfopi.
lujvo k1=c2 is a tank/armored combat vehicle for carrying k2, propelled by k3, with armor-plating c1.
lujvo x1 is a turtle of species x2.
lujvo c1=t1 is space-time occupied by c2. Cf. canlu, temci, tarske, mu'eske.
gismu rafsi: cak x1 is a shell/husk [hard, protective covering] around x2 composed of x3. See also pilka, skapi, gacri, bartu.
lujvo cm1 is a geometry describing cm2=ca1=t1 geometric object. Cf. carmi, tarmi, cmaci, cukyxratci, cukla, kubli, cibjgatai, cibjgacmaci.
lujvo cp1=ca1 demands cp2 from cp3. Cf. cpedu, nitcu, ca'icpe, mi'ecpe.
lujvo g1=c1 is vast/very wide in (2nd most significant) dimension g2=c2 with observer g3=c3. Cf. carmi, ganra, brabra, caibra, tcebra, selte'abra, dukse, cimni.
lujvo g1 is intensely happy about g2. Cf. carmi, gleki, mansygei, nalra'ugei.
lujvo r1 hypes r2=g1=c1. Cf. gubni, misno, casnu, notci.
cmene Robin Lee Powell. Name Lojbanized according to its meaning.
lujvo k1=c1 screams/howls sound k2. Cf. carmi, krixa, lausku.
fu'ivla x1 is a champagne made from grapes x2. Cf. vanju, fomvanju, risyvanju, xalka, koinka. For sparkling wines without an AOC designation, use fomvanju.
lujvo ci1 is a fan of/intensely interested in ci2 as received/measured by observer ca3. Cf. camselci'igri, crexalbo.
lujvo g1 is a fanclub for g2=ci2. Cf. camselci'i, crexalbo.
lujvo ci1=m2 is toucan/toucanet of species/type ci1 with bill m1=s1 of typically intense color or colors s2=ca1 Family Ramphastidae
lujvo t1 feels horror/is intensely frightened of t2 (event/tu'a object). Cf. ii.
lujvo c1 effortfully tries to do t2 by method t3, as perceived by c3.
gismu x1 vanishes/disappears from location x2; x1 ceases to be observed at x2 using senses/sensor x3. Also leaves, goes away (one sense). See also cliva, ganse, zgana, lebna, vimcu.
gismu rafsi: cad x1 is idle/at rest/inactive. "in motion", not implying a change in location, is negation of this. See also surla.
cmene Hong Kong. From Mandarin pronunciation. Cf. xyngon, xonkon, jungo, tcadu.

gismu rafsi: cag x1 is a farm/ranch at x2, farmed by x3, raising/producing x4; (adjective:) x1 is agrarian. Also grange; farming is any organized agrarian activity, not limited to plant crops. See also purdi, nurma, ferti, foldi, xarju.

gismu rafsi: caj x1 exchanges/trades/barters commodity x2 for x3 with x4; x1, x4 is a trader/merchant/businessman. Also (adjective:) x1, x2, x4 is/are commercial (better expressed as ka canja, kamcanja). x2/x3 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event (possibly service), or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= posycanja for unambiguous semantics); (cf. dunda, friti, vecnu, zarci, jdini, pleji, jdima, jerna, kargu; see note at jdima on cost/price/value distinction, banxa, cirko, dunda, janta, kargu, prali, sfasa, zivle)
gismu rafsi: ca'o x1 is a window/portal/opening [portal] in wall/building/structure x2. See also vorme, bitmu, ganlo, murta, pagre, kevna, jvinu, kalri, kuspe.
gismu rafsi: cal ca'u x1 is space/volume/region/room [at-least-3-dimensional area] occupied by x2. Also occupy (= selca'u). See also kensa, bliku, kumfa, kevna, kunti, tubnu, dekpu.
gismu rafsi: cna x1 is a shovel/spade [bladed digging implement] for digging x2. See also kakpa, guska, tutci.
gismu rafsi: can x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of sand/grit from source x2 of composition including x3. Also abrasive (= gukcanre). See also bidju, rokci, zalvi, boxna.
gismu x1 is a/the gut(s)/entrails/intestines/viscera/innards/digestive system [body-part] of x2. Metaphor: process hub. See also betfu.
cmene Shanghai. Cf. jungo, tcunCIN, xyngon, cangan, xonkon, tcadu.
lujvo l1 is an adventurer traveling via route l2 using means/vehicle x3. Cf. renvi.
lujvo x1 threatens x2 with x3 (danger, peril).
lujvo b1 snarls/growls/roars the threat (utterance) of idea/action s2 at audience s3. Cf. ckape, stidi, bacru, capti'i, fegba'u, fe'ucmo.
lujvo s1 (agent) threatens/menaces idea/action s2 to audience s3. Cf. baple'i, terpa, jamna.
cmavo cluster ZAhO* time tense: is going to, is now just about to, is now anticipating; (tense/modal).
lujvo b1=c1 is a tornado/waterspout moving from direction b2 at speed b3 rotating around centre /eye c2 with rotational direction c3. Cf. carna, brife, taifnu, vilti'a.
gismu x1 is a cart/carriage/wagon [wheeled vehicle] for carrying x2, propelled by x3. See also karce, xislu, marce, matra.
lujvo l1 reels in l2=c1 by handle/at locus l3 by rotating it around axis c2. Cf. bloti, fipkalte, curnu.
lujvo cr1=ca1 turns to face cr2. Cf. crane, carna.
lujvo cu1 is a roller skate/ice skate for feet cu2, of material cu3, for carrying x4=ca2. Cf. cucyxelkla, xilcutci, xilcucli'u, cucma'e.
lujvo k1 is k2 (quantifier, default: one) cartloads/wagonloads in quantity. Cf. carce, klani.
lujvo x1 turns x2 around axis x3 in direction x4. Cf. carcpu.
lujvo x1 is a whirligig beetle of species x2. Cf. cakcinki.

gismu rafsi: cam cai x1 is intense/bright/saturated/brilliant in property (ka) x2 as received/measured by observer x3. Also lustrous, gleaming, sparkling, shining (all probably better metaphorically combined with gusni: gusycai or camgu'i); in colors, refers principally to increased saturation (with opposite kandi). See also denmi, gusni, kandi, ruble, skari, tilju, tsali, mutce, blabi, blanu, bunre, cicna, crino, grusi, narju, nukni, pelxu, xekri, xunre, zirpu.
gismu rafsi: car x1 turns/rotates/revolves around axis x2 in direction x3. Also revolve (= jincarna). See also gunro, jendu.
lujvo x1 is a helicopter for carrying x2, propelled by x3. Cf. vofli.
cmene Rot-13. Cf. mifra, mipri, vlali'i, lerpoi.
gismu rafsi: cat x1 is a chart/diagram/map of/about x2 showing formation/data-points x3. See also platu.
gismu rafsi: cav x1 rains/showers/[precipitates] to x2 from x3; x1 is precipitation [not limited to 'rain']. See also bratu, dilnu, santa, snime, tcima, bisli, bumru.
gismu rafsi: snu x1(s) (mass normally, but 1 individual/jo'u possible) discuss(es)/talk(s) about topic/subject x2. Also chat, converse. See also bacru, cusku, darlu, tavla.
gismu rafsi: ca'e x1 [agent] shoves/pushes x2 at locus x3. Move by pushing/shoving (= ca'ermuvgau). (cf. danre for non-agentive force, lacpu)

gismu rafsi: cta x1 looks at/examines/views/inspects/regards/watches/gazes at x2. Also look through (= grecta, ravycta, bacycta); note that English "look" often means a more generic "observe". See also jvinu, minra, simlu, viska, lanli, zgana, setca, viska.
gismu rafsi: ca'i x1 has authority/is an official in/on/over matter/sphere/persons x2 derived on basis x3. See also turni, tutra, krati, cmavo list ca'i, jaspu, pulji.
fu'ivla j1 is the bishop/archbishop of j2 of religion l1. Cf. catni, jdatro.
gismu x1 (agent) kills/slaughters/murders x2 by action/method x3. See also morsi, xarci.
lujvo m1 orders m2 to have c2 excecuted by action/method c3. Cf. catra, minde.
lujvo x1 is a hitman. Cf. zekri, bakcatra, sonci.
cmavo BAI claxu modal, 1st place lacked by ...
lujvo g1 (person/agent) deprives c1 of c2. Cf. caucni, seicni, nonkansa, pavysei, xagji, nitcu, djica.
lujvo l1 (agent) showers l2. Cf. cavysezlu'i, lumci, carvi, jinsa, zbabu.
lujvo f1=c1, consisting of f2, pours into f3=c2 from f4=c3.
lujvo k1 is a raincoat of material k2, protecting from rain c1. Cf. tcima, bandu.
lujvo l1=s1 (agent) showers itself of soil/contaminant l3 with cleaning material(s) l4. Cf. cavlu'i.
fu'ivla x1 is a game of chess between x2 (white) and x3 (black).
gismu rafsi: cax x1 is shallow in extent in direction/property x2 away from reference point x3 by standard x4. See also condi, tordu, jarki, cinla, cmalu, jarki, jmifa.
lujvo f1 is actual (existing in act or reality, not just potentially). Cf. fasnu, ca'a, jetnu.
lujvo f1 is rotten/decayed/fermented with decay/fermentation agent f2. Cf. kukfusra.
cmavo rafsi: cec JOI non-logical connective: set link, unordered; "and also", but forming a set.
cmavo LAU 2-word letteral/shift: the word following indicates a new font (e.g. italics, manuscript).
cmavo CEhE links terms into an afterthought termset.
cmavo rafsi: cez PA3 digit/number: % percentage symbol, hundredths.
cmavo rafsi: ce'o JOI non-logical connective: ordered sequence link; "and then", forming a sequence.
cmavo KOhA8 pseudo-quantifier binding a variable within an abstraction that represents an open place.

gismu rafsi: cel ce'a x1 launches/fires/shoots projectile/missile x2, propelled by x3 [propellant/propulsion]. Also: x1 is a gun/launcher/cannon; x1 hurls/throws/casts (more general than renro in that propulsion need not be internal to x1). See also renro, danti, jakne, jbama, spoja.
gismu rafsi: cem ce'u x1 is a community/colony of organisms x2. See also bende, kulnu, natmi, tcadu, jecta, girzu.

gismu x1 is an era/epoch/age characterized by x2 (event/property/interval/idea). (x2 interval should be the defining boundaries; if merely a characterizing period, the nature of the interval should be expressed in an abstract bridi, or the interval should be marked with tu'a; x2 may also be characteristic object(s) or practices of the era, if marked with tu'a); See also ranji, temci, citsi.
lujvo m1=c1 is contemporary with/in the same epoch/era as m2 by standard m3 (m1=c1 and m2 interchangeable).
cmavo CEI selbri variable assignment; assigns broda series pro-bridi to a selbri.
lujvo k1 believes (without evidence/proof) that the god/deity c1 exists. Cf. seljda, nalceikri, ceirsenpi.
lujvo x1 is a/the habitation/dwelling/house of god x2. Cf. ceizda, lijda.
lujvo c1 is an agnostic. Cf. cevni, senpi, nalceikri, lijda.
lujvo z1 is the Heaven of religious community c2. Cf. ceirselxa'u, lijda.
fu'ivla x1 is a polo shirt of material x2. A T-shaped shirt with a collar, typically a two- or three-button placket, and an optional pocket. Cf. creka.
lujvo g1=c2 is an arrow made of g2 fired/launched by c1. Cf. cecla, grana, bagyce'a.

lujvo g1 (person/mass) attacks with a projectile weapon/shoots victim g2 with goal/objective g3 using launcher/gun c1 which launches/fires/shoots projectile/missle c2 propelled by propellant/propulsion c3. Cf. cecla, gunta.

cmene x1 is Sagittarius [astronomical constellation/astrological sign]. From shooter (=celgunta). The Babylonians identified Sagittarius as the god Pabilsaĝ, a strange centaur-like creature firing an arrow from a bow.The sumerian name may be translated as the 'Forefather' or 'Chief Ancestor' (=barda dzena?). In Greek mythology, Sagittarius is identified as a centaur: half human, half horse.
lujvo x1 is December of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavrelmasti, kanbyma'i, nanca.
lujvo xa1=c1 is a gun/cannon/firearm for use against xa2 by xa3, launching projectile c2 propelled by c3. jvajvo; Gismu deep structure is "cecla gi'e xarci".
lujvo l1=c1 is a tribe with members including l1 according standard l3.
lujvo s1 pertains to community s2=c2 Cultural gismu replacement lujvo for communities: From gismu cecmu and srana

gismu rafsi: cne x1 varies/changes in property/quantity x2 (ka/ni) in amount/degree x3 under conditions x4. Non-resultative, not-necessarily causal change. (cf. cenba which is non-resultative, galfi which is resultative and causal, stika which is non-resultative and causal; stodi, zasni, binxo)
lujvo x1 is x2 percent of x3 in dimension/aspect x3. Cf. ce'i.
gismu rafsi: ces x1 is holy/sacred to person/people/culture/religion/cult/group x2. See also cevni, krici, latna, pruxi, lijda, sinma.

gismu rafsi: cen x1 is a hundredth [1/100; 1*10^{-2}] of x2 in dimension/aspect x3 (default is units). See also grake, mitre, snidu, stero, delno, molro, kelvo, xampo, gradu, litce, merli, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.
lujvo m1=c1 is m2=c2 centimeter(s) / hundredth(s) of a meter [metric unit] in length (default 1) measured in direction m3=c3 by standard x4=m3. Cf. navytre, centi, mitre.

gismu rafsi: ced x1 is an heir to/is to inherit x2 (object/quality) from x3 according to rule x4. Pedantically, inheriting an object should be a sumti-raising (tu'a if non-abstract in x2) of inheriting loka ponse the object - the ownership of the object (= posycerda, posyselcerda for unambiguous semantics). See also jgina.
lujvo m1=c1 is the dawn of day m2=c2 at location m3=c3. Cf. vacmurse.

gismu rafsi: cer x1 is a morning [dawn until after typical start-of-work for locale] of day x2 at location x3. This morning (= cabdeicerni); tomorrow morning (= bavlamcerni); yesterday morning (= prulamcerni, prulamdeicerni) See also vanci, murse, tcika.
lujvo s1 (mass) is a breakfast composed of dishes including s2. Cf. dormijysai, vacysai, cerni, sanmi.
gismu rafsi: cre x1 is an expert/pro/has prowess in/is skilled at x2 (event/activity) by standard x3. Also competent, skilled. See also djuno, stati, kakne.
lujvo r1 blesses/sanctifies c1 in the name of person/people/culture/religion/cult/group c2 under conditions r3. Cf. ruxyzau, dapma, lijda, cevni, makfa, xamgu, vrude.
lujvo s1 worships s2=c1, which is holy/sacred to c2=r3, with ritual r1 having form/rules r4. Cf. cesri'a.
lujvo cu1=ce1 is a holy book containing work cu2 by (presumed) author cu3 for audience cu4=ce2 preserved in medium cu5. Cf. lijda, xebro, xriso, muslo, jegvo.
lujvo s1=c1 is a holy site to person/people/culture/religion/cult/group c2. Cf. ritli, cesri'a, cesri'isi'a, lijda.
cmene God. Cf. cevni, jegvon, jegvo, muslo, xebro, xriso.

gismu rafsi: cev cei x1 is a/the god/deity of people(s)/religion x2 with dominion over x3 [sphere]; x1 is divine. Also divinity; x2 religion refers to the religious community as a mass. See also censa, krici, lijda, malsi.
lujvo b1 is entirely in the future of b2; b1 begins after b2. Cf. cfari, balvi.
lujvo g1 notices g2 by means g3 under condition g4=c1. Cf. ganse, facki, sanji.
lujvo x1=g1 (person/agent) initiates/begins/starts/causes the beginning of x2=c1 (state/event/process). Cf. cfari, krasi, sisti, cfari'i, co'arbi'o.
lujvo p1 is preliminary to c1=p2's beginning.
gismu rafsi: cfa x1 [state/event/process] commences/initiates/starts/begins to occur; (intransitive verb). See also sisti, krasi, fanmo, co'acfa.
lujvo r1 is/are the ritual/proceedings for starting/commencing c1[event/state/process] by community r2 with rules c4. Cf. cfari, ritli, cfagau.
lujvo s1 realizes s2 under condition c1. Cf. sanji, cfaga'e.
lujvo x1 sits down on x2. Cf. co'a, cfari, zutse, nitytse, tsebi'o. Simple zutse refers to the act of sitting, whereas cfatse means the act of beginning to sit.
gismu rafsi: fik fi'a x1 is a work of fiction about plot/theme/subject x2/under convention x2 by author x3. Also story, lie, untrue. See also cukta, lisri, prosa, fatci, jitfa, jetnu, xanri.
gismu rafsi: cfi x1 (property - ka) is a flaw/fault/defect in x2 causing x3. See also cikre, srera, fenra, fliba, prane.
gismu x1 is a wedge [shape/form/tool] of material x2. See also tutci.
gismu rafsi: fi'u x1 (event/state) confuses/baffles x2 [observer] due to [confusing] property x3 (ka). See also pluja, cfipu, zunti.
lujvo s1 diagnoses/proof-reads/searches/tests/debugs for flaw/property c1=s2 in c2=s3 causing c3
lujvo j1 is a writing desk of material j2, supported by legs/base/pedestal j3, used by writer c1. Cf. bijyjbu.
lujvo f1=c1 writes/authors f2=c2 for purpose f3 from existing elements/ideas f4. Cf. cfika, cukta.
lujvo s1=c2 is a secretary to s2. Cf. briju, bijyjbu, ci'ajbu.
lujvo cu1=ci1 expresses in writing cu2=ci2 for audience cu3 using display/storage medium ci3 with writing implement ci4. Cf. ci'arfi'i, cukta, karni, notci.
cmavo BAI ciste modal, 1st place used in scalar negation in system/context ...
lujvo k1 plays game k2=c1 governed by rules c2 interrelating game parts (physical or conceptual) c3. Cf. ciste, kelci, nunkei, terjvi.
lujvo ke1=kl1 has score kl2 in game ke2=c1 governed by rules c2 interrelating game parts (physical or conceptual) c3. klani3 (the scale of the score) is implicit in the rules of the game.
cmavo PA5 digit/number: infinity; followed by digits => aleph cardinality.
cmavo cluster ROI* tense interval modifier: occurs infinite times, eternally; objective tense; defaults as time.
lujvo c1=z1 is more interesting than z2 to c2 in amount z4. Cf. ci'irme'a.
cmavo BAI cinmo modal, 1st place emotionally felt by ...
cmavo BAI ckilu modal, 1st place on the scale ...
lujvo x1 is a Wednesday of week x2 on calendar x3.
lujvo c1 is trigonometry of triangle j1. Cf. ci, jganu, cmaci, cibjgatai.
lujvo t1 is a triangle. Cf. cibjgacmaci, cibjgataidamri.
lujvo d1 is a triangle (musical instrument). Cf. cibjgatai, balzgibe'e, bikydamri.
lujvo g1 is g2 yard/yards (length unit). Cf. ci, jamfu, gutci, degygutci, jmagutci, birgutci, minli.
fu'ivla x1 is myrrh from tree species x2. Cf. ciblu.
gismu rafsi: blu x1 is blood/vital fluid of organism x2. See also risna, flecu.
lujvo x1 is March/the third month of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavmasti, nanca.

lujvo j1 has the rank of Major/Lieutenant Commander/Squadron Leader (equivalent of NATO OF-3) in military unit /organization j2. Cf. ci, moi, jatna, jemja'a, vairsoi, vonmoija'a, relmoija'a. Based on STANAG 2116: NATO Codes for Grades of Military Personnel.
lujvo m1=d1 is the middle finger of d2. Cf. degji.
lujvo x1 is a 3-dimensional vector with coordinates x2, x3 and x4. Cf. nacmei, relnacmei.
lujvo x1=kr3 is a three-way intersection of roads x2=kr1=kl1.
lujvo p1 is the third closest planet revolving around p2, with planetary characteristics p3, orbital parameters p4. Cf. pavyplini, relplini etc., terdi, solri, mluni, lunra, plinycma, tarci'e.
lujvo t2 is three-legged with legs t1. Cf. ci, tuple.
lujvo x1=xi2 is a three-wheeled device/vehicle, with wheel made of materials/having properties xi3. Cf. relxilma'e, karce.
lujvo v1 is a three-syllable word meaning v2 in language v3=s2 with syllables s1. Cf. relslakyvla, pavyslakyvla.
lujvo f1 is an uncultivated field of material f2. Cf. ricfoi, ricyci'e.
gismu x1 is cyan/turquoise/greenish-blue [color adjective]. See also skari, blabi, xekri, kandi, carmi, crino, blanu.
lujvo c1=p1 is a savage/wild person. Cf. cicre'a.
lujvo c1=r1 is a savage/wild human. Cf. cicpre.
lujvo cr1 wildcrafts cr2 from cr3=ci1. Cf. rarvelcange.
lujvo r1 is a hare of species r2.
lujvo x1 is wild rice of species/variety x2. Cf. dzizani, gurni.
lujvo s1=c1 is a weed of species s2. Cf. cicyspavi'u.
lujvo v1 weeds out plants s1=c1 of species s2 from v3 with/leaving result/remnant/remainder v4. Cf. cilce, spati, vimcu, cicfoi, cicyspa, cicyspafoi, cicycrepu.
gismu rafsi: dja x1 is food/feed/nutriment for x2; x1 is edible/gives nutrition to x2. See also citka, nitcu, pinxe, xagji, cpina.
fu'ivla x1 is a burrito/Mexican dish of ingredients wrapped in a tortilla including ingredients x2.
fu'ivla x1 is a quantity of couscous of ingredients including x2
fu'ivla x1 is a pizza with topping/ingredients x2. Cf. cidja, iptsa, pitnanba, nabypalne.
fu'ivla x1 is chometz. see also fomymledi, nanbrmatsa
gismu rafsi: cid x1 is a/the knee/elbow/knuckle [hinged joint, body-part] of limb x2 of body x3. Metaphor: a sharp bend/curve. See also korcu, jarco, jganu.
gismu rafsi: dro x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of hydrogen (H); [metaphor: light, flammable]. See also gapci, xukmi.
lujvo ca1=ci3 crawls on surface ca2. Cf. cidni, cadzu, cidydzu, cidykla, reskla. Similar to walking but without standing on feet.
lujvo t1 kneels on surface t2 on limb c2=x3 of body c3=x4.
gismu rafsi: cif x1 is an infant/baby [helpless through youth/incomplete development] of species x2. Also infantile. See also makcu, verba.
lujvo x1 is a caterpillar (larva of butterfly or moth - not sawfly) of species x2. Cf. toldi, cinki, sfani.
lujvo x1 is a flower bud of plant/species x2. Cf. banro, ba'orzu'e, ba'ostu, spati.
lujvo d1=c1 is a duckling of species/breed d2=c2. Cf. cipni, gunse, sovda.
lujvo l1 is a children's story about plot/subject/moral l2 by storyteller l3 to audience l4. Cf. ranmi, pemci, crida.
gismu rafsi: cig x1 is a/the gland [body-part] secreting x2, of body x3; x2 is a secretion of x1. Secretion (= selcigla). See also vikmi, xasne.
cmavo cluster PA* number/quantity: 3,000 expressed with comma.
gismu rafsi: cik (adjective:) x1 is awake/alert/conscious. See also sanji, sipna, tatpi.
gismu x1 repairs/mends/fixes x2 for use x3. A repair may be incomplete, fixing only one of the possible uses of x2, hence x3. See also cfila, spofu.

gismu rafsi: cki x1 (person) explains x2 (event/state/property) to x3 with explanation x4 (du'u). Explanation x4 is an underlying mechanism/details/purpose/method for x2 (= velcki for reordered places), generally assumed to be non-obvious; metaphorical usage with the various causal relations (i.e. jalge, mukti, krinu, rinka, nibli, zukte) is possible, but the non-obviousness, and the existence of an explainer with a point of view makes this word not a simple expression of cause. See also cipra, danfu, jalge, jinvi, krinu, mukti, nabmi, preti, rinka, sidbo, zukte, tavla.
lujvo s1=c1 daydreams about s2; s2 is a daydream of s1=c1. Cf. nunxumsne.
lujvo b1=c1 awakens/becomes awake under conditions b3. Cf. cikygau.
lujvo g1 (person/agent) wakes up c1. Cf. cikybi'o.
gismu rafsi: cic (adjective:) x1 is wild/untamed. Tame (= tolcilce). See also pinfu, panpi, tarti.
lujvo g1 ties j1 to j2 with c1.
gismu rafsi: cim x1 is moist/wet/damp with liquid x2. See also litki, lunsa, sudga.
gismu rafsi: cli x1 learns x2 (du'u) about subject x3 from source x4 (obj./event) by method x5 (event/process). See also ctuca, tadni, djuno, ckule.
gismu rafsi: cil x1 is a thread/filament/wire [shape/form] of material x2. See also fenso, nivji, skori, silka.
gismu x1 (property - ka) is a dimension of space/object x2 according to rules/model x3. See also morna, ckilu, merli, manri.
lujvo d1=c1 is a quantityof/contains/is made of mud from source d2 of composition d3, moist due to liquid c2. Cf. jduli.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantifier selbri: convert 3 to cardinal selbri; x1 is a set with the trio of members x2.

lujvo l1 is an implicitly metaphorical lujvo with meaning l2 and arguments l3 built from metaphor l4. Used to refer to metaphorical lujvo that do not contain any -pev- rafsi (for pe'a). The word cimjvo is itself an example of cimjvo.

gismu x1 is infinite/unending/eternal in property/dimension x2, to degree x3 (quantity)/of type x3. Also everlasting, eternity, (= cimnytei), eternal (= cimnyteikai or temcimni). See also vitno, renvi, munje, fanmo, sisti.
lujvo t1=c1 is an eternity. Cf. cedra.
lujvo j3=c1 is a/the black hole. Cf. cimni, junta, tarci, tarske, mu'eske.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert 3 to ordinal selbri; x1 is third among x2 ordered by rule x3.
lujvo r1 (event/state) moistens c1 with liquid c2 under conditions r3. Cf. djacu, carvi, litki.
lujvo t1=c1 is a swamp/marsh/wetland at location t2 with liquid c2
cmene Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region of China
gismu x1 (agent) kisses/busses x2 at locus x3. See also ctebi.
lujvo n1=z1=x1 is sexually deviant/perverted in activity/state n2=x2 in property z3=n3=x3 to person/by reference point z2=n4=x4; x1 is sexually perverted cf. cinse, cizra
gismu x1 is an oak, a type of tree of species/strain x2. See also tricu.
gismu x1 is a lion/[lioness] of species/breed x2. See also mlatu.
cmene x1 is Leo [constellation/astrological sign]. From cinfo (=lion; lojban); leo (=lion; latin). Many civilizations over thousands of years have portrayed the constellation of Leo as a lion.
lujvo x1 is August of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. bivmasti, kanbyma'i, nanca.
lujvo p1 is a transsexual person. Cf. datcinselta'u.
gismu rafsi: cij x1 is a wrinkle/crease/fold [shape/form] in x2. See also korcu, polje, boxfo, boxna.
lujvo j1=c1 courts/flirts with j1, exhibiting sexuality/gender/sexual orientation c3 (ka) by standard c4. Cf. cinse, jikca, prami, pampe'o
gismu x1 is an insect/arthropod of species x2; [bug/beetle]. See also civla, danlu, jalra, jukni, manti, sfani, toldi, bifce.
gismu x1 is thin in direction/dimension x2 by standard x3; [relatively short in smallest dimension]. See also rotsu, jarki, tordu, cmalu, caxno, plana, jarki.
lujvo s1 is a string of s2 material.
lujvo z1=c1 becomes thinner in direction/dimension c2 by amount z3. Cf. cinla, zenba.
lujvo m1=c1 is sexy/hot/attractive to m2 in aspect m3 by standard m4=c4. Cf. cinse, melbi, mleba'i.

gismu rafsi: cni x1 feels emotion x2 (ka) about x3. Also mood/humor (= nuncni). See also cmavo list ci'o, cumla, jilra, nelci, xendo, ckeji, cortu, jgira, kecti, kufra, manci, prami, steba, zungi, badri, burna, gleki.

gismu rafsi: ci'i x1 (abstraction) interests/is interesting to x2; x2 is interested in x1. Use x1 tu'a for non-specific interest in an object; interested in (= selci'i). See also zdile, kucli, manci, kurji.

gismu rafsi: cin x1 in activity/state x2 exhibits sexuality/gender/sexual orientation x3 (ka) by standard x4. Also: x1 courts/flirts; x3 could be a ka , ka , or ka , etc.; (adjective:) x1 is sexual/sexy; x1 is flirted with/courted by x2 (= cinfriti, cinjikca). See also gletu, pinji, plibu, vibna, vlagi.
gismu x1 [material] is a paint of pigment/active substance x2, in a base of x3. See also pixra, skari.
lujvo p1 paints surface p3 with paint p2=c1. Cf. cinta, punji, pirlarfi'i.
gismu x1 is a/are tong(s)/chopsticks/pincers/tweezers/pliers [tool/body-part] for x2 to pinch x3. See also tutci.
fu'ivla x1 is a panda of genus/species x2. Cf. latcribe, cribe, jungo, mabru.
lujvo x1 checks/investigates/examines/inspects x2 for property x3. Cf. cipra, catlu.
lujvo l1 experiments l2=c2 by means l3. Cf. lanli, cipra, tadni, birti.
gismu rafsi: cpi x1 is a bird/avian/fowl of species x2. See also datka, gunse, jipci, nalci, pimlu, vofli, xruki, danlu.
fu'ivla x1 is a buzzard of species/type x2 Genus Buteo
fu'ivla x1 is a dodo of species x2.
fu'ivla x1 is an emu of variety/species x2. This could also be used for any member of the Dromaius genus, of which there is currently only one surviving species.
fu'ivla x1 is a falcon (genus 'falco'). see falkoni
fu'ivla x1 is a pheasant/partridge/quail/peafowl of species/type x2 Family Phasianidae
fu'ivla x1 is a crow/raven of species x2. Cf. xekcpi, cipnrpika.
fu'ivla x1 is a cuckoo of species x2. Cf. cipni, parji, krotofaga, cipnrxuazine, sutybajycpi.
fu'ivla x1 is a gull of species x2 Family Laridae
fu'ivla x1 is a lory/lorikeet of species x2. Cf. spitaki.
fu'ivla x1 is a European magpie of subspecies x1. Cf. cipnrkorvo, xekcpi.
fu'ivla x1 is a stork of species/type x2 Genus Ciconia
fu'ivla x1 is a hoatzin of breed x2. Cf. cipnrkuku, cipni.

gismu rafsi: cip x1 (process/event) is a test for/proof of property/state x2 in subject x3 (individ./set/mass). Also examination, proxy measure, validation; (a set in x3 must be completely specified). See also ciksi, troci, jarco, pajni, saske.
lujvo p1 is a test-paper from source p2 for/proof of property/state c3 in subject c4. Cf. cipra, pelji, lanli.
lujvo ce1 is an historian of the history of ci2 according to standard ce3. Cf. balcu'e, balkulctu.
lujvo ct1 teaches history ci1 to audience ct2 by method ct5 (event). Cf. balcu'e.

gismu rafsi: cri x1 loses person/thing x2 at/near x3; x1 loses property/feature x2 in conditions/situation x3. x2 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event (rare for cirko), or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= po'ecri, posyselcri for unambiguous semantics). See also facki, ralte, sisku, claxu, jinga, pleji, canja, sfasa, dapma, binra, mipri.
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains cheese/curd from source x2. See also ladru.
lujvo m1 (person/object/event) is historical among community of persons m2 (mass). Cf. cirvai, circtu.
cmavo cluster ROI* tense interval modifier: thrice; objectively quantified tense; defaults as time tense.
lujvo v1 is historical/a landmark/watershed in the history of c2, according to v2=c3, in aspect/for reason v3 (nu/ka). Cf. cirmi'o.

gismu rafsi: ci'a x1 inscribes/writes x2 on display/storage medium x3 with writing implement x4; x1 is a scribe. Also x3 writing surface. See also papri, penbi, pinsi, tcidu, xatra, pixra, prina, finti for 'author' or specific authorial works, barna, pinka.
gismu x1 smiles/grins (facial expression). Smile/grin at something (= cismyfra). See also xajmi, cmila, frumu.
lujvo c1=f1 smiles at f3 under conditions f4.
lujvo t1 (hours, minutes, seconds) is the daylight saving time of state/event t2 on day t3 at location t4=c3. Cf. temci.

gismu rafsi: ci'e x1 (mass) is a system interrelated by structure x2 among components x3 (set) displaying x4 (ka). x1 (or x3) is synergistic in x4; also network; x2 also relations, rules; x3 also elements (set completely specified); x4 systemic functions/properties. See also cmavo list ci'e, cmima, girzu, gunma, stura, tadji, munje, farvi, ganzu, judri, julne, klesi, morna, tcana.
fu'ivla x1 is the minor key of tonic x2 of/with type/notes x3. Cf. cistrxioniano, zgike.
fu'ivla x1 is the major key of tonic x2 of/with type/notes x3. Cf. cistrxaioliano, zgike, zgika'u.
gismu rafsi: cti x1 eats/ingests/consumes (transitive verb) x2. See also cidja, pinxe, tunlo, xagji, xaksu, batci, gusta, kabri.
lujvo k1 is a kid of goat species k2. Cf. mabru, lanme.
lujvo z1=c1 is younger than z2 by amount z4. Cf. nilnalci'o, zatra'i, citme'a, citmle.
lujvo m1 is cute to m2 in aspect m3. Cf. citno, melbi, cinmle.
lujvo n1=c1 is a youth/young man by standard c2. Cf. citno, nanmu, bixma'u, xadbixma'u, verba.
gismu rafsi: cit ci'o x1 is young/youthful [relatively short in elapsed duration] by standard x2. Also age (= nilnalci'o); (adjective:) x1 is junior. See also laldo, cnino, slabu, verba.
lujvo p1 has a crush on/is infatuated with p2
lujvo t1=c1 is youngest among t4. Cf. citmau, nilnalci'o, zatra'i, jbena.
gismu rafsi: cir x1 is a history of x2 according to x3 (person)/from point-of-view x3. Also historic/historical (= cirtermo'i, cirvai). See also muzga.

gismu x1 is a season/is seasonal [cyclical interval], defined by interval/property x2, of year(s) x3. Also anniversary (= citsydei, na'arcitsydei), jubilee (= mumnoncitsi); the period of time may be short or long as indicated by x2, and may occur every year or every nth year as indicated by x3 (default every year); (x2 and/or x3 may need metaphorical restriction: djecitsi, pavdeicitsi; also equinox, solstice, time of year. See also cedra, crisa, critu, dunra, ranji, temci, vensa, jbena.
lujvo x1 migrates to x2 from x3 over path/route x4 in season x5.
gismu rafsi: civ x1 is a louse/flea [blood-sucking arthropod] of species/breed x2, parasitic on x3. See also cinki, jalra.
lujvo x1=c1=d1 is a monster/freak of species x2=d2, monstrous/freakish in property x4=c3 according to x3=c4. Cf. bi'amlu.
gismu rafsi: ciz x1 is strange/weird/deviant/bizarre/odd to x2 in property x3 (ka). Also alien, mysterious, deviant, queer, unusual, exotic. See also ranxi, rirci, fange, banli.
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of rubber/latex from source x2 of composition including x3. See also pruni.
lujvo b1 is bedcloth of material b2. Cf. kicne, matci, badgai, sipna.
lujvo x1 is a bedbug. Cf. ckacinki.

gismu rafsi: kaf x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of coffee from source/bean/grain x2. Brew based on a seed/bean/grain; e.g. also chicory coffee, decaf, postum. See also tcati, brewed from a leaf, barja, cakla.

gismu rafsi: kai x1 has/is characterized by property/feature/trait/aspect/dimension x2 (ka); x2 is manifest in x1. Manifested/property/quality/trait/feature/aspect (= selkai). See also cmavo list kai, tcaci, tcini.
lujvo k1 goes to bed from k3. Omit x3 = se klama (destination) = ckana (bed)
lujvo k1 is a bedroom in structure k2 surrounded by partitions/walls/ceiling/floor k3 (mass/jo'u). Cf. ctiku'a.
gismu rafsi: cka x1 is a bed/pallet of material x2 for holding/supporting x3 (person/object/event). See also kamju, kicne, nilce, palta, cpana, vreta, jubme, stizu, matci, zbepi, palne, sarji.
gismu rafsi: cap x1 is perilous/dangerous/potentially harmful to x2 under conditions x3. x1 is a danger/peril to x2. See also te bandu, te kajde, te marbi, se snura, se xalni.
gismu rafsi: cas x1 ridicules/mocks/scoffs at x2 about x3 (property/event) by doing activity x4 (event). See also cmila.
gismu rafsi: kej cke x1 feels ashamed/mortified/humiliated under conditions x2 before community/audience x3. See also cinmo.

gismu rafsi: kik x1 is a key fitting/releasing/opening/unlocking lock x2, and having relevant properties x3. Also x2 fastener, mechanism; code key (= termifckiku, kiktermifra); x3 is dependent on the type of key, but are those form properties of the key that enable it to serve the function of opening the lock - in the case of a metal key to a padlock, for example, this would be the shaft and teeth. See also stela.
gismu rafsi: ci'u x1 (si'o) is a scale of units for measuring/observing/determining x2 (state). See also cmavo list ci'u, gradu, merli, cimde, manri.

cmene x1 is Libra [astronomical constellation/astrological sign]. The symbol for Libra is the Scales. Since babylonian times, Libra has been represented intrinsically with law, fairness and civility, as the scales were commonplace in the livelihood of the people, throughout the ages.
gismu rafsi: ki'i x1 is related to/associated with/akin to x2 by relationship x3. See also cmavo list ki'i, ponse, srana, steci, mapti, sarxe, fange.
fu'ivla x1 is Albanian (Balkan) in aspect x2. Cf. ckiipyris, ropno.
gismu rafsi: kir x1 is grateful/thankful to/appreciative of x2 for x3 (event/property). Also gratitude (= nunckire or kamckire). See also cinmo, friti, pluka.
lujvo p1 is a diaper (absorbent garment) of material p2. Cf. cifnu, mikce.
lujvo k1 is a bookshelf attached to k2. Cf. cukta, kajna, sorcu, ckusro.
lujvo x1 is the x3'rd edition of book/publication x2 about subject/theme/story x4 by author x5 for audience x6 preserved in medium x7 . Cf. ckupra.
gismu rafsi: kul cu'e x1 is school/institute/academy at x2 teaching subject(s) x3 to audien./commun. x4 operated by x5. Also college, university. See also cilre, ctuca, tadni.
gismu rafsi: ku'u x1 is a conifer/pine/fir of species/strain x2 with cones x3. See also tricu.
lujvo p1 is a chapter of book c1=p2. Indices, appendices and forwards are also ckupau. Cf. ckupaupau.
lujvo x1 is a part of x2, which is a part of a book . x1 is a part of chapter x2 x2 is the name of the chapter, not the book. Cf. ckupau.
lujvo cup1 publishes cup2=cuk1 by process cup3. Cf. terkarni.
lujvo s1 is a library of books c1=s2. Cf. ckuzai.
lujvo z1 is a bookshop selling books z2=c1, operated by z3. Cf. ckusro.
lujvo c1 is a librarian by standard c3. Cf. ckusro, ckuzai, ckuzda.
lujvo s1 is library science with methodology s3. Cf. ckuzdaske, ckuzda, ckusro, ckuzai.
lujvo k1=b1 runs a marathon/long distance to destination k2 from origin k3 via route k4.
lujvo x1=ce1=cl1 is a rifle for use against x2 by x3, launching projectile c2 propelled by c3. Cf. clani, cecla, xarci, xumjimcelxa'i, mi'ircelxa'i, celgunta.
lujvo x1=d1=c1 is a sword / long knife weapon for use against x2=d2 by x3 with blade of material d3 long by standard c3. Cf. clani, dakfu, xarci, baldakyxa'i.
gismu rafsi: lau x1 is loud/noisy at observation point x2 by standard x3. See also savru.
lujvo k1=c1 is a limousine for k2, propelled by k3. Cf. clani, karce, marce.
lujvo z1 is longer/taller than z2 in direction c2 by margin z4. Cf. bramau, clame'a.
lujvo m1 is shorter than m2 in direction c2 by margin m4. Cf. clamau.
lujvo d1=cl1=cn2 is a giraffe of species/variety d2. Cf. clani, cnebo, danlu, mabru, friko.
gismu rafsi: cla x1 is long in dimension/direction x2 (default longest dimension) by measurement standard x3. See also slabu, condi, ganra, rotsu, tordu, barda, ganra, gutci, minli, rotsu.
lujvo p1 is a leaf of p2, long by standard c3.
lujvo p1 is a tall person, by measurement standard c3. Cf. claselxadni, torpre, brabracrida.
lujvo xa2=c1 is tall in stature by measurement standard c3. Cf. clani, xadni, clapre, brabracrida. Refers specifically to a body.
lujvo t1 is a long time/duration/interval/period/elapsed time from time/event t2 to time/event t3. Cf. tortei, cedra.
gismu rafsi: cau x1 is without/lacking/free of/lacks x2; x1 is x2-less. See also cmavo list cau, cirko, kunti, nitcu, pindi, banzu.
lujvo g1 is a cucumber of cultivar g2. Cf. clani, guzme, tityzme, guzmrkukurbita.
gismu x1 is a moss/lichen of species/strain x2 growing on x3; (adjective:) x1 is mossy. See also mledi.
lujvo n1=c4 is an instructional message about n2=c3 with contents c2 intended for audience n4=c1.
gismu rafsi: lir x1 (event) is early by standard x2. See also lerci.
gismu rafsi: lit x1 is polite/courteous/civil in matter x2 according to standard/custom x3. Also formal, ritual. See also ritli.
gismu rafsi: liv li'a x1 leaves/goes away/departs/parts/separates from x2 via route x3. Also: x1 leaves behind/takes leave of x2. See also litru, canci, vimcu, lebna, muvdu.
lujvo g1 (agent) fills c1 with c2. Cf. culno, gasnu, tisna.

gismu rafsi: cup x1 is a loop/circuit of x2 [material]. Also noose (= skoclupa, saljgeclupa; there is no indication of shape, but merely that the ends join/meet); closed curve defined by set of points (= cuptai). See also djine.
lujvo b1 nibbles b2 at locus b3 with b4. Cf. cmalu, batci.
lujvo b1=c1 decreases in size/becomes small to b2 under conditions b3. Cf. cmalu, binxo, cmaze'a, brabi'o.
lujvo ca1=cm1 is tiny/miniature/diminutive/very small in property ca2=cm2 to observer ca3=cm3.
gismu x1 is a mathematics of type/describing x2. See also mekso.
lujvo cu1 is a booklet/brochure about cu2, written by cu3 for intended audience cu4 in medium cu5=cm1. Cf. cukta, papri, karni.
lujvo c1 is tiny/miniature/diminutive/very small in property c2 with criterion c3.
fu'ivla x1 is a recursive function with arguments x2

lujvo t1 is a microscope used by t2=ca1 for looking at small things t2=ca2=cm1 which are small in property/dimension(s) cm2 (ka) as compared with standard/norm cm3. Cf. cmalu, catlu, tutci, le'otci, darvistci.
lujvo f1=c1 is a short story about plot/theme/subject c2 by author c3. Cf. cmalu, cfika, lisri, cukta, brafi'a.
lujvo b1=c1 is a destroyer of type/carrying b2, propelled by b3. Cf. cmalu, jamna, bloti, ni'ablo, brabrajamblo, brajamblo, badjamblo, vijblo.
lujvo g1 causes j1=c1 to decrease in the smallness of property/dimension c2 (ka) by amount j3. Cf. cmalu, jdika, gasnu, brazengau.
lujvo l1 is a mountain chain consisting of mountains c1 projecting from landmass c2. Cf. linsi, cmana.
gismu rafsi: cma x1 is small in property/dimension(s) x2 (ka) as compared with standard/norm x3. See also caxno, cinla, jarki, tordu, barda.
lujvo cman1=cman1is a hill in terrain cman2, small by standard cmal3. Cf. derxi, cmatcema'a, mantyzda.
lujvo z1 is smaller than z2 in dimension c2 by margin z4.
lujvo m1 is bigger/[less small] than m2 in dimension c2 by margin m4.
lujvo s1=m1=c1 is a woodchip/splinter of wood type m2, small as compared with standard/norm c3. Cf. tricu, mudypu'o.
gismu rafsi: ma'a x1 is a mountain/hill/mound/[rise]/[peak]/[summit]/[highlands] projecting from land mass x2. See also punli, derxi.
lujvo x1 is a Mandarin orange/tangerine/Citrus reticulata of species/variety/cultivar x2 Cf. nimre, najnimre
lujvo n1 is a roll/bun/biscuit/bun made from grains n2.
lujvo p1 is an asteroid revolving around p2 with planetary characteristics p3, orbital parameters p4. Cf. solri, terdi, lunra, mluni, bisycmaplini, rokcmaplini, plinycma, jdikyplini.
lujvo t1=c1 is the smallest among set/range t4 in property/dimension c2 (ka).
lujvo r1 is a creek/stream in land mass r2, draining watershed r3 into r4/terminating at r4. Cf. cmalu, rirxe.
lujvo c1=r1 is a small rock of type r2 from location r3, small by standard c3. c1 is gravel. Cf. derxi, canre.
lujvo c1=s1 is a/the sprout/shoot of plant/species s2 by standard/norm c3. Cf. stani, cmalu, stanycma.
lujvo x1 is a village in administrative area x3 serving hinterland x4 small by standard x5. Cf. cmalu, tcadu, sosyzda, jarbu.
lujvo cman1=cmal1 is a hillock/mound/rise/knoll in terrain cman2, small by standard cmal3. Cf. cmalu, mutce, cmana, cmama'a.
lujvo r1=cmal1 is a rivulet on surface/terrain r2 draining r3 terminating at r4 small by standard cmal3. Cf. cmalu, mutce, rirxe, cmari'e.
lujvo m1=c1 is tiny/miniscule/diminutive in property/dimension(s) c2 (ka) as compared with standard/norm c3. Cf. cmalu, mutce.
lujvo t1 is a tone low in pitch/frequency from source t3. Cf. cmalu, tonga, smaji, lauble.
lujvo t1 is a brush/bushy vegetation of species/type t2. Cf. cicyspafoi, tricu, dzitricu, demspa.

gismu rafsi: ma'o x1 is a structure word of grammatical class x2, with meaning/function x3 in usage (language) x4. x4 may be a specific usage (with an embedded language place) or a massified language description; x3 and x4 may be merely an example of cmavo usage or refer to an actual expression; cmavo list, if physical object (= (loi) ma'oste); referring to the mental construct (e.g. propose adding a new cmavo to the cmavo list = ma'orpoi, ma'orselcmi, ma'orselste). See also gismu, lujvo, gerna, smuni, valsi.
lujvo xi1=c1 is a pony of species/breed xi2. Cf. xasli, sufti.
lujvo z1 is a hut of/for z1, small as compared with standard/norm c3. Cf. nolzda, si'erdi'u.
lujvo z1=c1 shrinks/decreases in property c2 (ka) by amount z3. Cf. cmalu, zenba, cmabi'o, braze'a, tolba'o.
lujvo g1 causes z1=c1 to decrease in property/dimension b2 (ka) by amount z3. Cf. cmalu, zenba, gasnu, brajdikygau.
lujvo b1 is a pseudonym/pronoun, replacing real name b2=c1 of x3=c2 in circumstance x4=b3. Cf. basme'e.

gismu rafsi: cme me'e x1 (quoted word(s)) is a/the name/title/tag of x2 to/used-by namer/name-user x3 (person). Also: x2 is called x1 by x3 (= selcme for reordered places). See also cmavo list me'e, gismu, tcita, valsi, judri.
lujvo s1 identifies s2=c2 by name c1 used-by namer/name-user c3 (person). Cf. cmetcita.
lujvo l1 is an onomasticon of names l2=c1 in order l3 in medium l4. Cf. vlaste.
lujvo t1 is a name tag/nameplate of t2=c2 showing text c1.
lujvo g1=v3 registers c2 with user-name c1 on system/application c3. Cf. cmene, vreji, gasnu, cmiveigau, cmisau, plivei, plicme, japyvla.
lujvo x1 is a morphologically defined name word meaning x2 in language x3. In Lojban, such words are characterized by ending with a consonant. Examples: lojban, jegvon, camgusmis.
lujvo b1=c1 becomes a member of group b2=c2 under conditions b3. Cf. cmima, binxo, kamni.
lujvo cm1=cu1 votes for cu2 among choices cu3 in voting group cm2. Applies to any election, not just public ones. Cf. turni.
lujvo k1 is suffrage entitled to k2=cu1 by standard k3. It is a civil right, selcemkrali. Cf. cmicu'a.
lujvo g1 puts together c1 into group c2. Cf. cmima, girzu, jmaji, gunma.
gismu rafsi: mi'a x1 laughs (emotional expression). x1 laughs at x2 (= mi'afra). See also ckasu, frumu, xajmi, cisma.

gismu rafsi: mim cmi x1 is a member/element of set x2; x1 belongs to group x2; x1 is amid/among/amongst group x2. x1 may be a complete or incomplete list of members; x2 is normally marked by la'i/le'i/lo'i, defining the set in terms of its common property(ies), though it may be a complete enumeration of the membership. See also ciste, porsi, jbini, girzu, gunma, klesi, cmavo list mei, kampu, lanzu, liste.
lujvo s1=c1 is logged into system/application s2=c2. Cf. cmima, slabu, cmeveigau, plivei, plicme, japyvla.
lujvo g1=v3 registers c1 as a member of c2, registration preserved in medium x3=v4. Cf. cmima, vreji, gasnu, cmeveigau, cmisau, plivei.
lujvo z1=c1 participates in employing means/taking action z2 for purpose/goal z3.

gismu rafsi: cmo co'i x1 utters moan/groan/howl/scream [non-linguistic utterance] x2 expressing x3 (property). Also shriek, most animal sounds, e.g. bark, cackle, meow, neigh, moo, honk, baa, crow. See also krixa, bacru, cusku, cortu.
lujvo x1 is an element of kind x2 with purity x3. Cf. xumsle, ratni, jinme, trano, cidro, navni.
lujvo d1=c1 is a chisel for carving d2=c2 with blade of material d3. Cf. rokci, mudri, jinme, tarmi, blixra, larcu, mruli.

gismu rafsi: na'o x1 [value] is a norm/average in property/amount x2 (ka/ni) among x3(s) (set) by standard x4. Also mean, normal, usual; (x3 specifies the complete set). See also tcaci, fadni, kampu, lakne, tarti, rirci.
gismu rafsi: neb ne'o x1 is a/the neck [body-part] of x2; [metaphor: a relatively narrow point]. See also galxe, cutne.

gismu rafsi: nem ne'u x1 (agent) rewards x2 [recipient] for atypical x3 (event/property) with reward/desserts x4. Differs from earned payment because of atypical nature; rewards need not be positive but are in some sense deserved from the point of view of the rewarder: positive reward (= zanyne'u), punishment, penalty, demerit (= malne'u, sfane'u); x4 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event, or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= posne'u, posyvelne'u for unambiguous semantics). See also dunda, friti, jerna, jinga, jivna, pleji, sfasa, venfu, prali, dapma.
lujvo x1 is the derivative of x2 with respect to x3. Cf. sa'o, cmaci.
gismu rafsi: nic x1 is orderly/neat/ordered in property/quantity x2 (ka/ni). See also cunso, kalsa.
lujvo x1 feels x2 (ka) about x3 feeling x4 (ka) about x5
lujvo co1=ci1 hurts emotionally due to ci3. Cf. cortu, cinmo, cnixai, jgicro, badri, ckeji.
lujvo d1=c1 is far/distant from d2 in feeling d3=c2.
lujvo j1=c1 shows emotion j2=c2 (ka) about c3 to audience j3. Cf. badri, gleki.
lujvo x1 empathizes with x2 in feeling x3. Cf. cinmo, kansa, dai, uu, ga'i, tolcumla.
lujvo v1 is an attitudinal meaning v2=c1 in language v3.
gismu rafsi: nin ni'o x1 is new/unfamiliar/novel to observer x2 in feature x3 (ka) by standard x4; x1 is a novelty. See also nuzba, slabu, citno, se djuno.
lujvo r1 is the sense/feeling in c1 of emotion c2 about c3. Cf. cinmo, rango.
lujvo x1=r1 (event) moves/touches x2=c1 (person), causing emotion x3=c2 about object of emotion x4=c3 with causation conditions x5=r3; x1=r1 (event) is moving/touching. Cf. cnicro.
gismu rafsi: nis x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of lead (Pb); [metaphor: heavy, malleable, soft metal]. See also jinme, tinci.
lujvo s1 is the heart (emotional self) of s2=c1.
gismu rafsi: nit ni'a x1 is directly/vertically beneath/below/under/underneath/down from x2 in frame of reference x3. Also underside, nether. See also dizlo, gapru, galtu, farna, loldi.
lujvo t1=c2 is the mood experienced by t2=c1 about c3. Cf. selcni, tcini.
lujvo v1 sighs due to emotion c2 (ka) about c3 breathing/respiring v2. Cf. cinmo, vasxu, cmoni, sipfru.
lujvo xr1 offends xr2=c1 affecting emotion c2 (ka) about c3 resulting in xr4 (state). Cf. cinmo, xrani, cnicro, jgicro.
cmavo rafsi: col CO tanru inversion operator; "... of type ..."; allows modifier trailing sumti without sumti links.
cmavo rafsi: co'a ZAhO interval event contour: at the starting point of ...; initiative >|< |.

lujvo x1=cf1 [state/event/process] commences/initiates/starts/begins to occur from its natural start; (intransitive verb). See co'a cfari. x1 starts from the very beginning. Also in the sense of 'starting anew' or 'starting from scratch'.
lujvo b1 starts to become b2 under conditions b3. Cf. co'a, binxo, tolsisti, tolsti, cfagau, cfari'i.
lujvo c1 (agent) starts to express/say c2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) for audience c3 via expressive medium c4. Cf. co'a, cusku.
cmavo rafsi: com co'e GOhA elliptical/unspecified bridi relationship.
cmavo ZAhO interval event contour: at the instantaneous point of ...; achievative; point event >|<.
cmavo rafsi: co'u ZAhO interval event contour: at the ending point of ... even if not done; cessative | >< |.
lujvo d1 is relieved from stress/discomfort d2 Cf. surla, kufra, snura, gleki.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: greetings in passing.
gismu rafsi: cko x1 soaks up/absorbs/sucks up x2 from x3 into x4; x1 is an absorbant. See also panje, sakci, lacpu.
gismu rafsi: con cno coi x1 is deep in extent in direction/property x2 away from reference point x3 by standard x4. See also clani, caxno, bargu, ganra, rotsu, barda, gutci, minli.
lujvo g1 (agent) hurts/causes pain for c1 at locus c2. Cf. cortu, gasnu, crogau, crori'a, cnixai.
gismu rafsi: cor cro x1 hurts/feels pain/hurt at locus x2. See also cinmo, xrani.
gismu rafsi: cpa x1 gets/procures/acquires/obtains/accepts x2 from source x3 [previous possessor not implied]. Also fetch; accept a gift (= seldu'acpa). See also punji, lebna, vimcu.

gismu x1 is upon/atop/resting on/lying on [the upper surface of] x2 in frame of reference/gravity x3. (x1 may be object or event); See also se vasru, jbini, zvati, nenri, vreta, ckana, diklo, jibni, lamji, zutse, punji for lay upon, sarji, zbepi.
lujvo g1 causes c1 to [rest on]/[be on top of]/[lie on] c2 in frame of reference c3. Cf. cpana, gasnu.
lujvo g1=c1 rides/mounts/has sexual intercourse on top of g2=c2, in frame of reference/gravity c3. Cf. glepe'o, gaxygle.
lujvo f1=c1 refuses f2=c2 from c3. Cf. fapro.
gismu rafsi: par x1 climbs/clambers/creeps/crawls on surface x2 in direction x3 using x4 [limbs/tools]. See also klama, litru, bajra, farlu, plipe.
lujvo z1=c1 approves the receipt of c2 from c3. Cf. cpacu, zanru, fitytu'i, radji'i, zarcpa.

gismu rafsi: cpe x1 requests/asks/petitions/solicits for x2 of/from x3 in manner/form x4. Also demand (= mi'ecpe); x4 is a means of expression See also ve cusku.: a request may be indicated in speech, in writing, or by an action (e.g. petitions are often in writing, while begging/panhandling may be indicated by an action or even demeanor). (cf. pikci, te preti, te frati, se spuda, danfu)
lujvo cu1=cp1 pleas/[expresses request] cu2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) to cu3=cp3 via expressive medium cu4. Cf. cpedu, cusku.
lujvo x1 complies with/accedes to request x2 made by x3. Cf. cpezu'e, cperanda, vi'o.
lujvo x1 complies with request x2 from x3. Cf. cpedu, zukte, vi'o, cpetinbe.
lujvo x1 is a gryphon/griffin/griffon. Cf. cipni, cinfo, cizda'u.
gismu x1 is pungent/piquant/peppery/spicy/irritating to sense x2. Also prickly (= pecycpina). See also vrusi, kukte, cidja, panci, sumne.
lujvo s1 is a sense-irritating plant/thistle of species x2. Cf. spati, cpina.
lujvo t1=c1 is a hot/pungent spice causing flavor/effect t2 (event/property). Cf. tsaprpiperi, kapsiku, armoraki, cidja, kukte, cortu.
lujvo z1 is a nest of bird z2=c1 of genus/species/etc. c2. Cf. kolmba, sovda.
lujvo l1=m1 is a tractor pulling l2. Cf. cpumuvgau, trene, karce, pulni.
lujvo g1=l1 pulls m1=l2 to destination m2 from origin m3 over path/route m4 at handle/locus l3. Cf. catke, bevri, jgari, cpumi'i, trene, pulni.
gismu x1 broadcasts/transmits [using radio waves] x2 via station/frequency x3 to [radio] receiver x4. Also x1 is a broadcaster. See also tivni, benji, tcana.

lujvo c1 is a radio transceiver transmitting/receiving c2 on frequency c3 to/from transceiver c4. The x3 place may specify more than one frequency, for instance in cases where different frequencies are used for transmission and receipt. Cf. veltivni.
lujvo k1=c1 advances to k2 from k3=c2 via k4 using means/vehicle k5. Cf. klama, crane.
lujvo k1 is an anteroom of/in structure k2 surrounded by partitions/walls/ceiling/floor k3 (mass/jo'u). Cf. balku'a.
lujvo l1 is an initial letter in alphabet/character-set l2 representing l3.

gismu rafsi: cra x1 is anterior/ahead/forward/(in/on) the front of x2 which faces/in-frame-of-reference x3. Also: x3 is the standard of orientation for x2. See also sefta, flira, trixe, mlana, pritu, zunle.
lujvo v1=c1 is a front door/gateway/access between v2 and v3 of structure v4. Cf. ti'evro.
lujvo p1 is the front-cover picture/image/illustration showing p2 made by artist p3. Cf. crane, pixra.
lujvo c1=b1 becomes expert at c2=b2 under conditions b3 by standard c3. Coined because cilre makes it hard to talk about just learning about a subject. Cf. ckule, saske, ctuca.
lujvo j1=c2 is a profession (job) of person j2=c1. Especially a job requiring a high level of skill or training. Cf. jibri, gunka, certu.
gismu rafsi: cek x1 is a shirt/blouse/top [upper-body garment - not necessarily sleeved or buttoned], material x2. See also taxfu.
gismu rafsi: rep x1 (agent) harvests/reaps/gathers crop/product/objects x2 from source/area x3. See also critu, sombo, jmaji.
lujvo j1=c1 skillfully handles j2=c2 in event j3.
lujvo c1=xa1 is a geek/nerd of field c2=xa2 (event/activity) by standard c3.
lujvo x1 practices/exercises/drills/trains in/for action/event/performance x2. Cf. rapcreze'a, xadyplijvi.
gismu rafsi: rib x1 is a bear/ursoid of species/breed x2. See also danlu, mabru.
lujvo x1 is bearberry of species/variety x2.

gismu rafsi: rid x1 is a fairy/elf/gnome/brownie/pixie/goblin/kobold [mythical humanoid] of mythos/religion x2. Also orc, giant, demon or devil (when humanoid-form is presumed by the mythos/religion), bugbear, bogeyman. (cf. ranmi, especially for non-humanoid creatures of myth, lijda)
lujvo s1 (mass of facts) is the science of fairies/elves/pixies [mythical humanoid] of mythos/religion c2 based on methodology s3. Cf. crida, saske, ranmi.
gismu rafsi: ri'o x1 is green/verdant [color adjective]. See also skari, blabi, xekri, kandi, carmi, cicna.
gismu rafsi: rip x1 is a bridge/span over/across x2 between x3 and x4 [unordered, typically destination first]. See also bargu, kruca, ragve, kuspe.
gismu rafsi: cis x1 is summer/summertime [hot season] of year x2 at location x3. See also citsi, critu, dunra, vensa.
gismu x1 is autumn/fall [harvest/cooling season] of year x2 at location x3. See also citsi, crisa, dunra, vensa, crepu.
lujvo g1 (agent) hurts/causes pain for c1 at locus c2. Cf. cortu, gasnu, corgau, crori'a, cnixai.
lujvo g1 practices sadomasochism with g2=c1 with pain at locus c2. Cf. bikla, laktergu'i, darxi, tunta, pinfu, katna, jesni.
lujvo r1 (event/state) hurts/causes pain for x2=c1 at locus x3=c2. Cf. cpina, crotsapi, crovu'i, xrani.
lujvo t1 is hot spice. Cf. cpina.
lujvo v1 is a hot/spicy taste/flavor of/emitted by v2. Cf. crotsapi, cpina.

lujvo x1=j1=c1 is a rule permitting/allowing x2=j2=c2 (event/state) within system/community x3=j3 under conditions x4=c3 The use of c1 there is perhaps a bit iffy; the point here is that it's non-agentive.

lujvo t1 is a situation / condition / state / position that allows / is sufficient for event c2=t2 under conditions c3. As the whole point of this word is to ignore the agentive nature of c1, c1 has been dropped. Cf. curmi, tcini, rau, banzu.
lujvo v1 is a permit allowing c2 (event) under conditions c3, preserved in medium v4. Cf. jaspu, e'a.
lujvo k1=c1 is the audit committee of k3. Cf. catlu, kamni, trukamni, trokamni, gazykamni.
gismu x1 is a tide [cyclical/periodic expansion] in x2 caused by x3. See also xamsi.
gismu rafsi: teb x1 is a/the lip [body-part]/rim of orifice x2 of body x3; (adjective:) x1 is labial. See also moklu, korbi, cinba.
lujvo x1 is a nightjar/goatsucker/whippoorwill of genus/species x2. Cf. ctesa'acpi, rasycpi.
lujvo c1 is an owl of species c2. Cf. cipni, nicte.
gismu rafsi: tek ce'i x1 is a tax/levy/duty on goods/services/event x2 levied against x3 by authority/collector x4. Also custom, toll, tariff, tribute. See also pleji, flalu, turni.
lujvo m1 is dark of night of day n2 at location n3.
lujvo m1 is the midnight of n2 at location n3. Cf. nicte, midju, dormidju.
lujvo x1 is a nightingale of species/variety x2. Cf. sfanykavycpi, ctecmocpi.
lujvo s1 is a supper composed of dishes including s2. Cf. vacysai, dormijysai, cersai, cidja, citka.
lujvo cin1 is a/are chopstick(s) for eating cit2. Cf. jungo, ponjo.
lujvo cp1 orders food ci2 for cp2 from cp3 in manner/form cp4. Cf. cidja, gusta, barjyse'u, beipre, djabei, djabeipre.
lujvo d1 is a table knife for cutting food d2=c2, with blade of material d3. Cf. forca, smuci, palta.
lujvo g1 feeds c1 with food c2. Cf. citka, cidja, kurji, gusta.
lujvo k1 is a dining room in structure k2 surrounded by partitions/walls/ceiling/floor k3 (mass/jo'u). Cf. ckaku'a.
gismu x1 is a quantity of petroleum/oil from source x2. See also grasu.
lujvo x1 is an oil lamp using petroleum-based products, illuminating x2 with light x1. Cf. ctile, gusni, laktergu'i, fagytergu'i, dictergu'i, rastergu'i.
lujvo v1 is a fuel tank. Cf. karce, matra.
gismu rafsi: ti'o x1 is a shadow/the shade of object x2, made by light/energy source x3. See also manku, gusni.
lujvo p1 sets up diet p2 for c1 consisting of food c2. Cf. xadyplijvi, ctinei.
lujvo p1 is the digestion of food p2=c2 with output p3 passing through stage p4 of person/animal/plant c1. Cf. ctiru'egau, befru'e, djarunta, djaruntygau, djaruntyrango, xelbefru'e.
lujvo g1 digests food p2=c2 with output p3 passing through stage p4 of person/animal/plant c1. Cf. ctiru'e, befru'e, djarunta, djaruntygau, djaruntyrango, xelbefru'e.
lujvo s1 celebrates s2 with a banquet/feast. Cf. specfari'i, jbedetnunsla, balsai, nuncti.
lujvo t1 is cutlery for eating c2. Cf. ctidakfu, forca, smuci, palta.
lujvo x1 is x2 centuries in duration by standard x3. The default x2 is 1; Cf. xecto, nanca, cedra.

gismu rafsi: ctu x1 teaches audience x2 ideas/methods/lore x3 (du'u) about subject(s) x4 by method x5 (event). Also instruct, instructor, educate, educator, teacher, professor, pedagogue; (adjective:) x1/x5 is pedagogical. See also ckule, cilre, tadni.
lujvo ci1 is an education system interrelated by administrative policies ci2 among institutions ci3=ct1 displaying quality ci4. Cf. ctuca, cilre, tadni, ckule, balcu'e, ma'urcu'e.
lujvo cu1=ct1 is a textbook for teaching ideas/methods ct3 (du'u), by author cu3 for audience cu4=ct2 about subject(s) ct4 by method ct5, preserved in medium cu5. Cf. clinoi, ckule.
lujvo f1 is a lesson by c1 for teaching audience c2 ideas/methods/lore c3 (du'u) about subject(s) c4 by method c5 (event). *naljvajvo warning! Please use nunctu instead* Cf. ckule, balcu'e, ctucku.
lujvo x1=g1=c2 works on x2=g2=c5 for teacher x3=c1 to learn facts x4=c3 about subject x5=c4
