fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 NG (Nigeria) for people x2. Cf. gugdrnaidjiria.
fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 ''PK'' (Pakistan) for people x2. Cf. kisygu'e.
fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 PL (Poland) for people x2. Cf. gugdrpolska, polskas.
fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 RU (Russian Federation) for people x2. Cf. rukygu'e.
fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 SU (USSR) for people x2. SU is a ISO-3166 code exceptionally reserved from June 2008. Cf. sofygu'e, softo, sesre
fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 TR (Turkey) for people x2. Cf. gugdrturkie.
fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 TW (Taiwan) for people x2. Cf. xa'anzu.
fu'ivla x1 is the country with the code ISO-3166 ZA (South Africa) for people x2. Cf. nanfi'ogu'e.
fu'ivla x1 is Korea. Cf. gugdrtcosena, gugdrxanguke.
fu'ivla x1 is Poland. Cf. polskas, gugdepulu.
fu'ivla x1 is Italy. Cf. italian, gugde'itu.
fu'ivla x1 is North Korea. Cf. gugdekupu, gugdrgogurio, gugdrxanguke.
fu'ivla x1 is Turkey Cf. gugdeturu, kulnrturkie, kulnrturko.
fu'ivla x1 is South Korea. Cf. gugdekuru, gugdrgogurio, gugdrtcosena.
fu'ivla g1 is Switzerland. Cf. gugdecuxe, xelvet, xelvetik.
lujvo j1 is the president of people g2 in country g3. Cf. gugde, jatna, balnoltru, vliraitru, viptru, truralju, trupauja'a, vajraifla.
lujvo n1 is a summit between j1=c1 (heads of state/government) about topic/subject c2. x2 are usually presidents or prime ministers. x3 are points on an agenda (= snuselpla). Cf. casnu.
lujvo c1 is a supranational union of member states g1=j1=c3
lujvo x1 migrates to country x2 from country x3 over path/route x4.
lujvo k1 is a diplomat/ambassador representing country k2=g1 in matter(s)/function(s) k3. Cf. jansu.
lujvo k1 is international in aspect x2

lujvo p1 is a state/province/region (first-level administrative division) of country p2=g1. Cf.gugde, pagbu. A province or region can also be a second-level administrative division; for these use gugypausle.

lujvo s1 is a county/district/province (second-level administrative division) of country s2=g1. Cf. gugde, pagbu, selci. A province can also be a first-level administrative division; for this use gugypau, or optionally vipygu'e if it is in a country with a federal government.
lujvo g1=c1 is sandy abrasive material. guska canre
lujvo ga1 combines individual gu2 into mass gu1. Cf. gunma, jongau.
lujvo gun1=gug1 is a federative state consisting of states/lands gun2
lujvo d1=g1 is a pool of water.
gismu rafsi: gud x1 is industry/industrial/systematic manufacturing activity producing x2 by process/means x3. See also cupra, fanri, rutni, zbasu.
lujvo gunm1 is a project consisting of tasks gunk2 done by gunk1 with goal/objective gunk3. Cf. gunka, gunma.

gismu rafsi: gun gu'a x1 [person] labors/works on/at x2 [activity] with goal/objective x3. Also: x1 is a worker/laborer. (cf. sazri, gasnu, se jibri; zukte - which need not be labor; physics term 'work' = ni muvyselbai, briju, jibri, lazni, selfu)

gismu rafsi: gum x1 is a mass/team/aggregate/whole, together composed of components x2, considered jointly. A description in x1 indicates of mass property(ies) displayed by the mass; masses may reveal properties not found in the individual set members that are massified, which themselves are not necessarily relevant to the mass property implicit in this bridi. See also bende, girzu, pagbu, cmavo list loi, lei, lai, ciste, cmima, kansa, tinci, mulgunma.
gismu rafsi: gur gu'o x1 rolls/trundles on/against surface x2 rotating on axis/axle x3; x1 is a roller. See also bolci, carna, jendu, slanu.
gismu x1 is a goose/[gander] of species/breed x2. See also cipni.
gismu rafsi: gut x1 (person/mass) attacks/invades/commits aggression upon victim x2 with goal/objective x3. See also bradi, damba, darxi, jamna, jenca, jursa.

lujvo s1 is a communist ideology (default: Marxist-Leninist) as it applies to the governance of people/territory/domain t2 based on the works of thinker(s) s3 From gunka, turni, sidbo. Cf. trudjigri, ka'irtrusi'o, dzejdasratrusi'o, vricykricrutrusi'o, fairpaltrusi'o, natpamtrusi'o, tsarainaitrusi'o.
cmene Canton Based on the local Cantomese pronunciation. For the name based on the Chinese Mandarin pronunciation see guanJOUS.
lujvo x1=ga1 rolls object x2=gu1 on/against surface x3=gu2, with axis/ axle of rotation x4=gu3. See also gunro, gasnu, cu'arkubli.
gismu rafsi: gru x1 is grain/[British: corn]/cereal from plant/species x2. See also bavmi, cunmi, mavji, maxri, molki, mraji, rismi, sobde, spati, zumri, nanba, sorgu.
fu'ivla x1 is teff of variety x2. cf. gurni, pamsrasu, amxari
gismu rafsi: guk x1 blade/scraper/erosive scrapes/erodes/abrades x2 from x3. Abrade, abrasive (= mosyguska). See also balre, sraku, batci, canpa, mosra.
lujvo x1 is a photon. Cf. gusni, kantu, lektoni, kuarka.
lujvo x1 is x2 (default 1) light year(s). Cf. gusni, minli,solminli, tanminli, ki'otre, darno.
lujvo m1=g2 is shiny/gleaming/bright/reflective of light g1=m2 from source g3

gismu rafsi: gus gu'i x1 [energy] is light/illumination illuminating x2 from light source x3. [x3 illuminates/lights x2 with light/illumination x1; x2 is lit/illuminated by illumination x1 from source x3 (= selgu'i for reordered places); light/lamp (= tergu'i)](cf. dirce, manku, solri, carmi, ctino, kantu)
lujvo n1 is Diwali (Deepavali) celebrated by s1 with activities s3 from gusni nu salci
gismu x1 is a restaurant/cafe/diner serving type-of-food x2 to audience x3. See also barja, citka, kukte, sanmi, xotli.
lujvo b1=g1 brightens under conditions x2=b3. Cf. manbi'o.
lujvo x1 gleams/shines on to x2, the light source being x3. Cf. gusni, carmi, gusminra.
lujvo x1 is a lightning bug/glowworm/firefly of genus/species x2.
lujvo d1 extinguishes light g1 illuminating g2, the light source being g3. Cf. gusni, dicra.

gismu rafsi: guc x1 is x2 (default 1) short local distance unit(s) [non-metric], standard x3, x4 subunits. Foot (= jmagutci); yard (= cibjmagutci), pace (= tapygutci), inch (= degygutci), cubit (= birgutci). (additional subunit places may be added as x5, x6, ...); See also mitre, clani, ganra, condi, rotsu, rupnu, fepni, dekpu, minli, merli, bunda, kramu.
gismu x1 is a/the womb/uterus [body-part] of x2; [metaphor: nourishing, protective, giving birth]. See also jbena, rorci, sovda, tarbi, ganti, mabla.
lujvo c1=g2=p2 menstruates. Cf. gutra, pilka, cirko.
lujvo k1 is a tank propelled by k3. Cf. gunta, jamna, karce, jamkarce, xiljamkarce, sonjamkarce, tsakarce, karcycelxa'i.
gismu rafsi: guz zme x1 is a melon/squash [fruit/plant] of species/strain x2. See also grute.
fu'ivla x1 is a squash/pumpkin of species/strain x2. Cf. guzme, clazme, tityzme.
cmavo I sentence link/continuation; continuing sentences on same topic; normally elided for new speakers.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: acceptance - blame. See also nalna'e, nalpro, no'epro, nalzugjdi.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: approval - non-approval - disapproval. See also zanru.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: approval - non-approval - disapproval.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: approval - non-approval - disapproval.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: togetherness - privacy. See also kansa, gumna, sivni, sepli.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: appreciation - envy. See also ckire, jilra.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: familiarity - mystery. See also slabu, nalni'o, kufra.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: belief - skepticism - disbelief. See also krici, jinvi.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: belief - skepticism - disbelief.
cmene Yagi. One of the inventors of the Yagi-Uda antenna; or the name of the antenna itself
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: belief - skepticism - disbelief.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: agreement - disagreement. See also tugni.
fu'ivla x1 is ivy of species/variety x2.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: fear - security. See also terpa, snura.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought or.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought: (preceding sentence) if this sentence.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought and.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought conn question.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought x but not y.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought biconditional/iff/if-and-only-if.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought exclusive or; Latin 'aut'.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought whether-or-not.
fu'ivla x1 clicks (press and release) button/switch x2 to cause x3 (nu). Cf. batke, danre.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: sentence afterthought conditional/only if.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: respect - disrespect. See also sinma.
fu'ivla x1 is yohimbe of variety x2.
fu'ivla x1 is an ion of radical/(atom of element)x2 with x3 charges c.f. ma'u zei ionti, ni'u zei ionti, lektoni, xumsle.
fu'ivla x1 is a pizza with topping/ingredients x2. Cf. cidjrpitsa, pitnanba, nabypalne, fomymledi, cirla, toknu, tamca, cidja.
fu'ivla x1 is an IRC user on channel x2 in network x3. Add a me'e place for nickname, or a fi'o tcana place for server, if needed. Erase x2 using zi'o if no channel is involved.
cmene IRC (Internet Relay Chat) An Internet-based real-time text communication system. See irci.
fu'ivla x1 pertains to Italy/Italian culture/nationality/dialect in aspect x2. From the Italian prefix "italo". See also brito, bemro, ketco, xispo, glico, fraso, merko, latmo.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: love - no love lost - hatred. See also prami.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: love - no love lost - hatred.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: love - no love lost - hatred.
cmavo rafsi: jav JA logical connective: tanru-internal afterthought or.
cmavo NA bridi logical affirmer; scope is an entire bridi.
cmavo cluster NA* weak bridi affirmation; barely; almost not at all.
cmavo BAI jalge modal, 1st place resultingly; therefore result ...
cmavo cluster BAI* jalge modal, 1st place (event causal) nevertheless result ...
cmavo BAI javni modal, 1st place (by standard 1) orderly; by rule ...
cmavo UI2 evidential: I conclude. See also selni'i, ni'ikri.
lujvo c1 is a window displaying j2. jarco canko
lujvo ju1 is a scorpion of species ju2.

cmene x1 is Scorpius [astronomical constellation]/Scorpio [astrological sign]. The Babylonians called this constellation the 'Scorpion'. In Greek Mythology there are plenty of myths associated with Scorpio.
lujvo j1=x1 is a/the beak/talon-like jaw (body part) of j2=x2. Made from jgalu + xedja.
gismu x1 brakes/causes to slow motion/activity x2 with device/mechanism/principle x3. See also mosra.
lujvo j1=t1 is a tubular chime of material t2, hollow with t3, producing sound/note j2.
lujvo m1 is a steam engine driving m2. Cf. djacu, febvi, matra, jaurgacmatra.
lujvo x1 is x2 degrees Celsius / centigrade in temperature by standard x3. Cf. kelvrfarenxaito, glare, lenku, dunja, febvi.
lujvo p1 is a waterway to p2 from p3 via/defined by points including p4 (set). Cf. flecu, rirxe, klama, bloti.

lujvo t1=d1 is a board for use in water/(wind/kite)surfingboard/bodyboard/wakeboard of material/property t2. From tanbo, djacu. Also sufingboard (=bonjacta'o), windsurfingboard (=fanjacta'o), kitesurfingboard (=volfanjacta'o), wakesurfingboard (=blobonjacta'o).
lujvo fi1 is a gill of animal fe2=fi1 of species x3=fi2 Cf. fipfepri. See also fipybirka, fipyrebla for fish-body related words.
lujvo x1 is a (water) puddle on surface x2
gismu rafsi: jad ja'i x1 (object) adorns/decorates x2; x1 is an adornment/decoration of x2; x2 is fancy/decorated. Fancy/decorated (= selja'i). See also jemna, dirba, batke.
lujvo c1=j2 is plain/unadorned from c2=j1 (object). Cf. selja'i, jadypijne.
lujvo p1 is a brooch/fibula for fastening to/piercing p2, of material/properties p3. Cf. batke.
lujvo x1=s1=j1 is a decorative explosive/firework/roman candle decorating x2=j2 producing debris/pieces/fragments x3=s3 cf. jadni and spoja
lujvo p1 is a footprint on surface p2 made by foot/paw p3=j1
cmavo JAI convert tense/modal (tagged) place to 1st place; 1st place moves to extra FA place (fai).
cmavo cluster SE* convert time tense (tagged) place to 1st place; 1st place moves to extra place (fai).
lujvo l1=j1 picks at l2=j2 with l3=j3. Cf. lacpu, jgari, vimcu.
cmavo cluster SE* makes x1 the agent of a bridi; old 1st place moves to extra place (fai).
cmavo cluster SE* convert location tense (tagged) place to 1st place; 1st place moves to extra place (fai).
lujvo g1 collects j1 (mass) at j2 from j3. Cf. jmaji.
lujvo x1 is an accretion disk (in astronomy) Cf. tarci, kesyske
gismu x1 is a rocket [vehicle] propelled by jet expelling x2 carrying payload x3. See also cecla, danti, spoja.
cmene Jacob With French pronunciation /ʒa.kɔb/, where /ɔ/ is changed to its Lojban approximation /o/

gismu rafsi: jag ja'e x1 (action/event/state) is a result/outcome/conclusion of antecedent x2 (event/state/process). Also: x2 gives rise to x1 (= selja'e for reordered places); total (general meaning, but also = mekyja'e, pi'irja'e, sujyja'e). See also se mukti, te zukte, se rinka, se krinu, se nibli, mulno, sumji, pilji, mekso, cmavo list ja'e, ciksi.
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of starch from source x2 of composition including x3. See also patlu, samcu.

gismu x1 is a cockroach/orthopteran/termite of order/species/breed x2. Also grasshopper (= pipyjalra); cricket (= sagjalra); locust, termite (= mantyjalra or mudyctijalra). (Orthoptera includes grasshoppers, crickets, etc; termites are a closely-related non-Orthoptera, more akin to cockroaches than to e.g. ants); See also cinki, civla, manti.
lujvo s1 (set) collide with each other. Cf. janli, simxu.
lujvo g1 [agent/person] claps together/causes to collide/strikes together s1 from janli simxu gasnu
lujvo b1 is a warship of type/carrying b2, propelled by b3. Cf. jamna, bloti, ni'ablo, bratcejamblo, brajamblo, cmajamblo, badjamblo, vijblo.
gismu rafsi: jaf jma x1 is a/the foot [body-part] of x2; [metaphor: lowest portion] (adjective:) x1 is pedal. See also jicmu, genja, zbepi, tuple, jubme, xance, tamji.
lujvo ji1=ja1 conquers/wins ji2 from ja2 in a war over territory/matter ja3. Cf. jamna, jinga.
lujvo k1 is an armoured fighting vehicle/AFV propelled by k3. Cf. jamna, karce, gutyjamkarce, xiljamkarce, sonjamkarce, tsakarce, karcycelxa'i.
gismu rafsi: jam x1 (person/mass) wars against x2 over territory/matter x3; x1 is at war with x2. See also bradi, gunta, panpi, damba, darlu.
lujvo g1 is a squadron of aircraft v1. Cf. jamna, vinji, girzu, jamvinji.
lujvo v1 is a warplane of type/for carrying v2, propelled by v3. Cf. jamna, vinji, jamvijgri.

gismu rafsi: jab x1 is a bell/chime/[tuning fork] [tuned percussion instrument] producing sound/note x2. Also: x1 rings/tolls (i.e. if it rings, then it is a bell); resonates (one sense, = jabdesku). See also zgike, tonga, desku, slilu.

lujvo cr1=cl1=j2 is a tube top of material cr2. A shoulderless, sleeveless "tube" that wraps the torso, generally very tight over the breasts in order to prevent the garment from falling. "halterneck" (nebdadycreka) is its subtype. Suggested shortest fu'ivla form: ancrka. Cf. creka.
gismu rafsi: jan x1 is a/the shoulder/hip/joint [body-part] attaching limb/extremity x2 to body x3. See also birka.
lujvo x1 is a bazooka for use against x2 by x3. Cf. janco, jakne, xarci, sorjaknykarce.
gismu rafsi: jal x1 collides with/crashes/bumps/runs into x2. (also collide = simjanli for a collision between two moving objects); See also darxi.

gismu rafsi: jas x1 is a diplomat/consul representing polity x2 in/at negotiation x3 for function/purpose x4. (for) x3 polity, (use tu'a); also ambassador (= raljansu, trujansu). See also jecta, krati.
gismu rafsi: jat x1 is an account/bill/invoice for goods/services x2, billed to x3 by x4. See also jdima, vamji, vecnu, canja, jerna, dejni, jbera.
lujvo j2=k1 logs in to k2 with account j1 (username and password) from interface k3. The username and password may be connected with "joi". Cf. jaspu, klama.
lujvo v1=j1 is a password [issued to]/[used by] j2 (person), issued/confirmed by authority j3 allowing j4 (activity), in language v3. Cf. jaspu, valsi, plicme, snura, cmisau, cmeveigau.
gismu x1 is a suburban area of city/metropolis x2. See also nurma, se tcadu, ve tcadu.

gismu rafsi: ja'o x1 (agent) shows/exhibits/displays/[reveals]/demonstrates x2 (property) to audience x3. [reveal (= tolmipygau, mipyja'o, sivja'o); also: x1 shows that x2, x1 shows off x2; showing an object is generally expressed with a tu'a x2, since the properties of the shown object (other than its presence) intended for observation are seldom specified (simple presence could be expressed by leka Object. cu zvati)]; See also tigni, cipra, zgana, jvinu, lanli, mipri, simlu.
gismu rafsi: jak x1 is narrow in dimension x2 [2nd most significant dimension] by standard x3. See also caxno, cinla, tordu, tagji, cmalu.
lujvo z1=j1 is firmer/tougher/harder/more resistant than z2 by amount z4. Cf. jdari, zmadu, jaryrai.
lujvo p1=j1 is cardboard from source p2. Cf. tanxe, bonjarple.
lujvo j1=t1 is the tallest among set/range t4. Cf. jdari, traji, jarmau.
gismu rafsi: jap x1 is a passport issued to x2 (person) by authority x3 allowing x4 (activity). See also pikta, catni, curmi.
lujvo b1 is an embassy/consulate of j2 at b3. From jansu briju. Omit ambassador(s) b2=j1
gismu rafsi: ja'a x1 is captain/commander/leader/in-charge/boss of vehicle/domain x2. See also jitro, lidne, te bende, minde, ralju, gidva, bloti.
fu'ivla x1 is a pope of religion/patriarchy x2. Cf. jatna, jdaja'a.

cmene x1 is Aquarius [astronomical constellation/astrological sign]. From djacu, barfle, gasnu. Aquarius is identified as "The Great One" in the Babylonian star catalogues and represents the god Ea himself, who is commonly depicted holding an overflowing vase. In the Greek tradition, the constellation became represented as simply a single vase from which a stream poured down.
lujvo x1 is February of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. relmasti, kanbyma'i, nanca.
lujvo x1 is Wednesday of week x2 on calendar x3.
lujvo v1 is a pipe carrying v2=f2 to f3 from f4 fluid may be liquid or gas; see datnyfle for the computer metaphor
lujvo m1 is a steam engine driving m2. Cf. djacu, gapci, matra, jacfebmatra.
lujvo s1 irrigates/waters s3 c.f. djacu sabji c.f. jaursabypatxu
lujvo p1 is a watering can used by s1 to water/irrigate s3 made of p3 from djacu sabji patxu c.f. jaursabji
lujvo s1 is/are a reed(s)/wetland grass of species s2. Cf. djacu, srasu, jauspa.
lujvo m1 drowns in body of water d1.
lujvo s1 is a seaweed of species/type s2. Cf. djacu, spati, jaursrasu.

gismu rafsi: jva x1 is a rule prescribing/mandating/requiring x2 (event/state) within system/community x3. Regulation, prescription (also x2), principle, requirement (also x2), prescribe, require (conditions are usually contained within x2); x1 is regulatory; x2, x3 are regulated. See also flalu, ritli, cmavo list ja'i, marde, tcaci, tinbe, zekri.
lujvo x1 (object/person) is unimportant/not crucial/doesn't matter to x2 in aspect x3 under circumstances/in instance (in which x1 participates) x4=v_f cf. jai, na'e, and vajni

lujvo x1=p1j (object/person) seems pleasant to/pleases x2=p2 in property x3, in that x1 does/is/partakes in x4=p_fai This is the first defined lujvo using -jax-, the proposed rafsi for jai. See also pluka.
gismu rafsi: bam x1 is a bomb/explosive device with explosive material/principle x2. See also cecla, spoja.
gismu rafsi: jba x1 is a berry (fruit/plant) of plant/species x2. See also grute, tsiju, narge.
lujvo s1 is the birthday celebration of x2=j1 born at time j3. Cf. detke'u.
lujvo d1=j3 is the birthday [day,{week},{month},year] of j1 at location j4=d3 according to calendar d4. Cf. jbena, detri, terjbe, jbedetnunsla.

gismu rafsi: jbe x1 is born to x2 at time x3 [birthday] and place x4 [birthplace]; x1 is native to (fo) x4. x2 bears/gives birth to x1; also x3: natal day. See also fange, gutra, rorci, mamta, salci, citsi.

gismu rafsi: jer x1 (agent) borrows/temporarily takes/assumes x2 (object) from source x3 for interval x4. Credit (= jernu'e); borrow/assume a property or quality as a chameleon does (= zaskai, zasysmitra, zasysmitai). See also dejni, janta, zivle.
lujvo b1=j1 approaches/nears/draws nearer/closes in on j2. Cf. jibni, binxo, jbikla, jbize'a, la'irze'a.
lujvo g1 makes j1 close to/approximate j2 in property/quantity j3 (ka/ni). Cf. jibni, gasnu, jbibi'o, jbize'a.
lujvo jip1=jib1 is the end of jip2 at jip3 near to jib2
lujvo x1=j1=k1 approaches x2=j2=k2 from x3=k3 via route x4=k4 by means of transportation x5=k5. Cf. jibni, klama, jbibi'o, jbize'a.
lujvo j1=z1 is nearer/closer to j2 than x3=z2 by amount z4. Cf. jbirai.

gismu rafsi: bin bi'i x1 is between/among set of points/bounds/limits x2 (set)/amidst mass x2 in property x3 (ka). x2 (a complete set, generally ordered) defines the bounds/limits/range for x1. See also se vasru, nenri, zvati, cpana, snuji, senta, bitmu, jimte, kuspe, jibni, lamji, sruri, vanbi, midju, cmima, setca.
lujvo p1 puts p2=j1 close to p3=j2. Cf. jibni, punji.
lujvo t1=j1 is nearest/closest to j2 in property/quantity j3 (ka/ni). Cf. jbimau.
lujvo x1 is a neighbo(u)r of / living close/near to x2.
lujvo z1=j1 gets nearer/closer to j2 in property j3 by amount z3. Cf. jibni, zenba, jbikla, jbibi'o, la'irze'a.
lujvo c1=b1 converses orally in Lojban about subject c2 using sound/expression l1=b2. Cf. jbota'a, jbosnu.
lujvo l1=b1 is Lojban used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote).
lujvo l1 is Jbofihe. A computer program that parses Lojban text. Cf. lojbo, finpe, genturfa'i.
lujvo g1 is Lojban grammar for structure/text g2. Cf. glige'a.
lujvo x1 is a Lojbanic group/organization with role/purpose/function x2.
lujvo x1 is Lojbanistan / Lojbanic country of people x2
fu'ivla x1 is a boa of species x2. see also since, sincrxenakanda
lujvo x1 reflects Lojbanic Soviet Federative Socialist Republic culture/nationality/community in aspect x2 cf. lojbo je softo ke su'o gugde jecta ke'e bo fatri prali turni sidbo gubni and se
lujvo j1 is attentive towards/attends/tends/pays attention to object/affair j2=l1, which is lojbanic in aspect l2. From lojbo + jundi.
fu'ivla x1 is a bonobo of species/breed x2. See tcimpazi, smani.
lujvo n1 is Logfest. An annual Lojban festival
lujvo l1=p1 uses Lojban for purpose p3; l1=p1 is a Lojbanist.
fu'ivla x1 is a jbopomofo orthography (bopomofo orthography adapted for lojban) Cf. ciska, lerfu, la .tenguar.
lujvo l1=p1 is a Lojbanist in aspect l2. Cf. lojbo, prenu, jbopli.
lujvo c1 (mass normally, but 1 individual/jo'u possible) discuss(es)/talk(s) about topic/subject c2 in Lojban. Cf. jbota'a, casnu.
lujvo l1=v1 is a child who is a native speaker of Lojban.
lujvo lo1=li1 is Jbovlaste. A web-based Lojban dictionary editing system, and the contents of its dictionary. Cf. lojbo, valsi, liste, vlaste, vlacku
lujvo b1 is a congregation of believers of religion j1.
lujvo c1 is a priest/pastor/imam of community c2 adhering to religion l1. Cf. lijda, catni, jdatro, jdaja'a, ravboni.
lujvo x1=c1 is a scripture/religious book of religion x4=c4=l2 containing text x2=c2 written by x3=c3.
lujvo j1 is the head of religion j2=l1 including members l2 sharing common beliefs/practices/tenets including l3. Cf. lijda, jatna, jatnrpapa, jdatro, jdaca'i.
lujvo s1 pertains to religion of s2=l2 Cultural gismu replacement lujvo for religions: From gismu lijda and srana.
gismu rafsi: jar x1 is firm/hard/resistant/unyielding to force x2 under conditions x3. See also nandu, ralci, randa, ranti, tinsa, sligu, stodi.
lujvo c2 is a prayer of believer c1=l2 for deity c3 in medium c4 according to religion l3.
lujvo s1 is a paladin/holy warrior of army s2, and with religion l1.
lujvo j1 is the bishop/archbishop of j2 of religion l1. Cf. lijda, jitro, catnrpepiskopo, jdaja'a, jdaca'i. For 'archbishop' one can use 'lo banli jdatro'.
lujvo z1 is a sin/blasphemy according to religion z2=j1.
lujvo x1 is a warning message to intended audience x2 about danger x3 from author x4. See also kajde, notci
gismu rafsi: jdi x1 (person) decides/makes decision x2 (du'u) about matter x3 (event/state). See also pajni, cuxna, kanji, manri.
lujvo jd1=jm1 assemble/meet/gather/[form a caucus]  to make decision(s) jd2 (du'u) about matter jd3 (event/state)  at location jm2. Cf. jdice, jmaji, nunjmaji, nunpe'i.
gismu x1 (experiencer) decreases/contracts/is reduced/diminished in property/quantity x2 by amount x3. See also zenba, mleca, vimcu.
lujvo g1 reduces j1 in property/quantity j2 by amount j3. Cf. jdika, mleca.

lujvo j1 is a dwarf planet revolving around j2 with characteristics j3, orbital parameters j4. Cf. jdika, plini, pluton, eris, cmaplini, plinycma. In 2006, the International Astronomical Union (IAU)reduced the status of Pluto and Eris from 'planets' to a new category: 'dwarf planets'.

gismu rafsi: di'a x1 [amount] is the price of x2 to purchaser/consumer x3 set by vendor x4. x2 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event, or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= posydi'a, posyseldi'a for unambiguous semantics); price is something decided/set by the seller, and is closely akin to offer (friti), which is what a buyer may decide; (note that price is not he same as cost/expense, which is the actual amount exchanged in a transaction; the latter is vecnu or canja; neither is the same as "value" or vamji; in colloquial English, these are sometimes interchanged, at least partially because of the rarity of barter and bargaining in the marketplace). See also canja, friti, janta, jdini, kargu, pleji, dapma, vamji for 'value', ve vecnu for 'cost', canja, fepni, jerna, jinga, prali, rupnu, sfasa, vamji.

gismu rafsi: din di'i x1 is money/currency issued by x2; (adjective:) x1 is financial/monetary/pecuniary/fiscal. 'currency' sometimes is restricted to paper money (= pledi'i). See also fepni, jdima, rupnu, sicni, canja.
lujvo x1=m1=j1 is unwavering/determined/resolute in making decision x2=j2 (du'u) about x3=j3 (event/state). Cf. jdice, mutce, xarnu.
gismu rafsi: dul jdu x1 is a quantity of jelly/semisolid [texture] of material/composition including x2. (adjective:) x1 is gelatinous. See also litki, sligu.
cmavo rafsi: jev jve JA logical connective: tanru-internal afterthought and.
cmavo NAhE scalar affirmer; denies scalar negation: Indeed!.
cmavo cluster NAhE+BO negation sumti qualifier: that which indeed is. Cf. je'a, bo, na'ebo, no'ebo, to'ebo.
cmavo COI vocative: roger (ack) - negative acknowledge; used to acknowledge offers and thanks.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: roger (ack) - negative acknowledge; I didn't hear you.
lujvo ji1=je3 is a fountain expelling fluid ji2=je2 at location ji3. Cf. jetce, jinto.
lujvo c1=j3 is a volcano projecting from land mass c2. Cf. fagma'a.
cmavo JA logical connective: tanru-internal afterthought conn question.
cmavo BY1 shift letterals to Hebrew alphabet.
cmavo UI3 discursive: truth - falsity. See also jetnu.
lujvo ja1 (agent) proves that je1 (du'u) is true by standard/epistemology/metaphysics je2 to audience ja3 from jetnu jarco
lujvo x1 is political/pertains to the politics of territory/domain x2.

gismu rafsi: jec je'a x1 is a polity/state governing territory/domain x2; [government/territory relationship]. (adjective:) x1 is civil/political. See also gugde, tutra, turni, natmi, jansu, lanci, cecmu.
lujvo x1 is the x3 pole of x2
lujvo l1 is a meridian on celestial body/sphere j2 (default Earth) From jendu, jipno, linji, jedji'o. Cf. plinyxabykoi, sunsicyjudri.

gismu rafsi: jef x1 is x2 weeks in duration (default is 1 week) by standard x3. Re. x3, a week may be more or less than seven days, classically being tied to the time between trips to the marketplace; this week (= cabjeftu); next week (= bavlamjeftu); last week (= prulamjeftu). See also detri, djedi, masti, nanca.
lujvo x1=di1=dj1 is a regularly-occurring period of days off work [weekend] lasting x2=dj2 days, recurring every x3=j2=di3 weeks (default 1), for worker x4=g1, at job x5=g2
gismu rafsi: jeg je'o x1 pertains to the common Judeo-Christian-Moslem (Abrahamic) culture/religion/nationality in aspect x2. Also Muslim. See also lijda, muslo, dadjo, xriso.
cmene The Judeo-Christian-Muslim God. (cf. cevni, jegvo, xebro, xriso, muslo, cev)
cmavo rafsi: jez NU abstractor: truth-value abstractor; x1 is truth value of [bridi] under epistemology x2.

gismu rafsi: jel x1 burns/[ignites/is flammable/inflammable] at temperature x2 in atmosphere x3. Default x2/x3 to normal temperatures in air; ignite (= jelcfa), flammable/inflammable (usually = jelka'e or jelfrili). See also fagri, kijno, sigja, livla, sacki.
lujvo n1=j1 is toasted bread made from grain(s) n2. Cf. jelca, nanba, titnanba.
lujvo ja1 is a general of army je1 serving country/nation/group je2 (mass) in function je3 (activity). Cf. jenmi, jatna, vairsoi.

gismu rafsi: jme x1 is a gem/polished stone/pearl of type x2 from gemstone/material/source x3. Also jewel (= jmeja'i); gemstone (= x2, x3, or jmero'i, jmekunra); pearl (= selcakyjme - a gem found inside a shell, tercakyjme - a gem made of shell material, boijme - any ball-shaped gem), mother-of-pearl (= cakyjme). See also kunra, rokci, jadni, dirba, kargu, krili, pulji.
lujvo x1 is an army corps, a subdivision of army unit x2 which serves country/nation/group x3. Cf. jenmi, pagbu, jempaupau, jempausle.
lujvo x1 is an army division, a subdivision of army unit x2 which serves country/nation/group x3. Cf. Cf. jenmi, pagbu, jempau, jempausle.
lujvo x1 is an army brigade/regiment, a subdivision of army unit x2 which serves country/nation/group x3. Cf. jenmi, pagbu, selci, jempaupau, jempau, songri.
lujvo z1 is a military base for armed forces j1 serving group/community j2 in function j3.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: tanru-internal afterthought x but not y.
gismu rafsi: jen x1 (event) shocks/stuns x2. See also darxi, gunta, spaji.
gismu rafsi: jed x1 is an axle/spindle [tool] on which x2 rotates, of material/properties x3. See also se carna, gunro, tutci.
gismu rafsi: jem jei x1 (mass) is an army serving group/community x2 (mass) in function x3 (activity). See also bilni, sonci, xarci.
fu'ivla x1 is sesame of species/variety x2. syn. simsimu, xonxoli

gismu x1 (agent/person) earns/[deserves/merits] wages/salary/pay x2 for work/service x3 (activity). Also x2 earnings, reward (= zanseljerna or nemjerna), punishment/comeuppance (= sfaseljerna, malseljerna); x3 behavior; job (= terjerna); x2 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event, or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= posyjerna, posyseljerna for unambiguous semantics). See also jibri, pleji, vecnu, cnemu, canja, jdima, jinga, prali, sfasa, janta, kargu, vamji.
gismu rafsi: je'i x1 chases/pursues/(physically) follows after x2; volition is not implied for x1 or x2. x1 follows after x2. See also kavbu, rivbi, kalte, lidne.
gismu rafsi: jex x1 reflects Algerian culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also friko, xrabo, muslo, fraso.
gismu rafsi: jes x1 is a needle [pointed shape/form, not tool] of material x2. See also konju, pijne, jipno, kinli.
lujvo c1 is barbed wire. Cf. jesni, cilta.
lujvo x1 is a hedgehog/spiny anteater of species x2. general term for spiny mammals; see also ernace, zalgosu, jesyratcu
lujvo x1 is a porcupine of species x2.
lujvo s1 is a cactus of species s2.
gismu rafsi: je'e x1 is a jet [expelled stream] of material x2 expelled from x3. See also sputu, vamtu.
lujvo x1 has truth-value x2 under metaphysics x3 on scale x4. See also jei
gismu rafsi: jet je'u x1 (du'u) is true/truth by standard/epistemology/metaphysics x2. Words usable for epistemology typically have a du'u place. See also stace, jitfa, fatci, birti, cfika.
lujvo p1 judges the veracity of p2=j1 by standard/epistemology/metaphysics x3=j2. Cf. tcica, stace, jetnu, jitfa.
gismu rafsi: ja'u x1 is a/the claw/nail/talon [body-part] of x2; [metaphor: pointed, penetrating, physical weapon]. See also denci, jirna, batci.

gismu rafsi: jga x1 is an angle [2-dimensional shape/form] from vertex x2 subtended by lateral [segment] x3. Also (adjective:) x1 is angular; x2 corner; (segment x3 can be defined by interval). See also kojna, linji, konju, mokca.

gismu rafsi: jai x1 grasps/holds/clutches/seizes/grips/[hugs] x2 with x3 (part of x1) at locus x4 (part of x2). Hug (= birjai, pamjai); embrace (= xadjai); handshake (= xanjai, jikyxanjai), handle (= veljai, veljaitci). See also ralte, pencu, darxi, batke, rinju.
lujvo g1 ties j1 in a knot.

gismu rafsi: jge x1 is a knot/tangle in/between x2 (object/jo'u-objects). Knot (verb = jgegau, jgezu'e, jgeri'a, jgela'a), knot: fastening between two or more cords (= jgeterjo'e). See also pluja, julne, lasna, skori.
lujvo j1=j2=n1 is a pretzel made from grains n2.
lujvo c1=j1 is offended/[feels hurt pride] about j2 (abstraction). Cf. jgira, cortu, cnicro, cnixai.
gismu rafsi: gin x1 is a gene of creature [or locus on creature] x2 determining trait/process x3. Also chromosome = (gincilta, ginpoi). See also cerda.

gismu rafsi: jgi x1 (person) feels/has pride in/about x2 (abstraction). An emotional combination of satisfaction and respect/esteem towards property(ies) or action(s) of person/entity that has a specific tie to emoter; self-pride (= se'ijgi, tolcumla); use x2 tu'a for pride in non-specific actions/properties of someone. See also cinmo, cumla, sevzi, sinma, snada.
gismu rafsi: git x1 is guitar/violin/fiddle/harp [stringed musical instrument] with actuator/plectrum/bow x2. Also lute, viola, cello. See also zgike.
fu'ivla x1 is guitar with plectrum x2. Cf. jgita, jgitrsita, jgitrpipa, zgica'a.
fu'ivla x1 is a nyckelharpa [traditional swedish string instrument] with bow x2.
fu'ivla x1 is a pipa. Cf. jgita, jgitrgitara, zgica'a, jgitrsita.
fu'ivla x1 is sitar with plectrum x2. Cf. jgita, jgitrgitara, jgitrpipa, zgica'a.
fu'ivla x1 is violin/fiddle/ with bow x2. Cf. jgita, jgitrxu, mosyjgita, zgica'a.
lujvo x1 is violin concerto number x2 in key x3 composed by x4 performed by/at x5( event). Cf. zgike, nolzgi, konceto zei pagbu, konceto, jgitrviolino, pipnrpiano zei konceto, simfoni, zgifi'i.
fu'ivla x1 is an erhu with bow x2. Cf. jgita, jgitrviolino, jgitrpipa, mosyjgita, zgica'a.
fu'ivla x1 is a walnut of species x2. see also nargu, tricu
cmavo A logical connective: sumti afterthought connective question.
cmavo UI3b discursive: additionally. See also jmina.
lujvo f1=j1 defeats f2=j3 in competition f3=j4. Cf. fapro, jinga, bandu.
cmavo BAI jimte modal, 1st place limitedly; up to limit ...
lujvo x1 resurrects/brings back to life x2=j1 by standard j2. From xruti and jmive.
cmavo PA4 digit/number: approximately (default the typical value in this context) (number).
cmavo cluster PA* rounded up (appended after string of digits indicating a rounded value).
cmavo cluster PA* rounded down (appended after string of digits indicating a rounded value).
lujvo j1=c1 expresses/says opinion c2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) about subject/issue j3 to audience c3 via expressive medium c4 on grounds j4. j2 is defined by x2=c2
cmavo BAI jitro modal, 1st place (control) controlledly; under direction of ...
cmavo BAI jicmu modal, 1st place (assumptions); given that ...; based on ...
lujvo j2=m1 quits/retires from job j1 Elided SE from se jibri mulno.
gismu rafsi: jbi x1 is near/close to/approximates x2 in property/quantity x3 (ka/ni). See also darno, nenri, vanbi, jbini, lamji, zvati, cpana, bartu, diklo, stuzi.

gismu rafsi: jib x1 is a job/occupation/employment/vocation (a type of work regularly done for pay) of person x2. Working for another (= selplijibri). See also briju, gunka, te jerna which is employment specifically for pay and not specifically for another, te pilno which is employment not necessarily for pay and not necessarily regular or lasting but for another, se gasnu and se zukte for incidental activities.
lujvo c1 is a trade/vocational school at c2 teaching job skills c3=j1 to audience/community c4=j2 operated by c5
lujvo p1=j2 strikes (stops working), complaining about p2=j1 to audience p3 with action p4. Cf. pante, jibri, cpedu.
gismu x1 (object, or event: force) stirs/mixes/[roils/agitates] fluid (gas/liquid) x2. Convection (= nenflejicla); agentive stirring (= jiclygau, jiclyzu'e). See also fanza, tunta, mixre.

gismu rafsi: cmu x1 is a basis/foundation/underlying or fundamental principle of x2; x1 is at the bottom of x2. x2 is founded on basis x1 (= selcmu for reordered places); (adjective:) x1 is basic/basal/fundamental); (generally events and properties will be bases for events and states, while objects may be bases/bottoms for objects). See also cmavo list ji'u, jamfu, zbepi, genja, krasi.
lujvo c1 is a twig/sprig of j2 from jimca cmalu
lujvo x1 is cladistics about organisms x2 according to x3.

lujvo k1=jm1=ji3 is a phylum [animals]/division [plants] within/of kingdom [biology] k2=ji2. From jimca, jmive, klesi. For biological cathegory in general (=mivyske klesi), domain (=?), kingdom (=seljimcymivykle), phylum (=this definition), class (=xeljutsi), order (=veljutsi), family (=terjutsi), genus (=seljutsi), species (=jutsi).
lujvo x1 is a pseudocoelomate with pseudocoelom x2.
lujvo xu1 is wrong, falsely claiming xu2=j1, by truth standard xu3. Cf. xusra, srera.

gismu rafsi: jij x1 (person) intuits x2 (du'u) about subject x3; [epistemology]. Words usable for epistemology typically have a du'u place. See also djuno, facki, jimpe, jinvi, nabmi, pensi, sidbo, smadi.
lujvo jin1=jij1 has intuition-based opinion (suspicion) jin2=jij2 (du'u) on subject jin3=jij3
gismu rafsi: jik x1 interacts/behaves socially with x2; x1 socializes with/is sociable towards x2. See also tarti, penmi.
gismu x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of liquor/spirits distilled from x2. See also barja, vanju, birje, xalka.
lujvo s1=j1 is aloof/alone/solitary/a hermit, separated from s2=j1.
lujvo s1 commits faux pas (social error) s2, which is wrong under conditions s3 according to standard s4.
lujvo t1 is an institution governing social/cooperative human behaviour t2. Use x2 tu'a for e.g. education. Cf. turni
lujvo jd1=ji1 is tactful in making decision jd2 in matter jd3 (event/state) in social interaction with ji2.
gismu rafsi: jil x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of alkali/base of composition including x2. (adjective:) x1 is alkaline. See also sodna, bakri, sodva.
gismu x1 (person) is jealous of/envies x2 (person) about/for x3 (property - ka). See also cinmo.
lujvo j1=b1 is a prosthetic bone made of metal, performing function b2 in body b3.
gismu rafsi: jic x1 is a branch/bough/limb of x2; x2 forks into branches x1; [preferred over metaphorical birka]. Also appendage. See also birka, rebla, tuple.
lujvo z1 is an anvil for striking metal d2=j2 with instrument d3. Cf. mruli.
lujvo s1 is a zing/clang produced by metal j1=d2=s2 being hit.
lujvo x1 is Friday of week x2 on calendar x3.
gismu rafsi: jmi x1 understands/comprehends fact/truth x2 (du'u) about subject x3; x1 understands (fi) x3. See also djuno, jijnu, morna, smuni, saske, viska.
lujvo j1=s1 is a wire/cable of metal j2=s2 This may be a single or multiple strand, but must be metallic.

gismu rafsi: jit x1 is a limit/extreme/bound/border/[confinement] of x2 in property/domain x3. Restrain/constrain within limits (= jitri'u, jitygau, jityzu'e). See also cmavo list ji'e, traji, korbi, kuspe, rinju, bapli, curmi, fanta, jbini.
gismu x1 is a pair of shears/scissors for cutting x2. See also katna.

gismu rafsi: jig ji'a x1 (person/team) wins/gains prize x2 from/over x3 [competitors/losers] in competition x4. Also: x1 is a victor; x2 reward; x3 competitors here are opponents and in many situations, defeated/losers, vs. the set of those competing for a goal; x2 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event, or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= posyji'a, posyselji'a for unambiguous semantics). See also cirko, jivna, talsa, cnemu, prali, pleji, sfasa, jdima, jerna, bradi, kargu, kelci.
gismu x1 is a vaccine/immune-system stimulant protecting x2 against disease x3 introduced by method x4. Also serum; inoculation (= jestu'u veljinku). See also jurme, mikce, jesni, bilma.
lujvo t1=j1 is an immune-system deficiency of j2. From jinku, toldu'e. t2, t3, j3, j4 based on relative uselessness (you could use tanru to get what type-of immune deficiency you're referring at).

gismu rafsi: jim x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of made of metal of composition including x2. (adjective:) x1 is metallic. See also cnisa, gasta, lastu, margu, nikle, ransu, romge, sodna, tinci, tirse, tunka, zinki, kunra, sodva.
fu'ivla x1 is beryllium. see also jinme, xukmi
fu'ivla x1 is titanium (metal). See also: jinme
gismu rafsi: jir x1 (object/person) is immersed/submerged/bathes in liquid x2. Take a bath/bathe (= jirsezlu'i). See also lumci, nenri, jinsa.
gismu rafsi: jis x1 (object) is clean/pure of material/contaminant/dirt x2 by standard x3. See also lumci, jinru, curve, sepli.
lujvo d1=s1 is a ring/belt/band/girdle around/circling/ringing s2 near total containment in some dimension(s).
lujvo n1 is a quantity of doughnut. Cf. jinynanba.
gismu x1 is a well/spring of fluid x2 at location x3. See also krasi, djacu, fenra.
lujvo k1=j1 is a well in k2 containing fluid j2 at location j3. C.f. jinto, kevna.

gismu rafsi: jiv ji'i x1 thinks/opines x2 [opinion] (du'u) is true about subject/issue x3 on grounds x4. Words usable for epistemology typically have a du'u place. See also cmavo list pe'i, ciksi, jijnu, nabmi, pensi, senpi, sidbo, birti, pinka.
lujvo n1 is a bagel. Cf. jintitnanba.
gismu rafsi: jiz x1 (property - ka) is an innate/inherent/intrinsic/natural property/quality/aspect of x2. See also lakne, rarna, stati, cmavo list ka'e, tcaci.
gismu x1 is a chicken/[hen/cock/rooster]/small fowl [a type of bird] of species/breed x2. See also cipni.
lujvo x1 is a vertex of polytope x2 at locus x3.
gismu rafsi: jip ji'o x1 is a tip/point/vertex/extremity/end [0-dimension shape/form] on object x2 at locus x3. See also mokca, jesni, fanmo, kojna, krasi.
lujvo x1=g1 immerses x2=j1 in liquid x3=j2
lujvo l1 (agent) bathes l2=j1 in liquid j2=l4. Cf. cavlu'i, brabaktu.
gismu x1 is a/the horn [body-part] of x2; [metaphor: pointed extremity]. See also jgalu, bongu.

lujvo t1=j1 is a/the horn [brass-wind/lip-reed musical instrument; default jirnytabra refers generally to the common horn (brass instrument). "..the instrument is often informally known as the French horn. However, this is technically incorrect since the instrument is not French in origin, but German. Therefore, the International Horn Society has recommended since 1971 that the instrument be simply called the horn." (wikipedia). Also natural horn (=sampu jirnytabra), vienna horn (=vin zei jirnytabra or tabrviena), mellophone (=tabrmelofono), wagner tuba (tabrvagnri). See also jirna and tabra.
gismu x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of juice/nectar from-source/of-type x2. Water-based extract from a (generally) biological source. See also pinxe, djacu, grute, stagi.
gismu rafsi: jif x1 (du'u) is false/is an untruth by standard/epistemology/metaphysics x2. Words usable for epistemology typically have a du'u place. See also fatci, stace, jetnu, cfika.

gismu rafsi: tro x1 has control over/harnesses/manages/directs/conducts x2 in x3 (activity/event/performance). x2 are aspects/individuals controlled within activity/event x3; manage (= selzuktro, selzukfu'e, gu'etro, gunfu'e, xaktro, xakfu'e) (as distinct from manager/boss = gunterbe'e, gunja'a, gunmi'e, gunca'i). (cf. cmavo list ji'o, bapli, te bende, gidva - which does not necessarily control or command, jatna, macnu, minde, ponse, ralju, rinka, sazri, turni, vlipa, xance, xlura)
lujvo b1=j1 comes to the conclusion that j2 [opinion] (du'u) is true about subject/issue j3 on grounds j4, under conditions b3. Cf. jinvi, binxo, lojycpa, ja'o.
gismu x1 weaves x2 from material/[yarn] x3. See also fenso, nivji.

gismu rafsi: jvi x1 competes/vies with opponent x2 in contest/competition x3 (event) for gain x4; x1 rivals x2. Also x2 opponent(s), competitor(s), rival(s); x3 competition, race; x4 prize, reward, recognition (gain may be internal or external). See also cnemu, jinga, talsa, bradi, fapro, kelci.
lujvo p2=j1 is the temperament (innate personality) of p1=j2. Cf. selpre, jinzi.
lujvo c1 is an ankle of j2=c3
lujvo j1=d1 is a toe of j2=d2. Cf. jamfu, degji.
lujvo c1 is a toenail of toe c2=d1 of body d3. Cf. degycalku, xandegycalku, jmatajycalku, xantajycalku.
lujvo g1 is g2 foot/feet (length unit). Cf. jamfu, gutci, degygutci, tapygutci, birgutci, cibjmagutci, minli.
gismu rafsi: jaj x1 (mass/jo'u) gathers/collects at location x2 from locations x3 (mass/jo'u). Also focus (= seljmaji). See also crepu.
lujvo j1 is a sole (part of foot) of j2. Cf. jmati'e, jmadegji.
lujvo c1 is the big toe nail of body t3=j2. Cf. jgalu, brajmadegycalku, jmatamji, degycalku, xandegycalku, xantajycalku.
lujvo t1 is the big toe of t3=j2. Cf. brajmadegji.
lujvo t1 is a heel of j2. Cf. jmadegji, jmani'a.
lujvo v1 is a pedal with function v2, fulcrum x3, and lever arm x4.
gismu x1 is a shoal [shallow hazard]/reef of material x2 in body of water x3. Rapids (= ri'erjmifa, ri'ercaxno). See also caxno.
gismu rafsi: min x1 adds/combines x2 to/with x3, with result x4; x1 augments x2 by amount x3. See also zmadu, banro, sumji, zenba, setca.
lujvo s1=j1 misunderstands fact/truth j2 (du'u) about subject j3, an error under conditions s3 by standard s4. Cf. ki'a.
gismu rafsi: miv ji'e x1 lives/is alive by standard x2; x1 is an organism/living thing. (adjective:) x1 is vital, organic. See also lifri, morsi, stuzi, zvati, xabju.
cmavo rafsi: jov JA logical connective: tanru-internal afterthought biconditional/iff/if-and-only-if.
cmavo UI3a discursive: metalinguistic affirmer. See also drani.
cmavo rafsi: jom JOI non-logical connective: union of sets.
cmavo JOhI join mathematical expression (mex) operands into an array.
cmavo BY1 shift letterals to Arabic alphabet.
cmavo rafsi: jo'u JOI non-logical connective: in common with; along with (unmixed).
cmavo rafsi: jol joi JOI non-logical connective: mixed conjunction; "and" meaning "mixed together", forming a mass.
cmavo cluster BY* letteral: ampersand character; especially used in standing for a mixed connective.
cmavo cluster JA* logical connective: tanru-internal afterthought exclusive or; Latin 'aut'.
lujvo g1 causes j1 to be joined to/connected to/united with j2 at common locus j3. Made from jorne + gasnu.
lujvo x1 are joined at/by x2. Cf. jorne, simxu, jonsimgau.
lujvo g1 [person/agent] join s1 together. Cf. jorne, simxu, gasnu, jonsi'u.
lujvo x1 is the union of sets x2 and x3. See also jo'e, terkruca
gismu rafsi: jor jo'o x1 reflects Jordanian culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also filso.

gismu rafsi: jon jo'e x1 is joined to/connects to/is united with x2 at common locus x3; x1 and x2 are a union. Also joined/fastened/attached by joint x3/by means of x3/with fastener x3; fastener (= jo'etci, jonvelyla'a); train, sequence of joined objects (= jonpoi; porjo'e for a single object joined into a sequence). See also lasna, fenso, kansa, pencu, penmi.
cmavo rafsi: juv JA logical connective: tanru-internal afterthought whether-or-not.
cmavo UI2 evidential: I state - (default) elliptical/non-specific basis. See also xusra.
cmavo cluster UI* evidential: although, even though, while, whilst
cmavo JOI vague non-logical connective: analogous to plain ".i".
cmavo COI vocative: attention - at ease - ignore me.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: attention - at ease - ignore me.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: attention - at ease - ignore me.
cmavo UI5 attitudinal modifier: certainty - uncertainty - impossibility. See also birti, cumki.
cmavo cluster UI*5 attitudinal modifier: intense certainty.
cmavo cluster UI*5 attitudinal modifier: certainty - uncertainty - impossibility.
cmavo cluster UI*5 attitudinal modifier: certainty - uncertainty - impossibility.
cmavo VUhU2 binary mathematical operator: number base; [a interpreted in the base b].
gismu rafsi: jub jbu x1 is a table/flat solid upper surface of material x2, supported by legs/base/pedestal x3. See also ckana, jamfu, nilce, zbepi, tsina, stizu.
lujvo x1 makes x2 pay attention to x3; x1 directs x2's attention to x3.
gismu x1 is an address of/are coordinates of x2 in system x3. See also tcita, cmene, ciste, stuzi.
lujvo j1=s1 is a hyperlink/URL of resource/web page j2=s2 for browser s3. Cf. kibro.
lujvo x1 is a paragraph about x2 including sentence(s) x3. Cf. jufra, mei, vlagri, vlali'i. See also ni'o, no'i.
lujvo p1 is a phrase of sentence p2=j1 about j2 in language j3.

gismu rafsi: juf ju'a x1 (text) is a sentence/statement about x2 [topic/subject/predicate/focus] in language x3. Phrase (= jufpau, suzrelvla, suzvla, gensle). See also valsi, bangu, gerna, cusku, smuni.
lujvo s1 is a fragment of sentence s2=j1 about j2 in language j3. Cf. jufra, spisa
lujvo t1=m1 is the intonation of sentence j1=m2 with characteristics t2=m3. Cf. jufra, tonga, morna.
lujvo j1=b1 is the Chinese-Mandarin language, used by b2 to communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote) Cf. jungo, bangu, jugygu'e, djunguos, xa'anzu.
lujvo x1 is a Chinese character in writing system x2 (traditional/simplified/bopomofo/etc.) meaning x3.
lujvo j1=g1 is China. Cf. jungo, gugde, djunguos, gugdecunu, xa'anzu, jugbau.
gismu rafsi: juk x1 is a spider/arachnid/crustacean/crab/lobster/non-insect arthropod of species/breed x2. See also cinki, danlu.
gismu rafsi: jup x1 cooks/prepares food-for-eating x2 by recipe/method x3 (process). Cook with heat (= glajukpa, glaterjukpa), bake (= tokyjukpa); fry (= rasyjukpa). See also cupra, bredi.
gismu rafsi: ju'e x1 is a net/filter allowing passage of x2, prohibiting passage of x3, netting properties x4. Also sieve. See also komcu, ciste, jgena.
lujvo x1 is x2 degrees in angular measure (default is 1) Cf. junla, radno, cacryra'o, plinyxabykoi, jedjipli'i. pi'e used in x2 indicates a base of 60.
lujvo s1=j1 (mass of facts) is microbiology studying microorganisms x2 based on methodology x3. See also saske, jumri.
gismu rafsi: jud ju'i x1 is attentive towards/attends/tends/pays attention to object/affair x2. See also kurji, zvati.
lujvo x1 tells/makes known to x2 fact(s) x3 (du'u) about subject x4 by epistemology x5. See also djuno gasnu
gismu rafsi: jug x1 reflects Chinese [Mandarin, Cantonese, Wu, etc.] culture/nationality/language in aspect x2. See also xazdo.
fu'ivla x1 is a rush of species x2.
gismu rafsi: jul x1 is clock/watch/timer measuring time units x2 to precision x3 with timing mechanism/method x4. Also timepiece. See also cacra, mentu, snidu, tcika, temci.
fu'ivla x1 is a juniper/cedar of species/variety x2. some trees called "cedar" are actually juniper; see ricrcedro, ckunu
gismu rafsi: jur x1 (person) is serious/earnest/has gravity about x2 (event/state/activity). Also solemn (= drijunri, ri'irjunri, tcejunri). See also tilju, xalbo, badri, ritli.
gismu x1 is the weight of object x2 in [gravitational or other force] field x3. See also grake, linto, tilju, bunda.
lujvo m1 (agent) weighs object j2 as m3 units on scale m4 (si'o) in field j3. Cf. junta, merli.
lujvo x1=k1 is a kitchen, in which x2=j1 cooks x3=j2, in home/building/structure x4=k2 surrounded by partitions/walls/ceiling/floor x5=k3 (mass/jo'u).
lujvo t1 is a frying pan/wok used by cook j1 for cooking/frying/sautéing j2=t1, made of material t3
lujvo x1 is a plantain (banana) of species x2. see also plantago, badna
lujvo p1 is a pot used by j1 for cooking/boiling/steaming j2=p2 with recipe j3; pot made of material p3

lujvo p1=j2 is a baked good/cake/mochi/doughnut/pizza dough/pie/macaroon/[cooked paste] made from p2 prepared by j1 according to method/recipe j3 Cf. jukpa, pesxu, titnanba, rutytisna. Originally coined by .lis.nunyn. on IRC.
lujvo b1 is a dumpling made from material x2 filled with material x3
gismu rafsi: jum x1 is a bacterium/germ/microbe/protozoan/amoeba [1-celled life] of species/defining property x2. See also vidru.
lujvo j1=p1 considers / reflects on j2=p2. Cf. junri, pensi.
gismu rafsi: jus x1 (event/action/state) is severe/harsh to x2 [victim/experiencer]. See also gunta, vlile.

gismu rafsi: jut x1 is a species of genus x2, family x3, etc.; [open-ended tree-structure categorization]. Also subspecies, order, phylum; (places do not correspond to specific levels in the hierarchy; rather, x1 is at a "lower" or "bushier" part of the tree than x2, x2 is "lower" than x3, etc.; skipping a place thus means that there is one or more known-and-unspecified levels of hierarchy between the two); not limited to Linnean animal/plant taxonomy. See also klesi, lanzu.
lujvo s1 is (biological) taxonomy based on methodology s2.
gismu rafsi: jux x1 (action) is clumsy/awkward by standard x2. See also sluji, muvdu.

lujvo l1 is a regular/predictable lujvo (compound predicate word) with meaning l2 and arguments l3 built from phrase l4 and having an argument structure according to rule j1. A Lojban-specific term. The approach of jvajvo is intended to at least constrain what the x2, x3, x4... etc. of a lujvo may be, and also to draw the semantic values of those places from the semantic values of the places of the component brivla. The rationale is that the place structure of an unknown lujvo should not require memorization. This was previously known as ``dikyjvo''; a mistranslation of ``regular lujvo'', as it used the wrong sense of ``regular'' (see dikni).
lujvo c1=j1 wages a contest c2=j3 on c3=j2 for gain j4. Cf. cpedu, jivna, jamna.
gismu rafsi: vin ji'u x1 is the view/scene/panorama/sight/prospect of x2 (object/location) from point-of-view x3. Also x1 is on display to x2/x3. See also catlu, kanla, viska, canko, jarco.
lujvo xi1 is a racehorse of breed xi2 competing in race j3.
lujvo k1 separates affix compound k2 into its constituent affixes k3; k1 does morphological analysis. Cf. lujvo, katna, rafsi, lanli, rafske, genturfa'i
cmavo rafsi: kam NU abstractor: property/quality abstractor (-ness); x1 is quality/property exhibited by [bridi].
cmavo BAI klama modal, 1st place gone to by ...
lujvo m1 is an axe for cutting k2 with blade m3=k1 propelled by m4.
lujvo d1 is an incisor of d2. cf. denci, gerde'i, crazalde'i, zalde'i
cmavo CAhA modal aspect: innate capability; possibly unrealized.
cmavo BAI krati modal, 1st place represented by ...

lujvo s1 is the concept of representative democracy (default: political representative democracy) as it applies to the governance of t2 based on the works of thinker(s) s3 From krati, turni, sidbo. Cf. dzejdasratrusi'o, vricykricrutrusi'o, fairpaltrusi'o, guntrusi'o, natpamtrusi'o, tsarainaitrusi'o.
cmavo PA5 digit/number: imaginary i; square root of -1.
lujvo s1=k1 is sickly/appears healthy to observer s3 by standard k2. Cf. bi'amlu.
cmavo UI2 evidential: I know by cultural means (myth or custom). See also kluju'o.
lujvo x1 scores/gains a point against x2 in competition/game/contest x3.
gismu x1 is a cup/glass/tumbler/mug/vessel/[bowl] containing contents x2, and of material x3. A kabri is normally eaten from by lifting it; a palta is not. See also palta, citka, blaci, tansi.
lujvo k1 is k2 (quantifier, default: one) cupfuls in quantity. Cf. kabri, klani.
gismu x1 is a camera/photographic equipment recording illumination type x2 images to medium x3. See also lenjo.
lujvo p3 takes a photo/picture p1 depicting/representing/showing p2. Cf. kacma, pixra, kacmyxra.
lujvo p1 is a photograph of p2 taken by photographer p3 in medium p4=k3.
lujvo p1 is a sequence of numbers in ascending order. Cf. kancu, porsi, namcu, zenba
gismu x1 reflects Canadian culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also bemro, glico.
lujvo k1=f1=b1 is the Canadian French language used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote). from kadno fraso bangu c.f. fasybau
lujvo k1=g1=b1 is the Canadian English language used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote). Cf. kadno, glico, bangu, glibau, bangenugu.
lujvo k1=g1 is Canada Cf. kadno, gugde, KEnydys, kenyDAS.
gismu x1 coughs/farts/burps up/out x2 [predominantly gaseous] from orifice x3. See also bilma, senci, sputu, vamtu.
lujvo x1 is caffeine with chemical purity x2
lujvo j1 is the president/[chairperson of the board] of j2=k1. Cf. kagni, jatna, fuzrai, kagytruralju, kagyfu'e, trokamni, vipkagni.
gismu rafsi: kag x1 is a company/corporation/firm/partnership chartered by authority x2 for purpose x3. Also enterprise/organization (if chartered). See also kansa, kamni, banxa, bende.
lujvo f1 is a corporate officer. Cf. kagni, fuzme, kagnja'a, kagntruralju.
lujvo p1 is a business park managed by community/polity/company p2 for businesses/firms/corporations of type k3.. Cf. kagni, panka, zacpanka, zdipanka, gubypanka, fanrypanka.

lujvo t2 is a/the private computer network that includes nodes/computers t1=s1 whose function/purpose is s2, installed across organization k1. Cf. kagni, skami, tcana, mujysamseltcana, internet, intranet. May or may not be an intranet.

lujvo d2 is/are the indebtedness/liabilities of company/corporation/firm d1=k1 to creditor(s) d3 for the provision of goods /services/loans d4. Cf. kagni, dejni, kagyselpo'e, terdejni, ze'i zei seldejni, ze'u zei seldejni, paurseldejni, na'arkagnoi.
lujvo p2 is/are an/the asset(s) of company/corporation/firm/partnership p1=k1 according to law p3. Cf. kagni, ponse, kagyseldejni, ra'erprali, fairprali, paurseldejni, na'arkagnoi.
lujvo r1 is CEO (Chief Executive Officer)/MD (Managing Director) of company/corporation/firm t2=k1. Cf. kagni, turni, ralju, kagja'a, kagyfu'e, fuzrai, trukamni, vipkagni.

gismu rafsi: jde x1 (event/experience) warns/cautions x2 (person) of/about danger x3 (event/state/property). Agentive warning (= jdegau, jdezu'e); an attempt to warn which may not succeed (= jdetoi, jdegautoi, jdezuktoi). See also ckape, nupre, snura, tcica, xlura.
gismu x1 is a shelf/counter/bar in/on/attached to supporting object x2, for purpose x3. See also balni.
lujvo t1=k2 is a cupboard for storing t2, made of t3, with shelves k1. Cf. kajna, tanxe.

gismu rafsi: ka'e x1 is able to do/be/capable of doing/being x2 (event/state) under conditions x3 (event/state). Also: has talent; know how to; know how to use (= plika'e). (cf. stati, certu, gasnu (in the time-free potential sense), cmavo list ka'e, cmavo list nu'o, cmavo list pu'i, djuno, zifre)
gismu x1 (agent) digs x2 [material] up/out of x3 [source/hole] with limbs/tool(s) x4. Also x1 cuts into x3 (with material removal). See also katna, plixa, sraku, canpa, sraku.
lujvo c1=k4 is an excavator/power shovel for digging in k3, operated by k1=c3. Not for pushing bulldozer.
lujvo s1 is a sob/sobbing produced by k1 with tears k2 about/for reason k3 (event/state). Cf. klaku, sance.
lujvo x1 is a teardrop wept by x2 for reason x3.
lujvo b1=k1 is an eyeball (body part) of k2. Cf. kalgai, kalgaikre, kalselvi'i, kalvi'i.
gismu x1 is a/the feces/excrement/dung/shit of x2 (animal/person); (adjective:) x1 is fecal (matter). Also crap. See also ganxo, pinca, vikmi, mabla, festi.
lujvo g1 is an eyelid of eye k1=g2.
lujvo ke1 is an eyelash (body part) of ke2=ka2. Cf. kalgai, kalboi, kalvi'i, kalselvi'i.
fu'ivla x1 is a squid/cuttlefish of species x2. see also sedjmacurnu
lujvo ke1 is an eyebrow (supraorbital ridge) of ke2=ka2=m2. Cf. kerfa, kanla, mebri, kalgaikre.
gismu rafsi: kar x1 (portal/passage/entrance-way) is open/ajar/not shut permitting passage/access to x2 by x3. As a doorway. See also ganlo, pagre, canko, vorme.
gismu rafsi: kas x1 is chaotic/disordered in property/aspect x2 (ka). See also cunso, cnici.
lujvo x1=v2 is a tear/tear fluid of x2=v1. Cf. kalboi, kalgai, kalgaikre, molselpu'u.
gismu rafsi: kat x1 hunts/stalks prey/quarry/game x2 for purpose x3. Also verb: to fish (= fipkalte). See also jersi, kavbu, sisku, rivbi.
lujvo v1=k2 weeps/lacrimates tear(s) v2 from v3 via means/route v4. Cf. klaku, kalselvi'i, kalboi, kalgai, kalgaikre.
lujvo k1 is the greatness/majesty/splendour/magnificence/grandeur of b1 according to standard b3. Cf. ka, banli, kamnolraitru.

lujvo k1 is a security condition of b1 protecting b2 from threat b3. When used as "security", x3 is a planned threat. "security" is comparable to "safety" (kamnu'a), "reliability" (kamylacri), and "continuity" (kamra'i).
lujvo k1 is quality/property exhibited by b1 of being foolish/silly/stupid in event/action /property (ka) b2. Cf. ka, bebna, nunbebna.
fu'ivla x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of camphor (chemical compound)
lujvo x1 is a society; x1 is social
gismu x1 is a column/pillar of material x2. Spine (= bogykamju), vertebra (= kamjybo'u). See also ckana, garna, sanli, slanu.
lujvo m1 tests/evaluates/measures j1's knowledge of facts (du'u) j2 in subject area j3 as m3 units on scale m4 with accuracy m5
lujvo k1=b1 is a vertebra of b3 ; b3 is a vertebrate. Cf. bongu, bogykamju, terbo'u.
lujvo x1 is a leek of variety x2. see also sunga, sluni, tu'ursluni
lujvo kam1 is the health of kan1 by standard kan2. Cf. kanro.
gismu x1 (mass) is a committee with task/purpose x2 of body x3. Board of directors/trustees/cabinet (= trukamni, gritrukamni). See also bende, kagni.
lujvo k1 is the majesty of t1=n1 being a regent/monarch of t2 by standard n2. Cf. ka, nobli, traji, turni, kamba'i.

gismu rafsi: kau x1 (property - ka) is common/general/universal among members of set x2 (complete set). Only fully universal sense applies; x1 must be found in all members of x2. For the non-universal sense see fadni and zilfadni. See also cafne, rirci, fadni, cnano, tcaci, lakne, cmima, simxu.
lujvo k1 is the relation of s1 to s2. Cf. srana, ckini, jorne.
lujvo k1 is the speed of s1 doing/being/bringing about s2. Cf. ka, sutra, nilsutra.
lujvo k1 is the fatigue of t1 in being/doing t2 (event). Cf. tatpi, sipna
lujvo k1 is the strength of t1 in property/quality t2 (ka). Cf. ka, tsali.
lujvo c1 is the childhood (state of being a child) of v1. Cf. ka, verba, vercedra.
lujvo k1 is the power of v1 in aspect v2 under conditions v3. Cf. ka, vlipa, trubasti.
lujvo x1 is the quality of whom/what is free to do/be x2=z2; x1 is freedom/liberty of x2=z2 Cf. ka, zifre, nunzi'e, selzi'e, zi'ejva.
gismu x1 is a goat/angora/[billy-goat/kid] of species/breed x2. See also lanme, sunla.

cmene x1 is Capricornus [astronomical constellation]/Capricorn [astrological sign]. From goat (=kanba). Capricornus is Latin for "horned male goat" or "goat horn". Anyway, both male and female of the genus Capra have horns.
lujvo x1 is January of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavmasti, nanca, jaurbeima'i, fipma'i, lanma'i, bakma'i, matsi'uma'i, mlajukma'i, cinfyma'i, xlima'i, laxma'i, rebjukma'i, celma'i.
gismu rafsi: kac x1 (agent) counts the number in set x2 to be x3 [number/count] counting [off] by units x4. (x2 is complete set); See also kanji, satci, merli.

gismu rafsi: kad x1 is dim/dull/pale/non-intense in property x2 (ka) as received/measured by observer x3. In colors, indicates unsaturated, pastel, pale (though blabi can also indicate a kind of paleness). See also blabi, carmi, klina, linto, manku, murse, ruble, skari, milxe, blanu, bunre, cicna, crino, grusi, narju, nukni, pelxu, xekri, xunre, zirpu.
fu'ivla x1 is a candirú of species/variety x2. syn. finprvandeli, pincyfi'e; see also latfi'e
fu'ivla x1 is a kangaroo of species/breed x2. Cf. daskymabru, daskycribe, sralo, plipe.
gismu rafsi: kaj x1 calculates/reckons/computes x2 [value (ni)/state] from data x3 by process x4. See also kancu, jdice, skami.
lujvo j1=k1 is a watch (portable timepiece) measuring time units j2 to precision j3 with timing mechanism j4. Cf. junla, temci.
gismu rafsi: kal x1 is a/the eye [body-part] of x2; [metaphor: sensory apparatus]; (adjective:) x1 is ocular. x1 is optic. See also jvinu, kerlo, viska, kumte.
gismu rafsi: ka'o x1 is healthy/fit/well/in good health by standard x2. See also bilma, mikce.
gismu rafsi: kan x1 is with/accompanies/is a companion of x2, in state/condition/enterprise x3 (event/state). x1 is together with/along with x2. See also kagni, jorne, gunma, girzu, lasna.
lujvo x1 do x2 together. See also jo'u

gismu rafsi: ka'u x1 is a quantum/ray/elementary particle/smallest measurable increment of property/activity x2. Quantum ray (= bonka'u). (cf. selci for masses and most objects; ratni, gradu, gusni, nejni, linji)
lujvo xa1=k1 is a roommate of/lives with k2 at location/habitat/nest/home/abode x3=xa2.
gismu rafsi: kax x1 is a conjunction, stating that x2 (du'u) and x3 (du'u) are both true. See also vlina.
lujvo k1 is a skin pore of pelt/skin/hide/leather k2=s1 from x3=s2. Cf. nazbi, pilka, xasne.
fu'ivla x1 is a chili/bell pepper (Capsicum) of species/variety x2. cf. cpina, spatrpiperi, tamca, patlu, tanko, mlongena
lujvo x1=p1 is a tattoo/body art/brand/[image on the body] depicting x2=p2 on animal/body part x3=s2 made by artist x4=p3 Cf. skapi, pixra.
gismu rafsi: kab x1 [observer] compares x2 with x3 in property x4 (ka), determining comparison x5 (state). See also klani, mapti, sarxe, zmadu, mleca, dunli.
gismu x1 is a car/automobile/truck/van [a wheeled motor vehicle] for carrying x2, propelled by x3 See also carce, xislu, marce, sabnu.
lujvo c1 is a sandal for protecting feet c2, and of material c3. Cf. tupcutci, smoka.

lujvo x1=c1=k2 is a self-propelled artillery gun for use against x2 by x3, launching projectile c2 propelled by c3. Cf. karce, cecla, xarci, xumjimcelxa'i, gutyjamkarce, xiljamkarce, karcycelxa'i, sorjaknykarce.
gismu x1 is a card [small nearly-2-dimensional shape/form] of material x2, shape x3. (x3 shape default rectangular); See also matci, tapla, plita.
lujvo f1 is in the genus Dorstenia, species f2
lujvo g1 opens portal/passage/entranceway k1, permitting access to k2 by k3. Cf. kalri, gasnu, toltelgau.

gismu x1 (object/commodity/property/event) is costly/expensive/dear to x2 by standard x3. x1 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event, or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= poskargu for unambiguous semantics). See also vamji, dirba, vajni, jdima, pleji, canja, jerna, jinga, jemna, sfasa, vecnu.
fu'ivla x1 is hibiscus of species/variety x2.
fu'ivla k1 is a wolverine of variety k2.
gismu x1 is a collar/ring/belt/band around/surrounding x2 made of material x3. Also sphincter. See also sruri, djine.

gismu x1 is a journal/periodical/magazine/[newspaper] with content x2 published by x3 for audience x4. x2 may be a subject, but not all journals have a single subject; all have some sort of principle defining what is included, so this need not be a list. See also papri, pelji, tcidu.
lujvo x1 is the x3'rd issue/number of journal/periodical/magazine/publication x2 with content x4 published by x5 for audience x6 .
lujvo x1 is an open-break with broken piece x2.

lujvo j1=k3 hatches from eggshell j2=p1=k1 kalri+porpi+jbena This is based on the lujvo karpo'i, glossed as "something breaks open". It is not obvious to me whether any of k2 (portal destination), p2 (pieces of broken thing), j3 (birthdate), or j4 (birthplace) are appropriate to include in this lujvo.
lujvo s1 is a vowel sound. Cf. zunsna.
fu'ivla x1 is safflower of species/variety x2.
fu'ivla x1 is Georgian (Caucasus) in aspect x2. see also sakartulos
fu'ivla x1 is a caravan consisting of x2 traveling across/through x3 Cf. bende, girzu, gunma.
fu'ivla x1 is a katakana (Japanese syllabary) of sound x2. Cf. lerfu.

gismu rafsi: ka'a x1 (tool/blade/force) cuts [through]/splits/divides x2 (object) into pieces x3. For x1 force, it is a force acting as a blade, not acting upon a blade; agentive cutting (= ka'argau, ka'arzu'e). (cf. kakpa, sraku for cutting into without division; plixa, dakfu, jinci, porpi, spofu, tunta, xrani, fatri, fendi, balre, dilcu)
cmavo UI3a discursive: marks word serving as focus of indirect question: "I know WHO went to the store".
fu'ivla x1 is a salamander of family/genus/species x2. Cf. banfi.
lujvo d2=k1 is common sense to knowers d1=k2 about subject d3 by epistemology d4. Cf. selju'o, kampu.
gismu rafsi: kav x1 captures/catches/apprehends/seizes/nabs x2 with trap/restraint x3. Catch something thrown (= rerkavbu). See also jersi, kalte, pinfu, sisku, se rinju.
cmavo rafsi: kem KE start grouping of tanru, etc; ... type of ... ; overrides normal tanru left grouping. Cf. ke'e, bo.
cmavo KOhA7 pro-sumti: relativized sumti (object of relative clause).
cmavo rafsi: kep ke'e KEhE elidable terminator: end of tanru left grouping override (usually elidable).
cmavo GAhO open interval bracket marker; modifies intervals in non-logical connectives; exclude boundaries.
cmavo UI3 discursive: repeating - continuing. See also refbasna, krefu, rapli, velde'a.
lujvo x1 repeats x2 (sedu'u/text) to audience x3 via expressive medium x4 for the x5th time. See also krefu, cusku
gismu rafsi: kec ke'i x1 (person) pities/feels sorry for x2 (person) about x3 (abstraction). See also cinmo, xendo.
cmavo rafsi: kez KEI elidable terminator: end abstraction bridi (often elidable).
lujvo k1=g1 is a team / play group together playing / playing with plaything / toy / game k2=g2; members are from set g3 linked by relations g4. Made from kelci + girzu.
lujvo x1 is a moving piece used in a game x2.
lujvo x1 is a board used for playing the game x2.
gismu rafsi: kel kei x1 [agent] plays with plaything/toy x2. Play game (= ci'erkei), play competitively (= jvikei). See also jivna, jinga, zdile.
fu'ivla x1 plays croquet against x2 in competition x3 for prize/title x4. Cf. krokete, kroke, kriketi, ga'arboijvi, bolci, mruli.
lujvo g1 is a game master/dungeon master for players k1=g2 in role-playing game g3.
lujvo x1 is a turn/move by player x2 in game x3.
lujvo ku1 is a die/are dice for game x2 with surfaces/sides ku3 (default 6). Shortened from ke nu kelci ke'e kubli. Omitted ku2 (dice have always three dimensions). Cf. cu'arkubli.

gismu rafsi: ke'o x1 is x2 degree(s) Kelvin [metric unit] in temperature (default is 1) by standard x3. See also gradu, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.
fu'ivla x1 is x2 degrees Fahrenheit in temperature by standard x3. Cf. jacke'o, glare, lenku, dunja, febvi.
gismu rafsi: ken x1 is a cancer [malignant disease] in x2. See also bilma, mikce, spita.
lujvo r1 (event/substance) effects/physically causes cancer (of type) r2=k1 under conditions r3. See also kenra, rinka.
gismu rafsi: kes x1 is outer space near/associated with celestial body/region x2. See also canlu, munje, terdi, tsani.
gismu rafsi: kre x1 is a/the hair/fur [body-part] of x2 at body location x3. See also skapi, sunla, pimlu.
lujvo l1 is earwax/cerumen. Cf. kerlo, lakse.
gismu rafsi: ker x1 is a/the ear [body-part] of x2; [metaphor: sensory apparatus, information gathering]. (adjective:) x1 is aural. See also kanla, savru, smaji, tirna, ractu.
lujvo n1=b1 is an eardrum (tympanic membrane) of n2=k2. The tympanic membrane separates the external ear from the middle ear. Cf. kerlo, tirna, sance.
lujvo k1=z1 is an earlobe of k2=z2. Cf. kerlo.
lujvo x1 is astronomy based on methodology x2.
gismu rafsi: ket tco x1 reflects South American culture/nationality/geography in aspect x2. See also merko, xispo, brazo, gento, spano.
fu'ivla x1 has a body mass index of x2 by standard x3.

gismu rafsi: kev ke'a x1 is a cavity/hole/hollow/cavern in x2; x1 is concave within x2; x2 is hollow at locus x1. Also pit, depression, concavity; hollow (= selke'a). See also fenra, kunti, canlu, canko, galxe, tubnu.
lujvo ci1=cu1 is a woodpecker/wryneck/piculet/sapsucker of species ci2 Family Picidae
lujvo k1=xe1=j1 is a cleft/dimple chin of xe2. Cf. flira, kevna, xedja, xejyji'o.
lujvo k1=z1 is a cave for housing x2=z2, located in x3=k2.
cmavo KI tense/modal: set/use tense default; establishes new open scope space/time/modal reference base.
cmavo UI6 attitudinal question: confusion about something said. See also cfipu, kucli.
cmavo cluster UI*6 non-question: understanding of something said.
lujvo z1=k1 applauds/acclaims/praises loudly action z2 (object/event) with sound k2. Cf. krixa, zanru, xanvruzau, geirki'a.
lujvo c1=k1 shouts/cries out c2=k2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) to audience c3 via expressive medium c4 from krixa cusku
cmavo COI vocative: thanks - no thanks to you.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: thanks - no thanks to you.
cmavo BAI ckini modal, 1st place (related to) relatively; as a relation of ...
lujvo g1 is g2 kilograms in mass by standard g3.
lujvo x1 is x2 kilometres long in direction x3 by standard x4. Cf. gusminli, darno.
cmavo BAI krinu modal, 1st place (justified by) justifiably; because of reason ...
cmavo cluster BAI* sumti question asking for a rational explanation/justification; why?.
cmavo cluster BAI* krinu modal, 1st place despite reason ...
lujvo d1 uploads d2 to d3=k1. Cf. kibro, dunda, kibycpa.
lujvo c1 is a web browser for retrieving/presenting/traversing information k1. Cf. kibro, canko, zgana, datni, kibycpa, kibdu'a.
lujvo ki1=ka1 is an internet-journal/web-article/blog (web-log) with content ka2 published by ka3 for audience ka4 Cf. kibro, karni, snukarni, snustu.
lujvo p1 is a web page of site p2=k1. Cf. kibro, papri, kibyca'o.
gismu rafsi: kic ki'e x1 cushions x2 with material x3; x1 is a cushion/pillow/pad [for x2] of padding material x3. See also ckana, matci.
gismu rafsi: kij x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of oxygen (O); [metaphor: supporting life/combustion]. See also jelca, vacri, vasxu.
lujvo c1 lacks oxygen k1; c1 is anaerobic. Cf. claxu.
lujvo x1 spear/lance/assegai made of x2. Cf. kinli, grana, rerga'a.

lujvo x1=xa1=g1=k1 is a lance/spear/javelin/pointed-rod weapon for use against x2=xa2 by x3=xa3 of material x4=g2. kinli grana xarci; this lujvo structure is from noralujv. The author of this definition is uncertain that jesxa'i would not be a better lujvo for the purpose.

gismu rafsi: ki'o x1 is a thousand [1000; 10^3] of x2 in dimension/aspect x3 (default is units). See also grake, mitre, snidu, stero, delno, molro, kelvo, xampo, gradu, litce, merli, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro, minli
gismu rafsi: kil x1 is sharp/keen at locus x2. See also balre, dakfu, jesni.
lujvo p1=s3=s4 thinks about subject p2=s2 by imagining s1 which is like an imaginary movie about that subject.
lujvo x1=s1 is a frame from motion picture x2=k1 about x3=k2 [plot/theme/subject/activity]
gismu rafsi: kis x1 reflects Pakistani/Pashto culture/nationality/language in aspect x2. See also xurdo.
lujvo k1=b1 is the Pakistani Urdu language used by b2 to communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote) from kisto bangu c.f. xurbau.
lujvo k1=g1=b1 is the Pakistani English language used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote). Cf. kisto, glico, bangu, glibau, bangenugu, kisybau
lujvo k1=g1 is Pakistan. Cf. kisto, gugde, gugdepuku. The 'national' language of Pakistan is xurbau.
lujvo x1 is pottery made by x2 of clay x3. see also staku
lujvo b1 is a clay-based building brick of composition k2, surfaces/sides s4. Cf. kliti, bliku.
lujvo x1 is a potter who makes x2 out of clay x3. see also kitselzba, staku
lujvo c1 calls/summons c3=k1 to location k2 in manner/form c4. Cf. cpedu.
lujvo j1=k1 follows j2 to destination k2 from origin k3 via route k4 by means k5. Cf. klama, jersi.

gismu rafsi: laj x1 is a street/avenue/lane/drive/cul-de-sac/way/alley/[road] at x2 accessing x3. Also corridor; not typically a route between points, but offers access to sites along it. See also naxle, panka, pluta, dargu.
gismu rafsi: kak x1 weeps/cries tears x2 about/for reason x3 (event/state). See also badri, krixa.

gismu rafsi: kla x1 comes/goes to destination x2 from origin x3 via route x4 using means/vehicle x5. Also travels, journeys, moves, leaves to ... from ...; x1 is a traveller; (x4 as a set includes points at least sufficient to constrain the route relevantly). See also cadzu, bajra, marce, vofli, litru, muvdu, cpare, cmavo list ka'a, pluta, bevri, farlu, limna, vitke.
lujvo m1 summons m2=k1 to k2 from k3 via route k4. Cf. klama, minde, klacpe.
gismu rafsi: lai x1 is a quantity quantified/measured/enumerated by x2 (quantifier) on scale x3 (si'o). Also count. See also cmavo list la'u, namcu.
fu'ivla x1 measures x2 bels on scale x3 (si'o). One bel is equal to 10 decibels. Cf. klani, sance, cladu.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 joule(s) of energy (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. djaule, klanrniut,ni, klanrxuati.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 farad(s) of capacitance (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. terdikca, xampo.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 newton (s) of force (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. niutni, ki'orgratretrefrinynidysnidu.
fu'ivla x1 is x2 pascal(s) of pressure (default is 1) by standard x3. Cf. klanrniut,ni.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 tesla(s) of magnetic field B (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. maksi.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 volt(s) of electromotive force (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. xampo, klanrxomi, klanrxuati, klanrdjuli, terdikca.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 henry/henries of inductance (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. enri, klanrvolta, xampo.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 hertz of frequency (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. ertso.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 ohm(s) of electrical impedance/resistance (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. omso, xampo, klanrvolta, klanrxuati, klanrzimenzi.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 watt(s) of power (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. klanrdjuli, klanrvolta, xampo.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 siemens of electrical conductance (default is 1) by standard g3. klanrxomi, klanrvolta, xampo.
lujvo p1 is a track on p2
lujvo x1=s1=k1 drives x2=s2=k5 to x3=k2 from x4=k3 via route x5=k4
fu'ivla x1 is blackseed/nigella of species/variety x2

gismu rafsi: kle lei x1 (mass/si'o) is a class/category/subgroup/subset within x2 with defining property x3 (ka). Also type, kind, classification, species, genus, family, order, phylum. See also cmavo list le'a, cmima, jutsi, ciste, girzu, lanzu, vrici.

gismu rafsi: kli x1 (object/medium) is clear/transparent/without obstacle to in-the-clear x2 [transmission]. Also lucid; x2 remains apparent/lucid/clear (figurative use for 'understandable' is discouraged, better expressed as = filseljmi or filsmu). (cf. kandi, zunti - nalzu'i is better for 'unhindered')
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of halogen of type x2 [chlorine, fluorine, iodine, etc.]. Also bromine; default chlorine. See also xukmi.

lujvo x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of a clear/transparent carbonated beverage/soda of sweet flavor, of brand x2. Not any carbonated beverage, but one which is transparent and with sweet flavor, like Sprite (=sprait), 7-up, Sockerdricka (=a soft drink that is consumed in Sweden) or similar. Another flavor may be added and expressed as a tanru, as long as the combination doesn't differ too much from the characteristics of klisodva.
gismu rafsi: kit x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of clay [moist, clammy dirt] of composition including x2. See also dertu, pesxu, staku.
lujvo c1=b1=k1 is a jumper of material c2. A loose outer jacket (barcreka). Cf. creka.
lujvo c1 is a society of c2=k2 with cultural aspects k1. Cf. cecmu, kulnu, jikca, kulnu.
gismu rafsi: lup lu'e x1 is a screw [fastener] for purpose x2, threads [pitch, material] x3, frame [size, material] x4. Also bolt. See also korcu, sarlu, tutci.
lujvo s1 pertains to culture of s2=k2 Cultural gismu replacement lujvo for cultures: From gismu kulnu and srana
lujvo s1 is social anthropology. Cf. kulnu, saske, jikske
gismu rafsi: luz x1 (obj.) is loose/bloused/not tight on x2 (obj.) at locus x3. See also tagji, trati, rinju.
lujvo z1 is a taboo in culture z2=k1.
