cmavo KOhA3 pro-sumti: you (imperative); make it true for you, the listener.
fu'ivla x1 is a coyote of subspecies/breed x2. Cf. gerku, labno, lorxu, tcakali.
gismu rafsi: kob ko'i x1 is a quantity of cabbage/lettuce/leafy vegetable of species/strain x2. See also stagi.
fu'ivla x1 is mustard of species/variety x2. especially mustard greens; see also spatrsinapi, tsijrsinapi, sansrmustardo
cmavo BAI korbi modal, 1st place (bordered by) bounded by ...
fu'ivla x1 is a cognac distilled from grapes x2. Cf. xalka, jikru, vanjyjikru, vanju. For brandies without an AOC designation use vanjyjikru.
lujvo x1=z1 is at an edge/margin/border/curb/boundary of x2=k2 next-to/bordering-on x3=k3; x1=z1 skirts x2=k2. Cf. korbi, zvati

gismu rafsi: koj ko'a x1 is a corner/point/at-least-3-dimensional [solid] angle [shape/form] in/on x2, of material x3. Also apex; a corner exists on three dimensions but need not be limited to points; it suggests a discontinuity in slope in some direction; i.e. in some planar cross-section. See also jipno, konju, bliku, fanmo, jganu, krasi.
fu'ivla x1 is a ladybug/ladybird/lady beetle of genus/species x2. see cakcinki, spacivla
fu'ivla x1 is a sausage made of x2. Not necessarily with a gut skin; see also tisycanti.
fu'ivla x1 is a pigeon/dove of genus/species x2. more general than tcacpi
gismu rafsi: kol ko'e x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of coal/peat/anthracite/bitumen from source x2. See also tabno, tarla.
gismu rafsi: kom x1 is a comb [many-needled shape] of material x2 with tines/needles x3. See also julne, forca, burcu.
fu'ivla x1 is concerto number x2 in key x3 composed by x4 performed by/at x5( event). Cf. zgike, nolzgi, konceto zei pagbu, pipnrpaino zei konceto, jgitrviolino zei konceto, simfoni, zgifi'i.
lujvo p1 is a movement of concerto for solo instruments k2, number k3 in key k4 composed by k5. Cf. konceto, pagbu, zgike, nolzgi, simfoni.
fu'ivla x1 is a condom of x2 size for x3 sex and x4 material
fu'ivla x1 pertains to the Confucist culture/religion/ethos in aspect x2
fu'ivla x1 is konjac of species/variety x2. see also samcrtaro, samcu
gismu rafsi: kon ko'u x1 is a cone [shape/form] of material x2 with vertex x3. Also ellipse, ellipsoid (= konclupa). See also jesni, djine, sovda, kojna, jganu.
gismu rafsi: kor koi x1 is an edge/margin/border/curb/boundary of x2 next-to/bordering-on x3. See also cmavo list koi, greku, mlana, jimte, ctebi, bartu.
gismu rafsi: kro (adjective:) x1 is bent/crooked/not straight or direct/[twisted]/folded. See also cinje, klupe, kruvi, polje, sarlu, sirji, bargu, genxu.
lujvo t1 controls g1=t2 who crosses g2=k1 to g3=k2 from g4=k2. see also natmi, pagre, jaspu
gismu rafsi: kok x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of cork/bark from tree/species x2; [material]. See also tricu, calku, skapi, stagi.
lujvo s1=k1 is a cortex (outermost layer) of structure s3=k2. x2 may be an organ, a cell, a plant, or a rock. Cf. skapi, pilka, sefta.
gismu rafsi: kos x1 is a coat/jacket/sweater/cloak/[cape/shawl/pullover] [extra outer garment] of material x2. See also pastu, sunla, taxfu.
fu'ivla x1 is a cotyledon of seed x2 of plant x3.
lujvo g1 is Scotland (country). Cf. ritygu'e, gligu'e.
lujvo x1 is the duration of x2. See also ze'a, ze'e, ze'i, ze'o, ditcu, faurtei
lujvo gas1 resets/changes gal1 to its original value/content. Cf. krasi, galfi, gasnu, ninga'igau.
fu'ivla x1 is a starfruit/carambola of variety x2.

gismu x1 is x2 local area unit(s) [non-metric] (default 1) by standard x3, x4 subunits. (additional subunit places may be added as x5, x6, ...); See also rupnu, fepni, dekpu, gutci, minli, merli, bunda.

gismu rafsi: kra x1 (site/event) is a source/start/beginning/origin of x2 (object/event/process). Also root (figurative sense); (adjective:) x1 is initial. See also fanmo, cmavo list ra'i, sabji, cfari, jipno, traji, kojna, genja, jicmu, sitna, jinto.
lujvo s1=k1 is the origin of s2=k2. Cf. terkla, famstu.
fu'ivla x1 is a hawthorn of species/variety x2.
gismu rafsi: ka'i x1 represents/is an agent/proxy/stands-in for [absent] x2 in matter(s)/function(s) x3. Also: on behalf of. See also cmavo list ka'i, jansu, catni, vipsi, pulji.
lujvo b1 is wig/toupee/mirkin worn by k2 on body location k3. Cf. kerfa, basti, runkre.
lujvo b1 is an amount of velvet/velour/towelling/tufted cloth of type/material b2.

gismu rafsi: ref ke'u x1 (event) is the x3'rd recurrence/repetition of x2 (abstract); x2 happens again in [form] x1. Also case, another, instance, different, other, time, occasion. See also fukpi, rapli, cafne, fasnu, xruti.
lujvo ka1=ke2 has disheveled/tousled hair from kerfa kalsa
lujvo x1 washes x2's hair, removing x3 with shampoo x4.
lujvo s1 is dandruff on the head of k2. Cf. kerfa, snime.
lujvo x1 is a shampoo for washing x2's hair, removing x3, used by x4.
lujvo x1=v1 shaves/[removes hair] x2=k1=v2 from x3=k2=v3 Applies to any form of hair removal, not necessarily with a blade.

gismu rafsi: kri x1 believes [regardless of evidence/proof] belief/creed x2 (du'u) is true/assumed about subject x3. "without evidence" refers to objective external evidence; also gives credence, has conviction. See also censa, cevni, lijda, makfa, malsi, senpi, birti.
fu'ivla x1 plays cricket against x2 in competition x3 for prize/title x4. Cf. ga'arboijvi, krokete, kelcrkroke.
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of crystal of composition x2 in form/arrangement x3. x2: composition including x2, which need not be complete specification. See also jemna, bisli.
gismu rafsi: rin ki'u x1 (event/state) is a reason/justification/explanation for/causing/permitting x2 (event/state). See also ciksi, rinka, nibli, mukti, se jalge, te zukte, cmavo list ki'u, bapli.
fu'ivla x1 is a clove bud/tree of species/variety x2. see also cifxrula, baljypau
gismu rafsi: kix ki'a x1 cries out/yells/howls sound x2; x1 is a crier. See also klaku, bacru.
fu'ivla x1 croquets x2's ball. Cf. kelcrkroke, krokete, bolci, mruli.
lujvo b1=k1 bends under conditions b3. Cf. korcu, binxo, krosa'i, bolbi'o, krori'a.
lujvo k1=g1 is bow/arc supporting/restraining g2, of material g3.
fu'ivla x1 plays croquet against x2 in competition x3 for prize/title x4. Cf. kelcrkroke, kroke, kriketi, ga'arboijvi, bolci, mruli.
fu'ivla x1 is a crocodile (family Crocodylidae) of breed x2
lujvo r1 (event/state) bends/flexes k1 under conditions r3. Cf. korcu, rinka, krobi'o.
lujvo r1=k1 curtseys in front of r2. Cf. korcu, rinsa, krosa'i.
lujvo s1=k1 bows/takes a bow on surface s2 supported by limbs/supports s3. Cf. korcu, sanli, krorinsa, sa'orgau, dzibi'o, demtse.
fu'ivla x1 is an ani of species x2. see also cipnrkuku
gismu rafsi: kuc x1 intersects/crosses/traverses x2 at locus x3. See also cripu, ragve.

gismu rafsi: ruj x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of cream/emulsion/puree [consistency] of composition x2. [x2: composition including x2, which need not be complete specification]]; See also ladru, matne.

gismu rafsi: ruv kru x1 is a curve/turn/bend in x2, at locus x3, and defined by set of points/properties x4. (adjective:) x1 is curved; (x4 as a set of points is sufficiently specified to identify the relevant properties of the bend). See also korcu, bargu, genxu, linji, sirji.
cmavo KU elidable terminator: end description, modal, or negator sumti; often elidable.
cmavo rafsi: kuz JOI non-logical connective: intersection of sets.
cmavo KUhE elidable terminator: end mathematical (mex) forethought (Polish) expression; often elidable.
cmavo UI3b discursive: however/but/in contrast. See also karbi, dukti, nalpanra.
cmavo cluster UI3b discursive: hence/therefore. Used to draw conclusions in accordance with what said previously, as opposed to ku'i (in contrast).
cmavo KUhO elidable terminator: end NOI relative clause; always elidable, but preferred in complex clauses.
cmavo BAI kulnu modal, 1st place in culture ...
fu'ivla x1 is a quark with flavor x2. Cf. kantu, guska'u, lektoni.
gismu rafsi: kub x1 is a cube/regular polyhedron/polygon of dimensions x2 (def. 3), surfaces/sides x3 (def. 6). (cf. kurfa - needed for 'cube', bliku for a physical object; tanbo, tapla, tarmi)
lujvo kl1=ku1 (goer) crosses ku2 at point kl4=ku3 to reach (destination) kl2 using vehicle kl5
lujvo l1 cross examines l2. Cf. kruca, lanli, retsku.
gismu x1 is curious/wonders about/is interested in/[inquisitive about] x2 (object/abstract). Inquisitive (= retkucli). See also manci, sisku, se cinri.
lujvo x1 is a cross made of x2.
lujvo x1 is a crucifix. See also kucyga'a
lujvo g1 folds/crosses/intertwines s1(set). Cf. kruca, simxu, gasnu.

lujvo x1=v1=k1 is a word/quotation crossing other words/quotations, meaning/defined by x2=v2, located at x3=k3 Across -> pinta, down -> sraji, crossword puzzle -> "kucyvla se namkei". Example: "12 across: what you like -> beautiful" is "zo melbi cu kucyvla lu da poi do nelci li'u li pare poi pinta". x1 may be a non grammatical quotation.
gismu rafsi: kuf x1 feels comfort/is comfortable with conditions/environmental property(ies) x2. See also cinmo.
fu'ivla x1 reflects Seri culture/language in aspect x2
lujvo m1 is a nurse to/nurses m2. Cf. kurji, mikce.
lujvo j1=k1 nurses/holds with care j2=k2 (object/event/person) with/in j3 (part of j1). Cf. kurji, jgari.
lujvo f1=k1 is fermented with fermenting agent f2, tasty to observer x3=k2. Cf. jurme, fomymledi, mledi, birje, vanju, nanba, cirla, ladru, sobysanso, furfipsanso.
lujvo z2=k1 is something made by z1 out of z3 that is pleasing/delightful to sense k2. Cf. kukte, zbasu.
lujvo z2=k1 is something made by z1 out of z3 that is pleasing/delightful to sense k2. Cf. kukte, zbasu, kukselzba.
gismu rafsi: kuk x1 is delicious/tasty/delightful to observer/sense x2 [person, or sensory activity]. x1 is a delicacy. See also gusta, ralci, vrusi, cpina.
lujvo ci1 is a term/semester with interval ci2 of year ci3 for school ck1. x2 may be formed with "bi'o". Cf. citsi, ckule.
lujvo x1=g1 works on x2=g2 with goal/purpose x3=g3 which is associated to school x4=c1 at x5=c2 teaching subject(s) x6=c3 to audience/communicty x7=c4 (of which x1 is a part) operated by x8=c5

lujvo k4=m1 graduates/completes coursework from k1 at location k2 in subject matter k3, by the standards of the administration k5=m3 This is really a dropped SE of velkulmu'o. m2 is the implied "property of learning at k2 subject matter k3 from school k1"
fu'ivla x1 is Norwegian/pertains to Norwegian culture in aspect x2.
fu'ivla x1 is Turkish/pertains to Turkish culture in aspect x2. Cf. kulnrturko, bangrturkie, tu'urki.
fu'ivla x1 is Turkic/pertains to Turkic culture in aspect x2 c.f. kulnrturkie

gismu rafsi: klu x1 [mass of ideas, customs, skills, arts] is culture of nation/ethos x2 (mass); x1 is ethnic. (note that x2 is NOT individual; culture is what is shared among people and is not an individual trait). See also cmavo list ka'u, cmavo list ku'u, natmi, cecmu.
lujvo p1 is a diploma entitling p2 to entitlement/privilege p3 (event/state) from school/institute/academy x4=c1 teaching subject(s) x5=c3.
gismu rafsi: kum ku'a x1 is a room of/in structure x2 surrounded by partitions/walls/ceiling/floor x3 (mass/jo'u). Also chamber. See also bitmu, canlu, zdani.
gismu x1 is a camel/llama/alpaca/vicuna/dromedary of species/breed x2. Llama (= tcokumte), Bactrian camel (= zdokumte); Arabian camel/dromedary (= rabykumte). See also sunla, kanla, xirma, xasli.
fu'ivla x1 is a guanaco of breed x2. Cf. kumte, tcokumte, kumtrvalpaka, kumtrlama, kumtrvikunia.
fu'ivla x1 is a llama of breed x2. Cf. kumte, tcokumte, kumtrvalpaka, kumtrvikunia, kumtrguanako.
fu'ivla x1 is an alpaca of breed x2. Cf. kumte, tcokumte, kumtrvikunia, kumtrlama, kumtrguanako.
fu'ivla x1 is a vicuna of breed x2. Cf. kumte, tcokumte, kumtrvalpaka, kumtrlama, kumtrguanako.
lujvo z1=k1 is an apartment for z2 in structure k2. A complete domicile occupying only part of a building. Cf. zdani, selxa'u.
lujvo g1 is a/the metals and mining industry/sector producing/mining g2=k1 of type/metal k2 from location k3 by process g3 From kunra, gundi.
lujvo x1=ka1 (agent) mines material/ore x2=ku1=ka2 of type x3=ku2 from mine/source x4=ku3=ka3 using tool x5=ka4. Used in Theodore Reed's translation of A Princess of Mars.
gismu rafsi: kun x1 is/contains/is made from a mineral/ore of type/metal x2 mined from location/lode/mine x3. See also jinme, bisli, rokci, jemna.
fu'ivla x1 is/contains/is made from lapis lazuli of type/grade x2 mined from location x3.
fu'ivla x1 is/contains/is made from marble of type x2 mined from location x3.
fu'ivla x1 is/contains/is made from alabaster of type x2 mined from location x3.
lujvo s1=t1 is mineralogy [science about minerals] based on methodology s3. kunra2, kunra3 and saske2 subsumed. See also derske.
gismu rafsi: kut x1 [container] is empty/vacant of x2 [material]; x1 is hollow. Also vacuum (= kunti be roda/so'ada). See also culno, tisna, claxu, canlu, kevna, setca.

gismu rafsi: kur x1 is a right-angled shape/form defined by set of vertices x2, dimensions x3 (default 2). Also rectangle, square, rectilinear; square (= kubykurfa, pitkubykurfa), cube (= kurkubli), rectangle (= clakurfa), rhombus/diamond (= sa'orkurfa, sa'orpitkubli). See also bliku, kubli, tapla, salpo, tarmi.

gismu rafsi: kuj ku'i x1 takes-care-of/looks after/attends to/provides for/is caretaker for x2 (object/event/person). Also tends, cares for, keeps; x1 is a keeper/custodian of x2. See also jundi, cinri, prami, raktu, zgana.
gismu x1 is bitter/acrid/sharply disagreeable to observer/sense x2. See also titla, slari.
fu'ivla x1 is a weevil of genus/species x2. see also cakcinki
fu'ivla x1 is turmeric of species/variety x2.
lujvo m1 is a check/checkerboard pattern of squares k1=m2 arranged in structure m3 x2 might be a set of colors, with x3 specifying their arrangement
lujvo t1 is the square of t2. see tenfa
lujvo x1 is a spice of the mint family, with flavor x2. see also tebrulspa, spatrbasiliko
fu'ivla x1 is a quantity of couscous of ingredients including x2

gismu rafsi: kup ku'e x1 ranges/extends/spans/persists/reaches across/over interval/gap/area/scope/extent/range x2. Also continues. See also ranji, renvi, tcena, bancu, cripu, ragve, vorme, canko, bitmu, sirji, jbini, jimte, preja.
gismu rafsi: kus x1 (person) is cruel/mean/unkind to victim x2. See also xendo, jursa.
lujvo k1=t1 governs and oppresses k2=t2. see also kusyja'a vliraitru
lujvo x1 is a cruel-captain with object of cruelty-captained x2.
lujvo x1 a tautology by standard/epistemology/metaphysics x2. See also kunti, jetnu
lujvo t1=k1 is a desert located in/at t2 from kunti tumla
cmavo LA name descriptor: the one(s) called ... ; takes name or selbri description.
cmavo UI3 discursive: probability - improbability. See also lakne.
cmavo LAhE the referent of (indirect pointer); uses the referent of a sumti as the desired sumti.
cmavo cluster KOhA* pro-sumti: the referent of the last utterance; the state described: "IT was fun".
lujvo x1 expects x2 on grounds x3. See also bavykri, uenai
lujvo x1 has probability/likelihood x2 of occurring under conditions x3. See also zilpa'a, cu'o
cmavo LA name descriptor: the set of those named ... ; takes name or selbri description.
lujvo z1=l1 gets closer to l2 in property l3 by amount z3. Cf. lamji, zenba, jbize'a, jbibi'o.
cmavo ZOI delimited non-Lojban name; the resulting quote sumti is treated as a name.
lujvo le1 is a Roman numeral representing le3=n1.

lujvo x1 is the Roman nation made up of people x2 se la'ornai means the Roman people. The term refers to the ancient Romans, not to modern-day residents of the Italian capital, or small Wisconsin town.
lujvo x1=l1 is Roman Catholic in aspect x2=l2. Cf. xriso, latmo, glixi'o, patxi'o, sunxi'o, lijda.
cmavo BAI klani modal, 1st place (amount) quantifying ...; being a quantity of ...
cmavo cluster BAI* sumti question asking for a quantity; how many?.
lujvo n1 is white bread made from grains n2. Cf. burnanba, jinynanba, jintitnanba, cmananba.
gismu x1 is a wolf/lupine of species/breed x2. See also gerku.
lujvo bi1 turns pale/white under condition bi3. Cf. blabi, binxo.
lujvo c1 is lymph of animal c2. Cf. blufle, blutu'u.
lujvo x1 is a white blood cell of the blood/pus x2 of animal x3.
lujvo f1=b1 is a whitefish of genus/species f2. Cf. blabi, finpe, merlanu.
lujvo x1 is rose. Cf. blabi, xunre, xunblabi.
gismu rafsi: lap cpu x1 pulls/tugs/draws/drags x2 by handle/at locus x3. Gravity (= ka maicpu, maircpukai). See also catke, sakci, cokcu.
gismu rafsi: lac x1 relies/depends/counts on/trusts x2 to bring about/ensure/maintain x3 (event/state). See also minde, nitcu, tinbe.
lujvo l1=g3 is a dependent territory relying on the sovereignty of l2 (state). Examples are British Virgin Islands, Netherlands Antilles, and American Samoa. Cf. gugde, zifyje'a.
gismu rafsi: lad x1 is made of/contains/is a quantity of milk from source x2; (adjective:) x1 is lactic/dairy. See also lanbi, mabru, tatru, cirla, kruji.
gismu rafsi: laf x1 (force) lifts/applies raising/supporting force to x2 at locus x3 in gravity well x4. (x1 may be an abstract); verb lift/raise/elevate (= lafmuvgau). See also farlu, plipe.
cmavo LA name descriptor: the mass of individual(s) named ... ; takes name or selbri description.
lujvo x1 is quantifiable by quantifier x2 on scale x3.

lujvo c1 (quoted word(s)) is a street/road name/odonym of street/avenue/lane/drive/cul-de-sac/way/alley/[road] c2=l1 to/used-by namer/name-user c3 (person). s2 and s3 are omitted. A street name or odonym is an identifying name given to a street. The street name usually forms part of the address (though addresses in some parts of the world make no reference to street names).See also stucme, klaji, stuzi, cmene.
lujvo x1 is a train with train car x2 with train system x3 propelled by x4.
gismu rafsi: la'e x1 (event/state/property) is probable/likely under conditions x2. See also cumki, jinzi, kampu, tcaci, cunso, cafne, fadni, cnano.
gismu rafsi: lak x1 is quantity of wax [substance especially soft/moldable when warm] from source x2. Also paraffin. See also bifce, ranti, bidju.
lujvo g3=l1 is a candle/wax light with wax source l2. Cf. fagytergu'i, dictergu'i.
gismu rafsi: la'u x1 is a lake/lagoon/pool at site/within land mass x2. See also daplu, djacu, rirxe, xamsi, zbani.

gismu rafsi: lam la'i x1 is adjacent/beside/next to/in contact with x2 in property/sequence x3 in direction x4. Also touching, contiguous, against. See also zvati, cpana, jibni, diklo, stuzi, bartu, jbini.
lujvo p1=l1 passes by p2 to p3 from p4 by l2. Cf. lamji, pagre.
lujvo l1=p1 is recent, immediately preceding l2=p2. Cf. purci.
gismu x1 is a quantity of protein/albumin of type x2 composed of amino acids (sequence/jo'u) x3 . See also ladru, sovda.
gismu x1 is a flag/banner/standard of/symbolizing x2 with pattern(s) x3 on material x4. See also gugde, jecta.
lujvo m1 is a mass of set m2 with an even number of members m3 see also xirdegmei
lujvo j1 is a sheep bell producing sound j2. Cf. lanme, janbe.
gismu x1 is a basket with contents x2, woven from material x3. See also vasru, baktu.
lujvo k1 is a shepherd looking after sheep of species/breed l2 of flock l3. Cf. lanme, kurji.
gismu rafsi: lal x1 analyzes/examines-in-detail x2 by method/technique/system x3 [process/activity]. See also catlu, zgana, jarco, pensi, pinka.
lujvo x1 is April of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. vonmasti, kanbyma'i, nanca.
gismu rafsi: lan x1 is a sheep/[lamb/ewe/ram] of species/breed x2 of flock x3. See also kanba, sunla.
lujvo p1 is a lamb of species/breed l2 from lanme panzi
gismu x1 is a can/tightly sealed/pre-sealed container for perishable contents x2, made of x3. See also botpi, baktu, tinci.
gismu rafsi: lax x1 is in balance/equilibrium under forces x2 (mass). (cf. midju, nutli; fapro for balancing/opposing forces, nutli)

gismu rafsi: laz x1 (mass) is a family with members including x2 bonded/tied/joined according to standard x3. Also clan, tribe; x2 is in x1, a member of x1 (selylanzu for reordered places); relative (= lazmi'u - xy mintu y'y leka cmima da poi lanzu). See also natmi, cmima, girzu, jutsi, klesi.
gismu rafsi: lar x1 (process) is an art [creative application] of craft/skill x2 (idea/activity). (adjective:) x1 is artistic. See also finti, zbasu, stati.
lujvo x1 is a work of art created by an application of craft/skill x2. See also larcu, dacti.
lujvo f1 is an artist creating work of art f2=l1 in medium l2 for purpose f3 from elements/ideas f4 .
lujvo m1 is a gallery exhibiting m2 at location m3.
lujvo x1 is-an-artist/produces x2 by artistic application of skill/craft x3. See also larcu, cupra
fu'ivla l1 is a widow spider of species l2. cf. malminiata, jukni
lujvo c1 sculpts/carves c2=l1 from s2 using tool s1 implied c3 is "lo nu jai gau sraku s2 fai s1" implied l2 would likewise be "lo si'o nu jai gau sraku s2 fai s1"

gismu rafsi: la'a x1 (agent) fastens/connects/attaches/binds/lashes x2 to x3 with fastener x4. No implication that result is considered a single object; although x2 and x3 may be reversible, x3 may be used for the substrate, the fixed/larger object to which x2 becomes attached. See also jorne, fenso, jgena, batke, dinko, kansa.
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of brass [copper/zinc alloy] of composition including x2. (adjective:) x1 is brazen). See also jinme, ransu, tunka.
lujvo x1=c1=m1 meows expressing x2=c3. Cf. mlatu, cmoni, latpukcmo.
lujvo x1 is a panda of genus/species x2. syn. cionmau
lujvo x1 is catnip of species x2.
lujvo x1 is a catfish of genus/species x2.
gismu rafsi: la'o x1 reflects Latin/Roman/Romance culture/empire/language in aspect x2. See also ropno, fraso, spano, xispo, itlo.
gismu x1 is a lotus, plant/flower/herb of species/strain x2 symbolizing x3 to culture/religion x4. See also budjo, censa, lijda, spati.
lujvo b1=p2 purrs, expressing pleasure at p1 (event/state). Cf. mlatu, pluka, cmoni, latcmo.
cmavo LAU 2-word letteral/shift: punctuation mark or special symbol follows.
lujvo r1=c1 sounds quiet/weak at observation point c2 by standard c3=t3. Cf. cladu, ruble, smaji, cmato'a.
lujvo cu1=r1 (agent) whipers cu2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) for audience cu3 via expressive medium cu4. Cf. cladu, ruble, cusku, smasku, mliba'u.
cmene Laos. Under some interpretations of the morphology rules, not a valid word.
lujvo cu1=cl1 shouts cu2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) for audience cu3 via expressive medium cu4, loudly by standard x5=cl3. Cf. laurba'u, smasku, smaba'u.
lujvo x1 is October of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavnonmasti, kanbyma'i, nanca.
lujvo g1 balances l1 with force l2. Cf. lanxe, gasnu.
gismu x1 (person) is lazy/avoiding work/effort concerning action x2. See also nejni, vreta, gunka.
lujvo c1 is a family farm/ranch at c2, farmed by family c3=l1 (mass), raising, producing c4.
lujvo z1 is the home of family members z2=l2. Cf. lanzu, zdani.
lujvo k1 (agent) plays house. A child's play to emulate parents.
cmavo LE non-veridical descriptor: the one(s) described as ...
cmavo cluster KOhA* description pro-sumti: reuses the value of the x1 of the previous bridi.
cmavo cluster LE* description: marks description extracting the time tense place of the description bridi.
cmavo cluster LE* description: marks description extracting the agentive place of the description selbri.
cmavo cluster LE* description: marks description extracting the location place of the description bridi.
cmavo cluster KOhA* description pro-sumti: reuses the value of the x2 of the previous bridi.
cmavo cluster KOhA* description pro-sumti: reuses the value of the x3 of the previous bridi.
cmavo cluster KOhA* description pro-sumti: reuses the value of the x4 of the previous bridi.
cmavo cluster KOhA* description pro-sumti: reuses the value of the x5 of the previous bridi.
cmavo BAI klesi modal, 1st place (scalar set) in/of category ...
lujvo v1 is a loanword meaning v2 in language v3 based on foreign-language word l2. Old, deprecated synonym for fu'ivla. Could be considered an u'ivla.
lujvo xr1=l1 takes back xr2=l2 from xr4=l3. Cf. lebna, xruti, xrube'i, xrucpa.
cmavo rafsi: lem LE non-veridical descriptor: the stereotype of those described as ...
cmavo LE non-veridical descriptor: the set of those described as ..., treated as a set.
lujvo pi1=pl1 employs pi2=pl3 for a payment/compensation/salary/wage/reward of pl2 for the provision of goods/services pi3=pl4. From: pleji, pilno. Cf. seljibri.
cmavo UI5 attitudinal modifier: aggressive - passive - defensive. See also gunta, bandu.
cmavo cluster UI*5 attitudinal modifier: aggressive - passive - defensive.
cmavo cluster UI*5 attitudinal modifier: aggressive - passive - defensive.
lujvo t1 is a monocle/pair of (eye)glasses/spectacles for observational activity t2. Cf. lenjo, tutci, barkalyle'o, vistci.
cmavo LEhU end quote of questionable or out-of-context text; not elidable.

gismu rafsi: leb le'a x1 takes/gets/gains/obtains/seizes/[removes] x2 (object/property) from x3 (possessor). Also confiscate, appropriate. Acquire with volition such that x1 gains possession; x3 is possessor and not merely source, alienation is implied. (cf. punji, cpacu where volition or previous possession is not necessarily implied, vimcu for alienation where x1 need not gain possession, canci, cliva)
lujvo d1 is a/the wisdom tooth of d2 See also ka'arde'i, gerde'i, crazalde'i, zalde'i.
lujvo d1=l1 is the afternoon of day d2 at location d3.
lujvo g1 is a mushroom of species g2.
cmavo cluster LE* possessive/associative descriptor: the one(s) described as, of yours.
cmavo LE non-veridical descriptor: the mass of individual(s) described as ...
lujvo s1 is the taxonomy of s2=k2 based on methodology s3. x2 may be subjects of biology, semantics, economics, military science, safety science, etc. Cf. jutske, klesi.
lujvo x1=p1 bribes x3=p3 with x2=p2 into doing x4=p4.
lujvo m1 is a fridge/air conditioner for cooling x2=l1. Cf. dujmi'i, dujyku'a, lenku, kelvo, dunja, varmuvmi'i.
cmavo cluster LE* possessive/associative descriptor: the one(s) described as, of it-1's.
fu'ivla x1 is an electron in quantum state x2 Cf. protoni, nurtoni, xumsle, dicka'u, guska'u, kuarka.
lujvo t1=l1 is tundra at location t2, cold by standard l2 See also lenku, tumla
cmavo cluster LE* possessive/associative descriptor: the one(s) described as, of mine.

gismu rafsi: len le'o x1 is a lens/glass [focussing shape/form] focussing x2 to focus/foci x3 by means/material x4. (adjective:) x1 is optical; focussing may be optical or otherwise, hence x2 which may be light, sound, X-ray, etc., default is light/optical lens; ka is refraction. See also kacma, minra.
gismu rafsi: lek x1 is cold/cool by standard x2. See also glare, bisli.

lujvo s1 makes a typo, typing/writing letter l1=b1 in place of l1=b2 in word b3 by standard s4 The standard place covers cases of different spelling conventions in other languages and possibly other dialects of Lojban. For example, 'colour' is a typo is American English, but correct in British English.
gismu rafsi: lec x1 (event) is late by standard x2. See also clira.
lujvo ca1 is a keyboard for entering letters/symbols l1=cu2. Cf. batkyci'a.

gismu rafsi: ler le'u x1 (la'e zo BY/word-bu) is a letter/digit/symbol in alphabet/character-set x2 representing x3. Also x1 glyph, rune, character (also me'o BY/word-bu), x2 symbol set; (adjective:) x1 is alphabetic/symbolic; "letteral" used by analogy with "numeral"; sinxa is the more generic symbol. See also mifra, namcu, sinxa, pandi.
fu'ivla x1 is a jamo in syllable x2 in writing system x3 (default Hangul)
lujvo s1=p1 is a line in the text s2. Cf. vlali'i, lerseltcidu.
lujvo t2 is a text in medium t3 with character set l2.
lujvo m3 is a character encoding for bytes m2 with symbols/font m1. Cf. lerfu, mifra, skami.
cmavo cluster LE* possessive/associative descriptor: nearby demonstrative possessive; cannot use for 'THAT ...'.
cmavo cluster LE* possessive/associative descriptor: immediate demonstrative possessive; cannot use for 'THIS ...'.
cmavo cluster LE* possessive/associative descriptor: distant demonstrative possessive.
cmavo cluster LE* located descriptor: descriptive that-there (non-demonstrative).
cmavo cluster LE* located descriptor: descriptive this-here (non-demonstrative).
cmavo cluster LE* located descriptor: descriptive that-yonder (non-demonstrative).
cmavo LI the number/evaluated expression; convert number/operand/evaluated math expression to sumti.
cmavo UI3 discursive: clearly - obscurely. See also klina.
lujvo v1 is an exit out of c2. Cf. cliva, vorme, vrogai
cmavo BAI lidne modal, 1st place preceded by ...; non-time sequencing.
lujvo li1=la1 immediately precedes li2=la2 in sequence li3=la3.
cmavo rafsi: liz NU abstractor: experience abstractor; x1 is x2's experience of [bridi] (participant or observer).
lujvo s1 is a fluoride of s3. see also li'orklirytau
lujvo t1 is a fluoride of t3. See also li'orklirysilna.
cmavo LIhU elidable terminator: end grammatical quotation; seldom elidable except at end of text.
gismu rafsi: lib x1 reflects Libyan culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also friko, xrabo, muslo.

gismu rafsi: li'e x1 precedes/leads x2 in sequence x3; x1 is former/preceding/previous; x2 is latter/following. Also x1 before, forerunner; leading, as in 'leading indicators'; x2 after, trailing (= selyli'e for reordered places). See also cmavo list li'e, balvi, ralju, rebla, purci for time sequence, jersi, porsi, jatna, farna.
lujvo t1=v1 is a thunderstorm at place/region t2 Cf. lindi, vlile, tcima.
lujvo s1 is thunderous to s2. Cf. lindi, savru.
lujvo x1 is a sound with emit sound-lightning x2.

gismu rafsi: lif fri x1 [person/passive/state] undergoes/experiences x2 (event/experience); x2 happens to x1. Also has/have (of events/experiences); (adjective:) x1 is empirical; suggests passive undergoing but does not exclude active (per zukte) intent; a deserved experience: reward or punishment (= jernyfri, zanjernyfri, maljernyfri). See also cmavo list ri'i, jmive, fasnu, renvi.

lujvo x1=f1=s2 sublimates/evaporates from the solid state at temperature x2=f2=s3 with vapor pressure x3=f3. From sligu febvi; refers to a state change from solid to gas or vice versa, at the solid surface.

gismu rafsi: jda x1 is a religion of believers including x2 sharing common beliefs/practices/tenets including x3. Also mythos, creed, traditional beliefs, x2 people(s), adherents; (adjective:) x1, x2, x3 are religious/ecclesiastic in nature; x2 is a believer in/of x1, an adherent/follower of x1 (= seljda for reordered places); x2 is a practitioner of x3 (= selterjda for reordered places); x3 is a tenet/belief/ritual/creed of x1/x2 (= terjda for reordered places); priest/clerical (= jdaca'i, jdaka'i, jdaja'a); organized church/religion (= be'ejda); congregation (= jdabe'e, jdagri). See also budjo, censa, cevni, crida, dadjo, jegvo, krici, latna, malsi, marde, muslo, pruxi, ranmi, ritli, xriso, zekri.
fu'ivla l1 is the Bahai religion with beliefs/practices/tenets including l3
fu'ivla l1 is the Jain religion with beliefs/practices/tenets including l3
lujvo g1 is a row (group) showing common property (ka) g2 due to set g3 linked by relations g4. Cf. lerpinsle, depypoi.
lujvo x1=n1 is the length of line x2=l1=c1 defined by set of points x3=l2 in measurement system x4=n2=c3 Lines are 1D, so clani2 is derived. Cf. lutnilcla
lujvo x1=p1 (agent) anoints/rubs/greases/pours onto/applies/lubricate/baptises x3=p3 with liquid/semi-liquid/oil/cream/ointment x2=p2=l1.
lujvo g1 is a/the energy industry/sector producing fuel/energy source g2=l1 for powering l2 based on process g3 From livla, gundi.
lujvo la1 is a pool where li1 swims in fluid li2. Cf. limna, lalxu.
gismu rafsi: lim x1 (agent) swims in fluid x2. See also djacu, fulta, klama, litru.
lujvo n1 is a flipper [body-part] of n2. Cf. limna, nalci, fipybirka.
cmene Lindar Kelleigh Greenwood First name Lojbanised. A member of the Lojban central community.
fu'ivla x1 measures x2 lindars in social context x3.
gismu rafsi: lid x1 is lightning/electrical arc/thunderbolt striking at/extending to x2 from x3. Also thunder (= lidysna). See also dikca.
lujvo x1 is a nunchaku. A Japanese weapon consisting of two wooden sticks connected by a chain; also spelled ``nunchuku''
gismu rafsi: lij li'i x1 is a line/among lines [1-dimensional shape/form] defined by set of points x2. Ray/vector (farli'i or porli'i). See also kruvi, sirji, jganu, kantu, mokca.
fu'ivla x1 is a lily-of-the-valley / may-lily (Convallaria) of species/strain x2
gismu rafsi: lin x1 is a length of chain/links of material x2 with link properties x3. See also skori.
gismu rafsi: li'o x1 is light in mass/weight by standard x2. (cf. junta, tilju; se xalbo, kandi for metaphor)
lujvo g1 is Old English/pertains to Old English-speaking culture in aspect g2, early by standard x3=c2.
lujvo x1 is earlier than x2 by amount of time x3. cf. lecmau, temci
lujvo c1=t1 is the earliest among set / range t4.
lujvo lr1=xa1 is / are the earliest person(s) to dwell/live/reside/abide at/inhabit/be a resident of location/habitat/nest/home/abode xa2 among set / range lr2. Made from liryrai + xabju.
lujvo n1 is in character (actions or speech to be interpreted as part of a story/role-playing game) out of character: lisybartu
lujvo n1 is a drafting by author l3=t1 of story l1=t2 using method t3.

gismu rafsi: lis x1 is a story/tale/yarn/narrative about plot/subject/moral x2 by storyteller x3 to audience x4. Also legend; a narrative need not be fictional; x2 may be merely a convention rather than a subject; also x3 tells/recounts story/tale x1 about x2 to x4 (= selterlisri for place reordering); note that the storyteller need not be the author. See also ranmi, cfika, skicu, prosa, pemci.

gismu rafsi: ste x1 (physical object) is a list/catalog/register of sequence/set x2 in order x3 in medium x4. Also roll, log. (x2 is completely specified); (cf. porsi, girzu, cmima for mental objects wherein order is of varying importance; some manifested order is intrinsic to a physical list, but the specific order may be incidental and not intentional/purposeful)
lujvo x1=p1 is a comic strip about plot/subject/moral x2=l2 illustrated by x3=p3 with story written by x4=l3. Cf. lisri, pixra.
lujvo b1 is out of character (actions or speech not to be interpreted as part of a story/role-playing game) in character: lisne'i
lujvo c1 is a story book containing story/tale/yarn/narrative l2 by author c3=l3 for audience c4=l4 preserved in medium c5. Cf. fikcku.

gismu rafsi: lic x1 is x2 liter(s) [metric unit] in volume (default is 1) by standard x3. See also merli, grake, mitre, dekpu, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.

lujvo cr1 is a dress shirt of material cr2, potentially formal by standard cl3. A shirt with a collar, a full-length opening at the front from the collar to the hem, and sleeves with cuffs; normally made from woven cloth, and are often accompanied by a jacket and tie, for example with a suit or formalwear, but can be worn also more casually without. Cf. creka.

gismu rafsi: lik x1 is liquid/fluid, of composition/material including x2, under conditions x3. Conditions include temperature and pressure. See also cilmo, djacu, lumci, runta, pambe, sudga, gapci, sligu, flecu, jduli.

gismu rafsi: li'u x1 travels/journeys/goes/moves via route x2 using means/vehicle x3; x1 is a traveller. (x2 as a set includes points at least sufficient to constrain the route relevantly); See also bajra, cadzu, cpare, tcana, klama, cliva, pluta, limna, muvdu.
lujvo xe1=c1 is gracious to xe2 in matter xe3=c2. xendo, clite.
lujvo m1 is very/extremely polite/courteous/civil in matter c2 according to standard/custom c3. Cf. clite, mutce.
fu'ivla x1 is a lynx (Felis lynx) See mlatu
lujvo b1 expels c1 from c2; b1 throws c1 out of c2. Cf. cliva, bapli, livgau.
gismu x1 is a/the liver [body-part] of x2. See also rango, betfu.
lujvo g1 causes c1 to leave c2 via route c3. Cf. cliva, gasnu, livbai.
gismu rafsi: lil x1 is a fuel/energy-source for powering x2. See also nejni, xaksu, jelca.
cmavo LE veridical descriptor: the one(s) that really is(are) ... Under the xorlo reform, lo converts a selbri to a sumti in a rather generic way. In particular, lo broda = zo'e noi broda.
cmavo BY1 shift letterals to Lojban (Roman) alphabet.
cmavo rafsi: lom LE veridical descriptor: the typical one(s) who really is(are) ...
cmavo LE veridical descriptor: the set of those that really are ..., treated as a set.
cmavo LOhO elidable terminator: end math express.(mex) sumti; end mex-to-sumti conversion; usually elidable.
cmavo LOhU start questionable/out-of-context quote; text should be Lojban words, but needn't be grammatical.
gismu rafsi: loj x1 [rules/methods] is a logic for deducing/concluding/inferring/reasoning to/about x2 (du'u). Also (adjective:) x1, x2 are logical. See also nibli.
cmavo LE veridical descriptor: the mass of individual(s) that is(are) ...
lujvo b1 is a broom for purpose b2 (event) with bristles b3. From loldi, burcu.
lujvo l1=s1 undergoes an earthquake/an event of the ground shaking of magnitude x2. not necessarily earthquake, could be due to bomb explosion etc. too.
cmene Bob LeChevalier. Bob LeChevalier is one of the Original Lojbanists.
lujvo b1 is the loglan/Loglan/logic language used by community b2 to express ideas b3. Cf. bangu, runbau, lojbo, lojban
gismu rafsi: lob jbo x1 reflects [Loglandic]/Lojbanic language/culture/nationality/community in aspect x2. Pre-Lojban forms of Loglan (= dzejbo). See also bangu, logji.
lujvo x1 infers/concludes/draws conclusion x2 from premise x3 based on logic/reasoning x4. Cf. logji, cpacu, famsku, ni'i, ja'o, nibji'i, jivbi'o.
gismu rafsi: lol loi x1 is a floor/bottom/ground of x2. Floor/level/story of a building/edifice (= setloi, dijysenta). See also bitmu, drudi, dertu, dizlo, cnita, zbepi, sarji, serti.
lujvo g1 is floor covering/flooring/carpet/rug for covering floor g2=l1 of x3=l2. Cf. buklolgai.
lujvo c1 is underground/buried within ground c2=l1 of x3=l2. Cf. lolni'apu'i, derse'a.
lujvo j1=c1 is a landmine with explosive material/principle j2. Cf. loldi, cnita, jbama.
lujvo p1 (agent) buries/puts underground p2=c1 under surface x3=c2=l1 of x4=l2. Cf. lolni'a, derse'a.
lujvo b1=r1 is a cobblestone of material b2=r2 in floor l1.
fu'ivla x1 is a quantity of aloe vera of species/strain x2
gismu rafsi: lor lo'u x1 is a fox [bushy-tailed wild dog/canine] of species/breed x2. See also gerku.
cmavo LU start grammatical quotation; quoted text should be grammatical on its own.
cmavo LAhE the members of the set/components of the mass; converts another description type to individuals.
cmavo LAhE the symbol for (indirect discourse); uses the symbol/word(s) for a sumti as the desired sumti.
cmavo LAhE the set with members; converts another description type to a set of the members.
cmavo LAhE the mass composed of; converts another description type to a mass composed of the members.
cmavo LUhU elidable terminator: end of sumti qualifiers; usually elidable except before a sumti.
gismu rafsi: lu'o x1 reflects Lebanese culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also xrabo.
lujvo x1 is a complex number. See also ka'o, xarna'u, tolxarna'u
gismu rafsi: luv jvo x1 (text) is a compound predicate word with meaning x2 and arguments x3 built from metaphor x4. See also stura, cmavo, gismu, rafsi, smuni.
fu'ivla x1 is an earthworm of species x2. Cf. curnu, dertu, carvi.

gismu rafsi: lum lu'i x1 (agent) washes/cleanses x2 of soil/contaminant x3 in/with cleaning material(s) x4. Agentless washing/cleansing (= cuvbi'o, jisybi'o). See also djacu, jinru, litki, zbabu, jinsa, curve.

lujvo x1=k1 is a bathroom, in which x2=l1 washes x3=l2 (self/other(s)/body part), in home/building/structure x4=k2 surrounded by partitions/walls/ceiling/floor x5=k3 (mass/jo'u) A room with a sink technically qualifies, but this is more like a room with a bath or shower as well. What most Americans call a "bathroom". For a room specifically for urination or defecation, see vimku'a.
lujvo p1 is a wash tub/bath tub, for l1 to wash p2=l2, made of material p3.
lujvo t1 is a sink, for l1 to wash t2=l2, made of material t3
gismu rafsi: lub x1 is bare/naked/nude; x1 is without cover/clothes/[protection]. See also taxfu, bandu.

cmene x1 is Aries [astronomical constellation/astrological sign]. From lanme (=sheep/[lamb/ewe/ram];lojban) and lu (=sheep;sumerogram). This constellation has been known as the ram/sheep since babylonian times, and later become the leading sign of the zodiac (7th century BCE). In Hellenistic astrology, the constellation of Aries is associated with the golden ram of Greek mythology that rescued Phrixos.
gismu rafsi: lur x1 is Earth's moon (default); x1 is a major natural satellite/moon of planet x2. See also plini, solri, terdi, mluni.
gismu rafsi: lus x1 condenses/liquefies on/into x2 at temperature x3, pressure x4; x1 is dew/condensate on x2. See also cilmo, dunja, febvi, runme, bumru.
lujvo t1 is a screwdriver for turning screw k1
lujvo x1 is Monday of week x2 on calendar x3.
lujvo f1 is a dead end of route f2=p1 from origin p3. Cf. klaji.
lujvo x1=n1 is the length of path x2=p1=c1 between x3=p2 and x4=p3 defined by points x5=p4 (set) where the distance is on scale x6=n2=c3 Paths are 1D, so clani2 is derived. Cf. lijnilcla
lujvo c1=b1=k1 is a jumper of material c2. A loose outer jacket (barcreka). Cf. creka.
lujvo c1=k1 is a blouse of material c2. Cf. creka, taxfu.
cmavo KOhA7 pro-sumti: sumti question (what/who/how/why/etc.); appropriately fill in sumti blank.
cmavo KOhA3 pro-sumti: me/we the speaker(s)/author(s) & you the listener(s) & others unspecified.
fu'ivla x1 is a mahogany of species x2.
lujvo b1 is a yak of species/type b2
lujvo j1 is a valley between mountains/hills c1=j2 in terrain c2. Cf. ma'arfe'a, cmana, punli, kevna
lujvo f1 is a canyon/ravine/chasm in mountain f2=c1 in terrain c2. Cf. ma'arbi'i, cmana, fenra, kevna
lujvo p1 is a Copper Pheasant / Syrmaticus soemmerringii species of breed p2
cmavo BAI marji modal, 1st place material in object/substance ...
lujvo k1=m2 drives to k2 from k3 via route k4=m3 by means m1. Cf. marce, klama, litru.
lujvo g1 parks vehicle m1=s2 in/at s3.
cmavo BAI manri modal, 1st place (by standard 2) in reference frame ...
cmavo MAhO convert letteral string or other mathematical expression (mex) operand to mex operator.
lujvo x1=l1 is a list of structure words x2=l2=c1 of class(es) x5=c2 of language x6=c3 in order x3=l3 in medium x4=l4. Cf. cmavo, liste, vlaste, vlacku, gimste, jvoste
cmavo PA3 digit/number: plus sign; positive number; default any positive.
lujvo x1 is an cation of radical/(atom of element)x2 with x3 charges.
lujvo c1 is a college at c2 teaching subject c3 to audience c4=m1 operated by c5. An institution for adult education at a basic or intermediate level (teaching those of any age). Cf. ckule, balcu'e.

gismu rafsi: mal x1 is a derogative connotation/sense of x2 used by x3; x3 derogates/'curses at' x2 in form x1. Bloody (British sense), fucking, shit, goddamn. See also palci, dapma, xlali, zabna, funca, ganti, ganxo, gletu, gutra, kalci, pinca, pinji, plibu, vibna, vlagi, zargu.
fu'ivla x1 is a ferret. Cf. mustlei, ermine.
gismu rafsi: mab x1 is a mammal/'animal'/beast of species x2. See also danlu, ladru, tatru, ractu, xanto, xarju.
gismu rafsi: cnu x1 (event/action/process) is manual [not automatic] in function x2 under conditions x3. See also zmiku, jitro.
lujvo n1=m1 is the moral of story/situation m3 and entails action/event/state n2. Cf. marde, nibli.

lujvo s1 (mass of facts) is the study of conduct-governing standards s2=m1 based on methodology s3. Major branches of ethics include "meta-ethics" (ckaji zei madyske), "normative ethics" (bilga zei madyske), "applied ethics" (pilno zei madyske), "moral psychology" (menli zei madyske), and "descriptive ethics" (skicu zei madyske). Cf. saske.

lujvo c1=m2 moralizes expressing c2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) to audience c3 via expressive medium c4 using/based on ethics/morals/moral standards/ethical standards m1 from marde cusku c.f. bitygau dragau
lujvo c1=m3 is a wizard/sorcerer of m1=c1, which is magical to m2, with standard of sorcery c3. Cf. makfa, certu
lujvo x1 is x2 millimeters of mercury by standard x3. synonym torceli
lujvo x1 is an amalgam of composition including x2.
cmavo MAI utterance ordinal suffix; converts a number to an ordinal, such as an item or paragraph number.

lujvo x1=s1=m1 is the material environment/surrounding material (i.e. gaseous/liquid atmosphere, vacuum, etc.) enclosing x2=s2 in direction(s)/dimensions(s)/plane x3=s3=m3, of type/composition including x4=m2. A vacuum is arguably not 'material', but the word is much more convenient if that is included. Also, vacuum is never completely empty. See also marji, sruri, gapci, litki, kunti, sakci, kensa.
gismu rafsi: ma'u x1 is mature/ripe/fully-grown/adult in development-quality x2 (ka). See also cifnu, ninmu, verba, banro, farvi, nanmu.
gismu rafsi: maf x1 is magic/supernatural/sorcery/witchcraft/wizardry to x2, performed by person/force/deity x3. See also krici, manci.
lujvo x1 is a compass with magnet x2. see also maksi, terfarnilfrica, cukyxratci
fu'ivla x1 is a poppy of species x2
gismu rafsi: mak x1 is magnetic [adjective] producing magnetic field x2. See also dikca, trina, xlura.
lujvo v4=m1 is a magnetic storage medium storing v2 (data/facts/du'u) about v3 (object/event) in file(s) v1. Cf. vreji, datni, skami, cukmakyvelvei, srimakyvelvei
lujvo c1 is junk food for c2.
lujvo f1=m1 is vulgar/uncouth in property f2=m2 (ka) among members f3 (set). Cf. mabla, fadni, tolba'i.
lujvo f1=m2 (event/property) is determined by the bad luck/fortune of f2. Cf. mabla, funca, malselfu'a, zanfu'a.
fu'ivla x1 is Malagasy in aspect x2.

lujvo g1=m1 is an anglicism (in Lojban), inappropriate according to m3. Refers to any kind of reliance upon English in a Lojban expression, but is most common for calques. Is sometimes even extended to cover reliance upon cultural assumptions. ``malglico'' is a much more common form.
lujvo mak1 is black magic to mak2, performed by person/force/deity mak3. Cf. mabla, makfa, lijda, palci
fu'ivla m1 is a black widow spider of variety m2. cf. lartodektu
lujvo ma1=mi1=g2 is ill-lit with light g1 from light source g3. Cf. gusni, mabla, milxe
cmene Malmö Malmö, in the southernmost province of Scania, is the third most populous city in Sweden.
lujvo f2 is unlucky/unfortunate in f1=m2 (event/property). Cf. mabla, funca, zanselfu'a.

cmene Moscow Cf. moskov. Lojbanized pronunciations of the Russian capital are: 'masKVA'(Russian, but KV combination is invalid in lojban), 'mosiKY' (Chinese Mandarin; there is no 'v' in Chinese and 'f' is unusual except at the beginning of a word) and 'mosko' or 'moskau' in English.
gismu rafsi: sno x1 is slow/sluggish at doing/being/bringing about x2 (event/state). See also sutra.

gismu rafsi: ma'i x1 is x2 months in duration (default is 1 month) by month standard x3. This month (= cabma'i); next month (= bavla'ima'i); last month (= prula'ima'i). See also detri, djedi, jeftu, nanca.
lujvo c1 is a parish of parishioners c2.
gismu x1 is a mat/pad/mattress/pallet [flat, soft, dense form] of material x2. Also mattress = (kicymatci). See also kicne, tapla, karda, ckana.

gismu rafsi: mav x1 is a quantity of oats [grain] of species/strain x2. See also gurni.
gismu rafsi: xri x1 is a quantity of wheat [grain] of species/strain x2. See also gurni.
lujvo c1=m1 stomps on surface c2 using limbs c3 crushing m2 into pulp mass m3. Cf. marxa, cadzu.

cmavo ME convert sumti to selbri/tanru element; x1 is specific to [sumti] in aspect x2.
cmavo BAI mleca modal, 1st place (a lesser) undercut by ... ; usually a sumti modifier.

cmavo BAI cmene modal, 1st place (requires quote) with name ...; so-called ...

lujvo s1 is a brother-in-law (sister's spouse) of m2 under law/custom/tradition/system/convention sp3. Omit x4=s2=m1. Cf. speni, bunspe, tubyspe.

gismu rafsi: meb x1 is a/the brow/forehead [projecting flat/smooth head/body-part] of x2. See also stedu, flira.

lujvo me1=t1 is least beautiful among set/range t3 to m2 in aspect me3 (ka) by aesthetic standard me4. Cf. mleca, melbi, traji, mlerai, mlemau, mleme'a.

lujvo me1=t1 is least ugly among set/range t3 to me2 in aspect me3 (ka) by aesthetic standard me4. Cf. mleca, melbi, traji, tolmlerai, tolmlemau, tolmleme'a.
lujvo t1=b1 is the smallest/[ least big] among set/range t4 in property/dimension(s) b2 (ka).
lujvo t1=c1 is the biggest/[ least small] among set/range t4 in property/dimension(s) c2 (ka). Cf. mleca, cmalu, traji, brarai, cmarai, cmamau, cmame'a.
lujvo x1 is less than or equal to x2 in property/quantity x3 by amount x4. See also su'e
lujvo t1=x1 is the worst among set/range t4 for x2 by standard x3. Cf. mleca, xamgu, traji, xagme'a, xauzma, xagrai, xlarai.
lujvo m1=x1 is the best/[least bad] among set/range t4 for x2 by standard x3. Cf. mleca, xlali, traji, xagrai, xlamau, xlarai, xlame'a, zanrai.

gismu rafsi: mek me'o x1 [quantifier/expression] is a mathematical expression interpreted under rules/convention x2. See also cmaci, dilcu, fancu, frinu, jalge, namcu, parbi, pilji.

fu'ivla x1 is a quantity of peppermint of species/strain x2

fu'ivla x1 is a skunk of genus/species x2. Cf. ckankua, cribe, prokioni, mabru.

See also kancu, rupnu, fepni, dekpu, gutci, minli, merli, bunda, ckilu, gradu, satci, centi, cimde, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, kramu, litce, manri, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.

cmavo rafsi: mib KOhA3 pro-sumti: me/we the speaker(s)/author(s); identified by self-vocative.

lujvo x1=m1=c1 expresses/states command x2=c2 to recipient(s) x3=m2=c3 via expressive medium x4=c4. m3 of minde (the desired result) is presumably cointained in he expression of the command. x1 commands x3 with expression x2.

lujvo x1=c1 is a machine gun for use against x2 by x3, launching projectile c2 propelled by c3. Cf. minji, cecla, xarci, xumjimcelxa'i, xilcelxa'i, clacelxa'i, celgunta.

cmavo UI3b discursive: ditto. See also mintu.

lujvo x1 is medicine/medical science/medical treatment to x2 for ailmentx3 by treatment/cure x4. Cf. mikce, bilma, kanro, spita.

gismu rafsi: mij x1 is in/at the middle/center/midpoint/[is a focus] of x2; (adjective:) x1 is central. See also lanxe, jbini, nutli, snuji, milxe, denmi, ralju.

lujvo x1 is a meal with meal dish x2.
lujvo x1 is a diameter between x2 and x3 of x4.

Also medic; (adjective:) x1, x4 is medical; x2 is a patient of x1 (= selmikce for reordered places) ; x2 is treated by x1 person/x4 treatment/method; successfully cure transitive (= sadmikce, sadvelmikce), intransitive (= sadyselmikce, ka'orbi'o to not imply an external agent/process, though the x1 and x4 of mikce may be self/internal); treatment (= velmikce). See also bilma, kanro, spita.

See also grake, mitre, snidu, stero, delno, molro, kelvo, xampo, gradu, litce, merli, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, milti, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro

lujvo g1 is g2 milligrams in mass by standard g3
lujvo x1 is x2 milliseconds in duration. milti snidu; the default x2 is 1

See also grake, mitre, snidu, stero, delno, molro, kelvo, xampo, gradu, litce, merli, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, mikri, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro

Also machinery/mechanism; a machine is initiated/triggered by an agent/force, but thereafter performs its function automatically; if self-directed, (a minji is an) entity (= zukte). See also cabra, matra, tutci, zukte, pilno, skami.

gismu x1 is x2 (default 1) long local distance unit(s) [non-metric], x3 subunits, standard x4. (additional subunit places may be added as x5, x6, ...); See also mitre, kilto, clani, ganra, condi, rotsu, rupnu, fepni, dekpu, gutci, minli, merli, bunda, kramu.

Also: x1 is a mirror/reflector. x2 may be light, lu'e of an imaged object; x4 may be image or echo or the same as x2 if physical object; x3 may be a path for a bounced object; ka is reflection. See also catlu, viska, lenjo, pensi.

gismu rafsi: mit mi'u x1 is the same/identical thing as x2 by standard x3; (x1 and x2 interchangeable). (cf. panra, satci, mapti, simsa, drata, dunli, cmavo list du - which has no standard place, simxu)

lujvo s1 (place) hides m2=s2 from m3 by method m4; s1 is a hiding place. Cf. mipri, stuzi
fu'ivla x1 is a bug of species x2. see also cinki, ckacinki, moptera, miptinytci, cfila, fanza

lujvo x1=p1=m1 hides/conceals x2=p2 from x4=m3 on/at surface/locus x3=p3=m1, the location being kept secret by method x5=m4.
lujvo z1 spies/snoops on z2 using senses/means z3 under conditions z4.
lujvo x1 glitters/sparkles/glares, reflecting x2 to observer x3.
lujvo l1 is symmetrical about axis m1.
gismu x1 is a deer/elk/moose/[hart/stag/doe] of species/breed x2. See also mabru, danlu.
lujvo s1 is symmetrical about axis m1.
lujvo s1=m4 is a notion of s2=m2 to cognizer s3=m3. A mental reflection of real objects and phenomena in their essential features and relations. Cf. sidbo, selpei, selga'e, tarmi.
lujvo s1=m4 is an echo of sound m2=s2, reflected by m1 and heard by m3.

gismu rafsi: mis mi'o x1 (person/object/event) is famous/renowned/is a celebrity among community of persons x2 (mass). Also celebrated/well-known; (derogative meanings:) notorious/infamous (= malmi'o; these could also be expressed using the referenced words). See also se sinma, banli.
gismu x1 reflects Egyptian culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also friko, muslo, xrabo.
lujvo m1=b1 is the Egyptian Arabic language used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote). Cf. misro, bangu, rabybau, bangaru'a, bangarubu.
lujvo x1 is an Egyptian fraction with denominators x2, x3, ... see also porfrinu
lujvo x1 is Egypt. Cf. misro, gugde, gugde'egu.
lujvo x1 is an Egyptian character in writing system x2 (hieroglyphic/hieratic/demotic) meaning x3.
lujvo x1 is papyrus from source x2. see also misryplespa, pelji
lujvo x1 is a papyrus plant of variety x2. see also misryple, stagrleoxari
lujvo m1=s2 is glorified by s1. Cf. sinma, censa.
lujvo c1 is homosexual/bisexual in situation c2 by standard c4. For strict homosexuality, see pavmitcinse. Cf. relcinse, dutcinse, nakcinse, fetcinse.
lujvo x1 (person) is a/the namesake of x2 (person).
lujvo m1=f1 is palindromic by standard m3. Cf. valsi, mirsarxe.
lujvo s1=m1 seems to be the same as m2 by standard m3 to observer s3 under conditions s4. Cf. simlu, mitmlu.
lujvo mo1=mi1 follows the same pattern as mi2 with respect to forms/events mo2 arranged according to structure mo3. Cf. mintu, morna

gismu rafsi: tre x1 is x2 meter(s) [metric unit] in length (default 1) measured in direction x3 by standard x4. See also kilto, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, gutci, litce, megdo, mikri, milti, minli, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.
lujvo v1=m1 is a synonym of m2 by standard m3 in language v3. Cf. mintu, smuni, valsi, smuske
lujvo m1=j1=c1 cannibalizes c2. m1=j1=c1 is a cannibal.
lujvo x1=m1 is a zoo at x3=m3 with animals x2=m2=j1=d1. Cf. jmive, danlu, muzga
lujvo g1 reincarnates/resurrects j1 by standard j2. Cf. jmive, gasnu
lujvo jd1=jm1 is a jelly fish. Cf. jmive, jduli, finpe.
lujvo m1 is nature/the world of living things m2=j1, defined by rules m3. Cf. jmive, munje
lujvo x1=m1 is a life-goal of x3=m3=j1 motivating x2=m2 . Cf. jmive, mukti

lujvo p1 is the life of j1 through stages p4. This focuses on the process of x2's life as a succession of stages (childhood, chrysalis, etc.), while nunji'e more generally denotes the event of x2 being alive without a default terbri to specify the stages x2 goes through during that event.
lujvo l1 is adenosine triphosphate (ATP) transporting energy within organism l2=j1.
lujvo x1 is organic, originating in living organism x2. See also tabyselcmu, rarvelcange.
lujvo n2 (number) is the age (in years) of living thing j1, alive by standard j2, with year standard n3.
lujvo s1 is biology/Life Science based on methodology s2. Cf. mrodalmuzga.
lujvo x1 is a biological cell of x2. second lowest lujvo-scoring, but same form as in lowest scoring lujvo mivyslerango. See also jmive, selci.
lujvo r1 is an organelle of r2=s1=j1 performing function r3. See also mivysle and rango.
lujvo xu1 is an instance of chemical substance xu2 derived from biological source j1. Cf. xukmi.

gismu rafsi: mix xre x1 (mass) is a mixture/blend/colloid/commingling with ingredients including x2. x2 mingles/mixes/blends into x1; x2 is in x1, an ingredient/part/component/element of x1 (= selxre for reordered places). See also salta, te runta, stasu, jicla, sanso.
lujvo f1 is a flatfish of family/genus/species f2, swimming with side m1 upward. Cf. finpe, polgosu, flundero, platesa.
lujvo x1 is July of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. zelmasti, kanbyma'i, nanca.
lujvo x1=k1=m4 dodges/sidesteps/skirts x2=m2 from x3=k3 by route x4=k4 by means of transportation x5=k5. The lateral frame of reference is that of the one who sidesteps. Cf. mlana, klama, koizva.
fu'ivla x1 is a paperbark/tea tree of species/variety x2.

gismu rafsi: mla x1 is to the side of/lateral to x2 and facing x3 from point of view/in-frame-of-reference x4. (cf. crane, trixe, pritu, zunle which differ in that the direction of facing is the front and not the lateral side. The x4 of mlana may be either the front, or back side of x2, korbi)
lujvo s1=c1 is a sidewinder of subspecies/type s2
lujvo m1=p1 is the side of / is a part and on the side of m2=p2 and is facing m3 from point of view/in-frame-of-reference m4. Made from mlana + pagbu.
lujvo f2 is sideways from f3=m2 . x3=f1, the exact direction, is unspecified. Cf. mlana, farna.
gismu rafsi: lat x1 is a cat/[puss/pussy/kitten] [feline animal] of species/breed x2; (adjective:) x1 is feline. See also cinfo, tirxu, gerku.
lujvo m1 is a sideband of signal b1=m2.
lujvo m1=b1 is splendid/glorious/magnificent to m2 in aspect m3 (ka) by aesthetic standard m4, and by greatness standard b4.
gismu rafsi: mec me'a x1 is less than x2 in property/quantity x3 (ka/ni) by amount x4. Also negative (= nonme'a). See also cmavo list me'a, cmavo list su'o, jdika, zmadu, traji.
gismu rafsi: led x1 is a mold/fungus/mushrooms/truffles of species/strain x2 parasitic/growing on x3. See also clika.
lujvo ma1=g1 is a cosmetic/makeup for beautifying me1 in aspect me3, made up of material ma2 in form ma3
lujvo j1 is vain. Cf. melbi, jgira
lujvo z1=m1 is more beautiful than z2 to m2 in aspect m3 (ka) by amount z4. Cf. melbi, zmadu, mlerai, mecmlerai, mleme'a.
lujvo ml1=me1 is less beautiful than ml2 to me2 in aspect me3 (ka) by amount ml4. Cf. melbi, mleca, mlemau, mlerai, mecmlerai.
lujvo g1 grooms/spruces up c1=m1 in property/aspect c2=m3. Cf. melbi, cnici, gasnu, jisygau, lumci.
lujvo m1=t1 is most beautiful among set/range t3 to m2 in aspect m3 (ka) by aesthetic standard m4. Cf. melbi, traji, mlemau, mecmlerai, mleme'a.
lujvo ta1=tr1=m1 is coquettish/flirtatious with tr2=m2 in aspect m3 from melbi trina tarti
lujvo x1=m1=b1 whispers/mumbles/murmurs/coos utterance x2=b2; x1=m1=b1 speaks softly. Cf. milxe, bacru, smasku, laurblesku.
lujvo b1=m1 is breeze/zephyr from direction b2 with speed b3. Cf. milxe, brife
lujvo b1=m1 is somewhat big in dimension b2 by standard b3. Cf. milxe, barda
lujvo b1 is mildly embarrassed/disconcerted about/under conditions b2 (abstraction). Cf. milxe, burna
lujvo m1=f1=b1 grumbles with sound b2 at f2 because of f3 (action/state/property). jvajvo definition; Gismu deep structure is "milxe gi'e fengu gi'e bacru"
lujvo g1=m1 is warm by standard g2. Cf. glare.
lujvo l1=m1 is cool (mildly cold) by standard l2. Cf. lenku.
lujvo c1 chuckles. Cf. cisma, mi'afra, mlimi'afra.
lujvo r1 (event/state) mildens/allays/alleviates effect r2 (event/state) under conditions r3. Cf. mliri'agau for a person as x1.
lujvo s1 (agent) pets/gently strokes s2 with s3. Cf. pencu, mi'arpe'u, tikpa, tunta.
fu'ivla x1 is eggplant of variety x2. see also patlu, tamca, kapsiku, labnyjba
gismu rafsi: lun x1 is a satellite/moon orbiting x2 with characteristics x3, orbital parameters x4. See also plini, solri, lunra.
cmavo rafsi: mob PA4 digit/number: too few; subjective.
cmavo cluster ROI* tense interval modifier: too few times; objective tense; defaults as time tense.
cmavo MOhE convert sumti to mex operand; sample use in story arithmetic: [3 apples] + [3 apples] = what.
cmavo rafsi: mov MOhI mark motions in space-time.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: northwardly; to the north directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: moving to coincide directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: forward directional space motion.

lujvo c1=m1 memorizes/commits to memory c2=m2 (du'u) about subject c3=m3 from source c4 (obj./event) by method c5 (event/process)) This word is different from cilre in that it doesn't include actual understanding of the memorized data but merely the storage of it in one's memory.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: eastwardly; to the east directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: arriving at; arriving at a point directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: upwardly; upwards directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: approximating; moving around the neighborhood of ... space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: moving into directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: southwardly; to the south directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: downwardly; downwards directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: passing through directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: along; along a path directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: rightwardly; to the right directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: orbiting; surrounding/annular directional space motion.
lujvo s1 is a memory/storage/anamnesis containing facts/data/recollection s2=m2 within medium/substrate/containment s3, said facts related to subject m3. Cf. morji, sorcu, mojrango.
lujvo s1=m1 forgets fact/memory m2 about subject m3. Cf. morji, sisti, tolmo'i.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: moving along the border directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: rearwardsly; rearwards directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: moving away from a point directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: westwardly; to the west directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: outwardsly; outward directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: passing by a site directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: approaching directional space motion.
cmavo cluster FAhA* space motion tense: leftwardsly; to the left directional space motion.
cmavo MAI higher-order utterance ordinal suffix; converts a number to ordinal, usually a section/chapter.
cmavo ZAhO interval event contour: at the natural ending point of ...; completive | >|<.
lujvo d1 is stingy about giving d2 to d3. Cf. mo'a, dunda.
cmavo rafsi: mom moi MOI convert number to ordinal selbri; x1 is (n)th member of set x2 ordered by rule x3.
lujvo g1 reminds m1 of facts m2 about m3. Cf. morji, mojgaunoi, mojri'a.
lujvo x1=n1 is a message reminding facts x2=m2 about x3=m3=n2 from author x4=n3=g1 to intended audience x5=n4=m1. Cf. selmojnoi, mojgau, notci'a, gasnu, notci.
lujvo z1 has a better memory than z2 with regards to facts m2 about subject m3 by amount/excess z4.
lujvo r1 is the memory faculty of body/species r2. Cf. morji, rango, mo'isro.
lujvo r1 (event) reminds m1 of facts m2 about subject m3 under conditions r3. Cf. morji, rinka, mojgau.
lujvo p1=m1 remembers/thinks back/reminisces about p2=m3, recalling facts m2. Cf. morji, pensi.
lujvo s1 is a structure of parts s2 as a monument/memorial to m3. Cf. mrostu.
gismu rafsi: moc x1 is a point/instant/moment [0-dimensional shape/form] in/on/at time/place x2. x1 is dimensionless. See also jipno, jganu, linji, stuzi, tcika.
gismu rafsi: mol mo'u x1 is a/the mouth/oral cavity [body-part] of x2; (metaphor: entrance/intake for consumption). (adjective:) x1 is oral. See also ctebi, denci, tance.
lujvo j1=d1=m1 is a/the (palatine) uvula [body-part] of m2. See also ranmoldru, jipno.
lujvo g1 is a muzzle on m2 from moklu gacri
lujvo g1 is the palate of m2. Cf. moklu.
lujvo g1=m2 performs oral sex on g2. Cf. gletu, vibgle, gaxygle. le gletu is taken as the 'active' partner.
lujvo m1=j1 is the mandible of arthropod m2=j2 This is a mandible of a insect/other arthropod. This is not to be confused with the mandible of vertrabrates which is xedja or dzixe'a

gismu rafsi: mlo x1 is a mill/foundry/industrial plant/[assembly line] performing process x2. (unlike fanri,) need not produce a product; grain mill (= grumlo), grinding mill (= zalmlo, zalmlotci, zalmloca'a). See also gasta, gurni, tirse, fanri, zalvi.
lujvo m1=s1 is a philtrum (infranasal depression) of m2=s2. Cf. skuro, moklu, nazbi, flira.
lujvo x1 is the cheek of x2 (person/animal)

gismu rafsi: mo'o x1 is x2 mole(s) [metric unit] in substance (default is 1) by standard x3. See also centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.
lujvo x1=s2 is saliva/sput/sputum/spittle of x2=s1. Cf. kalselvi'i.
lujvo x1=v1 yawns/[breathes while stretching mouth] Cf. vasxu, moklu, tcena, sipfru, ta'irva'u.
lujvo t1 is a mouthpiece/embouchure of material t2 conveying fluid t3. Cf. tubnu, zgica'a.
lujvo x1 is the x2nd member of set x3 ordered by rule x4 .
lujvo f1 is an emulation/imitation of f2 in medium f3, emulated by method f4 and exhibiting pattern m1. Cf. morna, fukpi, monfu'igau.
lujvo x1=g1 (agent) emulates x3=f2 resulting in emulation/imitation x2=f1 in medium x4=f3 by method x5=f4 exhibiting pattern x6=m1. Cf. monfu'i.
gismu rafsi: moj mo'i x1 remembers/recalls/recollects fact(s)/memory x2 (du'u) about subject x3. See also cmavo list ba'anai, menli, pensi, sanji, djuno, notci.
gismu rafsi: mor x1 reflects Moroccan culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also friko, xrabo, muslo.

gismu rafsi: mon mo'a x1 is/reflects/represents a pattern of forms/events x2 arranged according to structure x3. [x3 is a model for x1 (= termontai, or the more abstract = termonsi'o); image (= gusmo'a, nenmo'a, dairmo'a, selylenmo'a, selmirmo'a, velmirmo'a, but also all of these -tai instead of -mo'a for the ideal)]; See also ciste, ganzu, marji, slilu, stura, tarmi, boxna, cimde, gidva, jimpe, rilti.
gismu rafsi: mro x1 is dead/has ceased to be alive. Die/mortal (= mrobi'o, co'urji'e). See also jmive, catra, betri.

gismu rafsi: mos x1 is friction [force opposing motion] due to contact/rubbing between x2 and x3; (fe) x2 rubs x3. Also x2 scrubs/wipes/brushes (against) x3 (= seltermosra); non-agentive rub (= termosra). See also sakli, sraku, jabre, satre, guska, pencu, spali.
lujvo l1 drags/hauls l2=m2 by handle/at locus l3 along surface m3. Cf. mosra, lacpu.
lujvo j1 is a bowed string instrument using bow m2. Cf. mosra, jgita, jgitrviolino, jgitrxu.
lujvo v1=m2 rubs off v2 from v3=m3 leaving remainder v4. Cf. mosra, vimcu.
fu'ivla m1 is Welsh in aspect m2.
gismu x1 is a quantity of rye [grain] of species/strain x2. See also gurni.

lujvo ml1 is ergot of species ml2. A fungus that grows on rye and other cereals; it contains the alkaloid ergotamine, which has hallucinogenic effects on humans and animals, and from which LSD!en is synthesized.
lujvo n1 is a real number. Cf. namcu, mulna'u, xarna'u.
lujvo s1 is metrology based on methodology s2.

gismu rafsi: mri x1 mails/posts [transfer via intermediary service] x2 to recipient address x3 from mailbox/post office/sender address x4 by carrier/network/system x5. Also x4 post office, mailbox. (cf. benji In which the medium need not be a 3rd party service/system, and x2 need not consist of discrete units. notci, xatra, tcana)
lujvo l1 is a mailing list with subscribers/recipients l2=m3. Cf. mrilu, ve cusku
lujvo cip1=cit1 is a vulture of species cip2. Cf. morsi, citka, cipni.
lujvo mu1 is a natural history museum for preserving [and possibly exhibiting] animals of kind mu2=d2=mo1 at location mu3. Cf. mivdalmuzga, mivyske.
lujvo x1 is mortal/subject to death. See also morsi, dimna, mroka'e
lujvo b1 mourns/grieves over the death of m1=b2
lujvo f1 is a cemetery/graveyard/burial ground for dead person(s)/animal(s) m1. Cf. morsi, mrobi'o, derse'a.
lujvo m1=k1 is mortal/capable of dying under conditions k3. Used in Theodore Reed's translation of "A Princess of Mars".
lujvo k1 is a grave in ground k2 for m1. Cf. morsi, mrostu, mrofoi, derse'a.
lujvo x1 is the cause of x2's death under conditions x3; x1 kills x2.
lujvo x1=s1 is widowed from x2=m1=s2 by law/convention x3=s3 See also: speni, nu'ospe, spesti
lujvo s1 is the grave/tomb of m1=s2. Cf. morsi, mrofoi, derse'a.
lujvo k1 buries/inters corpse/[entomb] k2=m1 at grave/cemetery/[mausoleum/crypt] k3 k4 dropped because of little use in this application.
lujvo v1 is a coffin containing v2=m1. Cf. morsi, mrostu, mrofoi.
lujvo x1 is the hammer/malleus in ear x2 in body x3
gismu rafsi: mru x1 [tool] is a hammer for/hammers x2 [target] consisting of weight/head x3 propelled by x4. See also tutci.
cmavo UI3 discursive: for example - omitting - end examples. See also mupli.
cmavo cluster UI*3 discursive: for example - omitting - end examples.
cmavo cluster UI*3 discursive: for example - omitting - end examples.
cmavo rafsi: muf NU1 abstractor: achievement (event) abstractor; x1 is the event-as-a-point/achievement of [bridi].
lujvo x1 is cosmology (in astronomy) based on methodology x2 Cf. mu'eske, kesyske, kensa, munje, krasi, saske
lujvo s1 is cosmology based on methodology s3. Cf. munje, saske, tarske, termu'eske.
lujvo t1 is a lord of universe t2=m1.
cmavo BAI mukti modal, 1st place because of motive ...
cmavo cluster BAI* sumti question asking for a motive; why?.
cmavo cluster BAI* mukti modal, 1st place despite motive ...
cmavo COI vocative: over (response OK) - more to come.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: over (response OK) - more to come.
cmavo BAI mupli modal, 1st place exemplified by ...
lujvo k1 is k2 (quantifier, default: one) spoonfuls/scoopfuls in quantity. Cf. smuci, klani.
gismu rafsi: mut x1 is immaterial/not physical/without material form. See also marji, menli, pruxi, sidbo.
lujvo x1 is a block of wood x2 with surfaces x3.
gismu rafsi: mud x1 is a quantity of/is made of/contains wood/lumber from tree(s) of type/species x2. See also tricu, stani.
lujvo j1 is a termite of species j2. Cf. jalra.
lujvo x1 is Thursday of week x2 on calendar x3.
lujvo f1 is a wood fire burning in/reacting with oxidizer f3. Omit x3=f2=m1. Cf. fagri, jelca, mudri.
lujvo p1 is a woodcutter/lumberjack using tool k1 to cut trees of species m2. Cf. mudri, katna.
lujvo p1=m1 is sawdust of wood type p2=m2. Cf. cmamudyspi, tricu.
lujvo m1 is the marriage of s1 and s2 under convention s3. Probably a misnomer for nunspe
lujvo k1 is universal in domain m2 defined by rules m3 from munje kuspe c.f. kampu
lujvo t2 is the internet/cyberspace that includes nodes/computers t1=s1 whose function/purpose is s2. Cf. munje, skami, tcana, samseltcana, kagysamseltcana, internet.
cmavo cluster PA* number/quantity: 5,000 expressed with comma.

gismu rafsi: muk mu'i x1 (action/event/state) motivates/is a motive/incentive for action/event x2, per volition of x3. Also; x3 is motivated to bring about result/goal/objective x2 by x1 (= termu'i for reordered places); (note that 'under conditions' BAI may apply and be appropriately added to the main predicate level or within the x2 action level). (cf. cmavo list mu'i, nibli, te zukte - generally better for 'goal', se jalge, krinu, rinka, ciksi, djica, xlura)
lujvo x1 is completed in property x2 according to standard x3
lujvo x1 (event) is after x2 (event) concludes. x1 is in the future when x2 finishes
lujvo f1 is the end/finish/completion of completed thing/process f2=m1.
lujvo g1 makes m1 complete in property m2 by standard m4. Cf. mulno, gasnu, tolcfari'i.
lujvo g1=m1 is a complete set showing common property (ka) g2, complete by standard m3. Cf. mulno, girzu

lujvo g1=m1 is a mass/team/aggregate/whole, together composed solely/completely/wholly of components x2, considered jointly, by standard m3. From mulno + gunma. Just gunma with a complete specification of members. m2 dropped since the property is always "membership in the mass in question". m3 left in since it seems to do no harm, although its meaning seems a bit unclear here.
lujvo x1 is almost/nearly done/complete/finished/whole in property x2 by standard x3. See also so'a
lujvo s1=mn1 is an indivisible / prime number in integer domain s2. Made from mulna'u + selci.;

gismu rafsi: mul mu'o x1 (event) is complete/done/finished; x1 (object) has become whole in property x2 by standard x3. Also perfected, entirety; (adverb/adjective:) entire, total, integral, fully, totally, wholly, completely, entirely. See also fanmo, culno, pagbu, xadba, prane, jalge, sumji, munje, sisti, xadni.
lujvo p1 is the integer result of multiplying integer p2 by integer p3. Made from mulno + pilji. See also mulna'u, mulna'usle.

lujvo x1 is a eukaryote of species x2. An eukaryote is an organism whose cells contain complex structures enclosed within membranes. All species of large complex organisms are eukaryotes, including animals (=danlu), plants (=spati) and fungi (=mledi, although most species of eukaryote are protist microorganisms (=jurme).
lujvo m1=t3 (du'u) is unanimous / based on complete agreement among t1=t2.
lujvo x1 is a starfish of species x2. Cf. mu, birka, curnu.
lujvo x1 is a Friday of week x2 in calendar x3.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantifier selbri: convert 5 to cardinal selbri; x1 is a set with the quintet of members x2.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert 5 to ordinal selbri; x1 is fifth among x2 ordered by rule x3.

lujvo p1 is the fifth closest planet (default is Jupiter if p2 is the Sun) revolving around p2 (default is the Sun), with planetary characteristics p3, orbital parameters p4. Cf. mumplin, pavyplini, relplini etc.; see also terdi, solri, mluni, lunra, plinycma, tarci'e.
lujvo x1 is May/the fifth month of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavmasti, nanca.

lujvo j1 has the rank of Colonel/Captain/Group Captain (equivalent of NATO OF-5) in military unit /organization j2. Cf. mu, moi, jatna, jemja'a, vairsoi, xavmoija'a, vonmoija'a. Based on STANAG 2116: NATO Codes for Grades of Military Personnel.
lujvo m1=d1 is the little finger of d2. Cf. degji.

gismu rafsi: muj mu'e x1 is a universe/cosmos [complete and ordered entirety] of domain/sphere x2 defined by rules x3. Also world; a universe is a kind of system, one which comprehensively encompasses its domain; e.g. 'universe of discourse', or 'world of birds'; x3 are the rules/defining principles which distinguish the universe from other universes, or from non-universe. See also ciste, plini, kensa, mulno.
lujvo c1 takes a sample of c2=m2 from source/set c3=m3. Cf. cpacu.

Also mobile (= comymu'u, for the non-specific opposite of immobile); after a muvdu, object is alienated from/no longer at origin (unless physically returned there, per litru or slilu); agentive move (= muvgau, muvzu'e), non-agentive transitive move (= muvri'a), self-propelled (= sezmuvgau), motion of a part of the object (= pagmu'u), having a moving part (= muvypau, muvyselpau); apparent motion (= mlumu'u). (cf. rinci, klama (which differs in that the means of motion is explicit), litru, cliva, fatri; dunda, benji for agentive movement that does not necessarily imply alienation from origin, preja for similar movement with no agent implied, bevri, vimcu)
