lujvo k1 descends/goes down to k2=c1 from k3=c2 via k4 using means k5. Cf. cnita, klama.
lujvo z1=c1 is lower than z2 beneath c2 in frame of reference c3 by amount/excess z4. Cf. cnita, zmadu, nitrai.
lujvo t1=c1 is the lowest among set/range t4 beneath c2 in frame of reference c3. Cf. cnita, traji, nitmau.
lujvo s1 dips at an angle of s2 to reference frame s3, to beneath c2. Cf. cnita, salpo, sa'orgau.
lujvo z1 sits on surface z2=c1 that is below c2 in frame of refernce c3. Cf. cnita, zutse, cfatse.
fu'ivla g1 is g2 newton (s) of force (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. klanrniut,ni, ki'orgratretrefrinynidysnidu.
gismu rafsi: niv x1 (agent) knits x2 [cloth/object] from yarn/thread x3. See also cilta, fenso, jivbu, pijne.
lujvo c1=n2 is a sweater of material c2=n3. A knitted jacket or jersey, usually of thick wool. Cf. creka, tafrkardiga.
cmene Miss Cf. nixli, nanl, naun, nim.
gismu rafsi: nix xli x1 is a girl [young female person] of age x2 immature by standard x3. Word dispreferred in metaphor/example as sexist; (use verba). See also nanla, verba, ninmu.
cmavo GOhA pro-bridi: repeats the bridi in which this one is embedded.
cmavo rafsi: nor no'e NAhE midpoint scalar negator: neutral point between je'a and to'e; "not really".
cmavo cluster NAhE+BO negation sumti qualifier: the neutral form/value of. Cf. no'e, bo, na'ebo, je'abo, to'ebo. Midpoint between je'abo and to'ebo.
cmavo NIhO discursive: paragraph break; resume previous topic.
cmavo GOI non-restrictive appositive phrase marker: which incidentally is the same thing as ...

gismu rafsi: nol no'i x1 is noble/aristocratic/elite/high-born/titled in/under culture/society/standard x2. Also upper-class; high/low, upper/lower are poor Lojban metaphors; note x2 standard applies when the title/nobility is not recognized culture/society wide; this would include self-assumed titles. See also banli.
cmavo cluster KOhA* logically quantified sumti: nothing at all (unless restricted).
cmavo NOI non-restrictive relative clause; attaches subordinate bridi with incidental information.
lujvo c1 announces/proclaims c2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) for audience c3=n4 via expressive medium c4. Cf. notci, cusku.
lujvo b1=n1 is titled with high aristocratic/noble/elite status in/under culture/society b3=n2. Cf. nobli, banli, kamba'i. 'Your Highness' or 'Your Majesty' is {doi nolba'i).
lujvo x1 is an orb made of b2 used by n1. Cf. nobli, bolci, nolga'a, trumapku.
lujvo g1 is a sceptre made of g2 used by n1. Cf. nobli, grana, nolboi, ri'irga'a, trumapku.
fu'ivla x1 is a Jedi of power / level / rank x2
lujvo k1 is a courtier to sovereign/aristocrat/noble k2 in culture/country n2=k3. Cf. nobli, kansa, nolse'u, nolraitru, noltronau, noltruni'u, balnoltru.
lujvo m1 is a crown made of m2. Cf. nobli, mapku, trumapku, nolboi, nolga'a.
lujvo m1=n1 is elegant to m2=n2. Cf. melbi.
cmene Sir Cf. nobli, nanmu, nol, nolnim.
lujvo ni1=no1 is a lady, considered noble in culture/society/standard no2. Cf. nobli.
cmene Madam Cf. nobli, ninmu, nol, nolnaum.
lujvo t1=n1 is a regent/monarch of t2 by standard n2. Cf. nobli, traji, turni, balnoltru, noltruni'u, noltrunau, noltroni'u, noltronau, nolse'u, nolkansa, gugja'a, truralju.
lujvo s1 is a servant of sovereign/aristocrat/noble s2=n1 in culture/country n2 with responsibilities s3. Cf. nobli, selfu, nolkansa, nolraitru, balnoltru.
lujvo s1 is a throne/ceremonial chair used by noble/aristocratic/elite/high-born/titled in/under culture/society/standard n2. Cf. nobli, stizu, trustizu.
lujvo ni1=j1=no1 is a Duke/Baron/Count/Earl/Marquess/ [titled noble of middle rank] ruling j2 under culture/standard no2. Cf. nobli, jitro, nanmu, noltroni'u, noltruni'u, nolraitru, balnoltru.
lujvo ni1=j1=no1 is a Duchess/Baroness/Countess/Marchioness/ [titled noble of middle rank] ruling j2 under culture/standard no2.. Cf. nobli, jitro, ninmu, noltronau, noltruni'u, nolraitru, balnoltru.
lujvo x1 is the king of x2 by standard x3. see also noltruni'u, nolraitru
lujvo x1 is the queen of x2 by standard x3. see also noltrunau, nolraitru
lujvo z1 is a palace of/for noble person(s) n1=z2. Cf. badydi'u.
lujvo z1=n1 the classical music performed at/by z2 (event) originating in culture n1. Cf. nobli, zgike, dzeklu, ronri'izgi, naizgi, sopselneizgi, dja'aza, te'ekno.
cmavo cluster MAI* discursive utterance ordinal: zeroth section/chapter ordinal; foreword.
lujvo x1 is a Sunday of week x2 in calendar x3. Sunday is either day seven or day zero, depending on your perspective.
lujvo x1 is undecided/makes no decision about x2. See also aicu'i
lujvo x1 is alone/lonely/lonesome in state/condition/enterprise x2. Cf. kansa, seicni.
lujvo c2 disbelieves in god/deity c1 with dominion over c3; c2 is an atheist. Cf. cevni, ceikri, nalceikri, selcei, pavyselcei, sorselcei, ceirsenpi.
lujvo x1 is available for free/without cost to x2 from provider x3.
lujvo x1 is invisible from point-of-view x2.
lujvo j2 (du'u) is a mystery for j1, the subject being j3. Cf. jimpe, mipri.
lujvo x1 is nonsense/nonsensical to x2. See also no smuni
lujvo x1 is the additive inverse of x2. See also va'a
cmene Nora LeChevalier (was Tansky) Nora is one of the Original Lojbanists
lujvo c1 neither gets c2 from c3 nor puts c2 at c3 see also tolcpa
fu'ivla x1 reflects Norman culture/nationality/language in aspect x2.
cmavo cluster ROI* tense interval modifier: never; objectively quantified tense; defaults as time tense.
lujvo x1 is indifferent/neutral/apathetic about event x2, expected likelihood x3. Cf. no'e, pacna, tolpa'a, norzau.
lujvo x1 is indifferent/apathetic/dispassionate/uninvolved/unmoved towards/with/by x2. See also iunai
lujvo x1=c2 is disinterested in x2=c1. Cf. cinri, selci'i, nalselci'i, tolselci'i, a'ucu'i.
lujvo s1=v1 is an interpretation of s2 recognized by s3 but judged unimportant by v2. no'e+vajni+smuni

fu'ivla x1 is a norovirus of species/breed/defining property x2 capable of infecting [at] x3. From the city of Norwalk, Ohio, and vidru. The scientific name of the virus was first "Norwalk agent" and then shortened to "norovirus". See also xilvidru, remjinkytoldu'evidru and vidru.
lujvo x1 is indifferent towards x2. Cf. no'e, zanru, norpa'a.

gismu rafsi: not noi x1 is a message/notice/memorandum about subject x2 from author x3 to intended audience x4. Emphasis on brevity, single or identifiable subject (contrast with xatra: the emphasis in notci is on the single or cohesively focused subject, while the audience is less defined - indeed only an 'intended' audience. xatra need not have a single or focussed subject - its corresponding place is for 'content'); reminder/memo/note (= mojnoi). See also xatra, nuzba, mrilu, morji.
lujvo c1 notes down c2 on display/storage medium c3 with writing implement c4. Cf. notci, ciska, selmojnoi.
lujvo c1 announces/proclaims c2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) for audience c3=n4 via expressive medium c4. Cf. notci, cusku.
cmavo rafsi: nun NU abstractor: generalized event abstractor; x1 is state/process/achievement/activity of [bridi].
cmavo NUhA convert mathematical expression (mex) operator to a selbri/tanru component.
cmavo COI vocative: promise - promise release - un-promise.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: promise - promise release - un-promise.
cmavo cluster COI* vocative: promise - promise release - un-promise.
cmavo NUhI start forethought termset construct; marks start of place structure set with logical connection.
cmavo rafsi: nu'o CAhA modal aspect: can but has not; unrealized potential.
lujvo x1=s1 is single (never been married) by law/convention x2=s3 See also: speni, spesti, mrospe, spenu'e
cmavo NUhU elidable terminator: end forethought termset; usually elidable except with following sumti.
gismu rafsi: nuk x1 is magenta/fuchsia/purplish-red [color adjective]. See also skari, blabi, xekri, kandi, carmi, xunre, zirpu.
lujvo n1 is an event of b1 being foolish/silly/stupid in event/action /property (ka) b2. Cf. nu, bebna, kambebna.
lujvo n1 is a conversation involving c1(s) (mass normally, but 1 individual/jo'u possible) about topic/subject c2. Cf. nu, casnu.
lujvo n1 is the killing by c1 of c2 by action/method c3. Cf. nu, catra.
lujvo n1 is the youth of c1. Cf. nu, citno.
lujvo x1=n1 is a change in property/quantity x2=c2 (ka/ni) of amount/degree x3=c3 under conditions x4=c4. Cf. nu, cenba, galfi, stika.
lujvo n1 is order (state of being well arranged) of c1 with orderliness c2. Cf. cnici, kalsa, ganzu.
lujvo n1 is an event at which c1 eat(s) c2. Cf. nu, citka, sanmi, ctisla, balsai.
lujvo n1 is a fight/battle in which d1 fights d2 over issue d3 (abstract). Cf. nu, damba, nundamba, terjvi.
lujvo n1 is a fight/battle in which d1 fights d2 over issue d3 (abstract). Cf. nu, damba, nunda'a, terjvi.
lujvo n1 is a dance with dancer(s) d1 (individual, mass) to music/rhythm d2. Cf. dansu, seldansu.
lujvo n1 is a pause by d1 for/until d2 at state d3 before starting/continuing d4 (activity/process). Cf. nu, denpa.
lujvo n1 is a pause by d1 for/until d2 at state d3 before starting/continuing d4 (activity/process). Cf. nu, denpa, nunde'a.
lujvo n1 is the equality of rights k1=d3 entitled to k2=d1=d2.
lujvo n1 is a facial expression (countenance) of agent f2=c1 expressing f1=c2. Cf. flira, cusku.

lujvo n1 is a trial of dispute j2 involving people f3. Cf. nu, pajni, tavla, fapro, nunpai, flapaizda. x3 includes not only the disputing parties but also the judge and juries, which may be connected with "jo'u".
lujvo n1 is the decay/fermentation (recycling of matter/energy/electrons) of f1 by chemical agent f2.

lujvo n1 is fishery (fish industry) of product c2 (aquatic animals) from source/area c3=t1 (ocean/sea/coast/lake/river) by fishermen c1. x2 can be any harvestable aquatic animals, including mollusks and crustaceans. Cf. crepu.
lujvo n1 is the life of j1.

lujvo x1 is a gathering/meeting/assembly/conclave/conference/ congregation/congress/convention/encounter/get-together/reunion of participants x2 at location x3 from locations x4. Cf. nu, jmaji, jdijmaji, nunpe'i for a meeting between two parties.

lujvo n1 is an established connection between j1 and j2 at common locus j3. n1 or j1 may be a mass formed with "joi", as is the case in a computer network between a server and clients. Cf. jorne, srana.

lujvo n1 is a condition of ku1 managing the health of ka1. Usually the prevention, treatment, and management of illness and the preservation of mental and physical well-being through the services offered by the medical, nursing, and allied health professions. x2 and x3 may the same or different. Cf. kamnu'a.
lujvo n1 is a game played by k1 playing with plaything/toy k2 Cf. nu, kelci, terjvi, ci'erkei.
lujvo n1 is the lateness of l1 (event) by standard l2. Cf. nu, lerci.
lujvo n1 is the laugh/laughter of/by c1 from nu cmila
lujvo n1 is medical, involving doctor/nurse m1, patient m2, ailment m3, and treatment/cure m4. Cf. mikce, kurji, sidju.
lujvo n1 is the death (state of being dead) of m1 (person).
lujvo n1 is the event of m1 motivating action m2 per volition m3.
lujvo n1 is a trial/judgement/arbitration with judge/arbitrator/referee p1 determining/deciding matter p2. Cf. nu, pajni, nunflapai, flapaizda.
lujvo x1 is a meeting between x2 and x3 at/in location x4. Cf. nu, penmi, nunjmaji, jdijmaji.
lujvo x1 is a believe-deceived with deceive-belief subject x2 with deception subject x3.
lujvo n1 is self-restraint shown by f1=s2 from nu sevzi fanta c.f. sezyfanta
lujvo n1 is an event of integration between s1=b1
lujvo n1 is engineering in branch s2 based on methodology s3 from nu saske zukte
lujvo n1 is the marriage of s1 and s2 according to tradition s3.
lujvo n1 is the effort of t1 trying/attempting to do/attain t2 (event/state/property) by actions/method t3 from nu troci
lujvo n1 is agriculture of product c2 from source/area c3=t1 by farmers c1 cf. tumla, crepu, cange.
lujvo n1 is an earthquake at location t2. Cf. nu, tumla, desku.
lujvo s1 is a trip/drug-induced hallucination about s2 due to chemical substance xu2 with purity xu3. Cf. mrajymledi, ciksne.
lujvo n1 is the freedom of z1 doing z2 under condition z3. Cf. nu, zifre, kamyzi'e, selzi'e, zi'ejva.
gismu rafsi: nup nu'e x1 (agent) promises/commits/assures/threatens x2 (event/state) to x3 [beneficiary/victim]. See also kajde, xusra.
lujvo b1 archives s1=b2 in medium b5. snura benji; see also vreji, fukpi, citri, jmaji, sorcu, morji
lujvo f1 is a backup / danger avoiding duplicate / copy of f2=s1 in form / medium f3 made by method f4 to protect / secure against event s2 (generally destruction or loss). Made from snura + fukpi.
gismu rafsi: num x1 is a rural/rustic/pastoral area of x2; x1 is in the country. See also jarbu, rarna, tcadu, cange.
fu'ivla x1 is a neutron in quantum state x2. Cf. lektoni, protoni, kuarka, xumsle.
lujvo x1 saves/rescues/redeems/delivers x2=s1 from threat/peril s2

gismu rafsi: nul nu'i x1 is neutral/not taking sides/medial/not towards any extreme on scale/in dissension x2. Also x2 dispute/struggle (though x2 is not limited to disagreements, which is merely one manifestation of scalar or distributed values in which there is a medial position). See also midju, lanxe, milxe, mutce, cmavo list no'e.
gismu rafsi: nuz x1 (du'u) is news/tidings/new information about subject x2 from source x3, to observer x4. See also cnino, notci.
lujvo no1 is a news/press release with news nu1 about subject nu2=no2 issued by no3 for audience no4. Cf. nuzba, notci.
cmavo A logical connective: sumti afterthought biconditional/iff/if-and-only-if.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: pride - modesty/humility - shame. See also jgira, cumla, ckeji.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: pride - modesty/humility - shame.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: pride - modesty/humility - shame.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: closeness - distance. See also cnijbi, cnikansa.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: caution - rashness. See also capyrivbi, capfanta, srerivbi, srefanta, naldarsi, seljde.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: patience - mere tolerance - anger. See also fengu, to'ersteba, de'acni
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: patience - mere tolerance - anger.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: patience - mere tolerance - anger.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: relaxation - composure - stress. See also surla, cnilanxe, dunku.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: relaxation - composure - stress.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: relaxation - composure - stress.
fu'ivla x1 is a walrus of breed x2. Cf. mabru, arktik, xamsi.
fu'ivla x1 is a dragonfly/damselfly (order Odonata) of species x2. Cf. ansoptera, zgoptera, laxsfani, sfani, cinki.
cmavo UI1 attitudinal: complaint - pleasure. See also pante, pluka, kufra.
cmavo cluster UI*1 attitudinal: mental complaint (puzzlement, excess mental work).
fu'ivla x1 is an octopus of species x2 see also tu'urbirka
fu'ivla g1 is g2 ohm(s) of electrical impedance/resistance (default is 1) by standard g3. Cf. klanrxomi, xampo, klanrvolta, klanrxuati, klanrzimenzi.
cmavo cluster A* logical connective: sumti afterthought exclusive or; Latin 'aut'.
fu'ivla x1 is an orca/killer whale (Orcinus orca) of breed x2
fu'ivla x1 is broomrape of species x2. see also rasykobli
fu'ivla x1 is an oyster of species x2. Cf. cakcurnu.
fu'ivla x1 is an octopus of species x2. See also tu'urbirka.
cmavo BAI panra modal, 1st place (parallel; shared property) similarly; in addition to ...
cmavo cluster BAI* sumti: explicitly marks respective use as in "THEY read THEIR (respective) books".
lujvo b1 is Esperanto. Cf. pacna, bangu, spe'ato, lojbo, runbau.
cmavo cluster BAI* among (with a share for each)
cmavo UI3 discursive: justice - prejudice. See also tcinydracu'a, tcinydrapai, vudypai.
cmavo VUhU2 binary mathematical operator: ratio; [the ratio of a to b].
cmavo FAhA3 location tense relation/direction; transfixing/passing through ...

lujvo pi1 is a cross section/tomogram, a picture of slice pa1=pi2 of pa2 made by pi3 in medium pi4. samterpli pa'oxra = CAT scan. There is another kind of tomogram which may be better termed tadmijyxra.
cmavo BAI pagbu modal, 1st place having component ...

gismu rafsi: pa'a x1 hopes/wishes for/desires x2 (event), expected likelihood x3 (0-1); x1 hopes that x2 happens. Also: x1 is hopeful of x2; x2 will hopefully occur, as hoped for by x1; the value of x3 is a subjective estimate of likeliness according to x1, and is the basic determinant of whether pacna means 'hope' or 'wish' or 'expect': hoping for objects/states with negligible expectation is "wishing"; if the state is plausibly likely, it is "hoping"; when the probability is subjectively near 1, the attitude is described as "expecting"; the value will usually be expressed using inexact numbers ("li piso'u" to "li piro"); wish (= sotpa'a), hope (= sorpa'a), expect (= sojypa'a). See also djica.
lujvo t1 is the Hell of evil spirit(s) t2=pa1=pr1, evil by standard pa2. Cf. palci, pruxi, ruxse'i, dapma, lijda
lujvo x1=z2=p1 is a sin/evil action by x2=z1 for purpose/goal z3, evil/depraved/wicked (morally bad) by standerd x4=p2. Cf. jdazei, zekri.
lujvo xl1 (agent) tempts xl2 into evil xl3=p1 by influence/threat/lure xl4, said act being evil by standard p2. Cf. xlura, palci, jdazei.
lujvo z1 sins by doing z2=p1 by standard p2.
cmene Dad The rafsi for patfu used as a familar name. See also mam, bes, tix, bun, mes.
gismu rafsi: pag pau x1 is a part/component/piece/portion/segment of x2 [where x2 is a whole/mass]; x2 is partly x1. Partly (= selpau). See also cmavo list pa'u, mulno, xadba, spisa, gunma, rafsi.

gismu rafsi: gre x1 passes through/penetrates barrier/medium/portal x2 to destination side x3 from origin side x4. Passing through in both directions (= rolfargre, pagre ... .i so'ivo'ivo'u (and vice versa)). See also bitmu, denci, ganlo, kalri, vorme, pluta, canko, ragve.
lujvo p1=c1 is a tab (navigational widget) in p2=c2. x2 is usually a web browser or a text editor. Cf. pagbu, canko.
lujvo p1=g1 is a constituent country of p2 (sovereign state / supranational body). Cf. gugde, zifyje'a.
lujvo j1=p1 gives a verdict j2 (du'u) about matter j3=p2 (abstract). Cf. pajni, jdice.
lujvo p1=k1 is a jury/judging panel deciding matter p2 in court/judging body k3.
lujvo c1 is a member of jury/judging panel c2=p1=k1 deciding matter p2 in court/judging body k3.
lujvo x1 is fair/just/equitable/impartial/unprejudiced/unbiased in judging/refereeing/arbitrating/determining/deciding matter x2. See also pajni, nutli, pa'e
lujvo j2 is a verdict given by j1=p1 about matter j3=p2 (abstract). Cf. pajni, jdice.
lujvo c1=t1=p1 is the judicial branch of the government of people/territory/domain/subjects t2. Cf. pajni, turni, ciste, truci'e, zuktruci'e, flatruci'e, flacfatrugri, flazautrugri, vajraifla.

gismu rafsi: pai x1 judges/referees/arbitrates/is a judge determining/deciding matter x2 (abstract). x2 includes jei = rule (jetpai), ni = estimate (lairpai), ka = evaluate (kairpai or vampai), or nu = referee/arbitrate (faurpai); single events of judging including specific decisions/judgements (= paijdi, jetpaijdi, lairpaijdi, kairpaijdi, vampaijdi, faurpaijdi); jury (= pairkamni), serve on a jury (= kamnypai, as part of mass x1). See also cuxna, jdice, vajni, cipra, zekri, manri, mansa.
cmavo cluster PA* number/quantity: 1,000 expressed with comma.
lujvo x1 gets promoted to x2 (object, state).
gismu rafsi: pac x1 is evil/depraved/wicked [morally bad] by standard x2. See also zekri, vrude, xlali, marde, mabla.
lujvo x1 promotes x2 to x3 (object, state).
gismu rafsi: pak x1 are pants/trousers/slacks/leggings [legged garment] of material x2. See also taxfu, pastu, skaci.

gismu x1 is a tray/platter/flat container [pan/sheet/griddle] of contents x2, and made of material x3. Also pallet, when used for carrying rather than support on the ground; a tray is flat-bottomed and shallow or without a rim, and is generally portable. See also tansi, patxu, palta, ckana.
fu'ivla x1 is a Sith / Dark Jedi of power / level / rank x2
gismu x1 is a plate/dish/platter/saucer [flat/mildly concave food service bed] made of material x2. See also ckana, palne, kabri, tansi, ckana.
lujvo l1 (agent) washes dishes l2 of soil/contaminant l3 with cleaning material(s) l4 Cf. paltylumca'a, zbabu, ctitcilu'i.
lujvo c1 is a dishwasher (machine). Cf. taflumca'a, zbabu, ctitcilu'i, paltylu'i.
cmavo cluster MAI* discursive: first utterance ordinal.

gismu x1 is a pump/injector [tool/apparatus] pumping/inserting fluid x2 to x3 from x4 by means x5. x2 fluid may be liquid or gas; x5 may be a force; a pump generally causes a pressure gradient, such that x3 is a place of lower pressure, x4 a place of higher pressure. (cf. gapci, litki, rinci; metaphorical use of fepri for gas, risna for liquid, rinci, tutci)
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert 1 to cardinal selbri; x1 is a set with single/sole/only member x2.
lujvo j1 hugs/embraces j2 with j3 (part of j1) at locus j4 (part of j2).
lujvo p1&p2=l1 (mass) date via route l2 using means l3. Cf. litru, penmi.
cmavo cluster MAI* discursive utterance ordinal: first section/chapter ordinal.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert 1 to ordinal selbri; x1 is first among x2 ordered by rule x3.
lujvo pr1=pe1 is a lover of pr2=pe2. Cf. prami, pendo, glepe'o, cinse
gismu rafsi: pan x1 is an odor/fragrance/scent/smell emitted by x2 and detected by observer/sensor x3. An undetected emitter is odorless to the observer. See also nazbi, sumne, cpina.
gismu rafsi: pad x1 (agent) punctuates x2 (expression) with symbol/word x3 with syntactic/semantic effect x4. See also lerfu, basna, denpa.
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of sponge/porous material. Also metaphorically used for coral, Swiss cheese. See also cokcu for a generalized absorbant.
lujvo j1=p2 is incense emitting odor p1. Cf. panjelga'a, sumne, ritli, lijda, budjo, danmo.
lujvo g1=p2 is an incense stick with odor x2=p1. Cf. panjelca.
lujvo x1 is a sponge of species x2.
lujvo x1 is a loofa of variety x2.
gismu x1 is a park/land reserve managed by community/polity/company x2 for purpose x3. See also sorcu, zdile, klaji, purdi.
gismu rafsi: pa'o x1 is a slice [thin flat portion] of x2 (mass). See also nanba.
cmavo cluster PA* number/quantity: 10,000,000 [ten millions](Western numbering system/1,00,00,000 [100 lakhs](Indian numbering system). Cf. panonoki'o.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantifier selbri: convert 10 to cardinal selbri; x1 is a set with the decade of members x2.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert 10 to ordinal selbri; x1 is tenth among x2 ordered by rule x3.
cmavo cluster PA* number/quantity: 100,000 [hundred thousand](Western numbering system)/[one lakh](Indian numbering system).. Cf. panoki'oki'o.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantifier selbri: convert 100 to cardinal selbri; x1 is a set with the century of members x2.
gismu rafsi: pap x1 is at peace with x2. (cf. jamna; use sarxe, smaji, tugni for most metaphorical extensions, cilce, jamna)

gismu x1 parallels x2 differing only in property x3 (ka; jo'u/fa'u term) by standard/geometry x4. Also: x1 is parallel to x2, x3 is the only difference between x1 and x2 (= terpanra for reordered places); x1 and x2 are alike/similar/congruent. A parallel involves extreme close similarity/correspondence across the entirety of the things being compared, generally involving multiple properties, with focus placed on one or a small number of differences. See also pa'a, mintu, simsa, girzu, vrici.
gismu rafsi: pat x1 protests/objects to/complains about x2 (event/state) to audience x3 with action x4. (x4 is an event or tu'a quotation) See also xarnu.
gismu rafsi: paz x1 is a [biological] offspring/child/kid/hybrid of parent(s) x2; (adjective:) x1 is filial. See also grute, verba, bersa, tixnu, se rorci, patfu.

gismu x1 is a [physical] page/leaf of book/document/bound mass of pages x2. Numbered pages (as in a book) are the sides of a page (= paprysfe, paprysfelai); a pageful of text (= papryseltcidu, paprytcidylai). See also karni, pelji, prina, xatra, vreji, pezli, cukta, ciska.
lujvo x1 make up/peace with each other under condition x2. Cf. panpi, simxu, binxo, simpapybi'o.

gismu rafsi: pab x1 (me'o, fraction) is a ratio/rate of x2 (quantity) with respect to x3 (quantity), [x2:x3]. Also x1 fraction/proportion/quotient; x2 dividend/numerator; x3 divisor/denominator. See also frinu, dilcu, mekso.
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert 12 to cardinal selbri; x1 is a set with a dozen members x2.
lujvo k1=c1 creeps/crawls to k2 from k3 via k4 using k5=c4. Cf. cpare, klama, reskla, cidydzu.
cmavo cluster ROI* tense interval modifier: once; objectively quantified tense; defaults as time tense.

fu'ivla x1 is a tunic of material x2. A garment worn over the torso, with or without sleeves, and of various lengths reaching from the hips to the ankles. Originated in Greece and Ancien Rome. tu'inka for type 4. Cf. pastu.
gismu rafsi: pas x1 is a robe/tunic/gown/cloak/dress/[coveralls] [a long/full body garment] of material x2. Also coveralls (= paspalku). See also kosta, taxfu, palku.
lujvo s1=p1 is a dress/gown (full-length un-legged garment) of material s2=p2.
gismu rafsi: paf pa'u x1 is a father of x2; x1 begets/sires/acts paternal towards x2; [not necessarily biological]. See also mamta, rirni, rorci, tarbi, dzena, famti, panzi, bersa, sovda.
gismu x1 is a potato [an edible tuber] of variety/cultivar x2. (use samcu for starchy/tuberous roots that do not reproduce from eyes of tuber); See also genja, jalna, samcu.
lujvo pa1=pe1 disapprovingly minds/cares pa2=pe2. Cf. pante, pensi.
lujvo c1=p1 protests expressing c2 to audience c3=p3 via medium c4 about p2. Cf. pante, cusku, patspu.
lujvo s1=p1 protests/objects to/complains about s2=p2 with action s3=p4 to audience p3. Cf. pante, spuda, patsku, patyva'u.
lujvo x1=p1 is Protestant in aspect x2. Cf. xriso, pante, glixi'o, sunxi'o, la'orxi'o, lijda.
gismu rafsi: pax x1 is a pot/kettle/urn/tub/sink, a deep container for contents x2, of material/properties x3. (cf. tansi, palne for depth; baktu, botpi for open/lidded)
lujvo v1=p1 sighs in exasperation responding to p2 (event/state). Cf. pante, vasxu, patspu.
cmavo UI3a discursive: optional question premarker. See also preti.
cmavo cluster UI*3 discursive: unreal/rhetorical question follows.
lujvo p1 is a bond issued by d1 held by d3. Cf. pagbu, dejni, terdejni, ze'i zei seldejni, ze'u zei seldejni, posfai.
lujvo b1 is the first Buddha, Siddhartha Gautama. Cf. budjo, pa, moi, lijda, censa
lujvo x1 is a Monday of week x2 on calendar x3.
lujvo x1 is the reciprocal/multiplicative inverse of x2 . See also fa'i

lujvo c1 is strictly heterosexual in situation c2 by standard c4. This word does not apply to bisexuals and is the direct Lojban equivalent of English "heterosexual". Cf. pavycinse, dutcinse, pavmitcinse.
lujvo t1 is a vehicle of units x2 for monorail x3, propelled by x4. Cf. trene.

lujvo x1 is January/the first month of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. relmasti, cibmasti, vonmasti, mumymasti, xavmasti, zelmasti, bivmasti, sozymasti, pavnonmasti, pavypavmasti, pavrelmasti, nanca, kanbyma'i.

lujvo c1 is strictly homosexual in situation c2 by standard c4. This word does not apply to bisexuals and is the direct Lojban equivalent of English "homosexual". Cf. pavycinse, mitcinse, pavdutcinse.

lujvo j1 has the rank of Lieutenant/1st Lieutenant (equivalent of NATO OF-1) in military unit /organization j2. Cf. pa, moi, jatna, jemja'a, vairsoi, relmoija'a. Based on STANAG 2116: NATO Codes for Grades of Military Personnel.
lujvo x1 is October/the tenth month of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavmasti, nanca.

lujvo j1 has the rank of Field Marshall/General of the Army//Fleet Admiral/Marshall of the Air Force (equivalent of NATO OF-10) in military unit j2. Cf. pa, no, moi, jatna, jemja'a, vairsoi, sozmoija'a, bivmoija'a. Based on STANAG 2116: NATO Codes for Grades of Military Personnel.
lujvo x1 is December/the twelfth month of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavmasti, nanca.
lujvo x1 happens once in interval x2. Cf. pa, roi, paroi.

lujvo c1 is monosexual in situation c2 by standard c4. Monosexual means sexual interest in only one sex/gender, so this word does not apply to bisexuals (= relcinse). Cf. fetcinse, nakcinse, mitcinse, dutcinse.
lujvo x1 is November/the eleventh month of year x2 in calendar x3. Cf. pavmasti, nanca.

lujvo p1 is the closest planet (default is Mercury if p2 is the Sun) revolving around p2 (default is the Sun), with planetary characteristics p3, orbital parameters p4. Cf. pavyplin, relplini, cibyplini etc.; see also terdi, solri,mluni, lunra, plinycma, tarci'e.
lujvo p1=s1 is alone, lacking the company of s2.
lujvo c2 believes in one god/deity c1 with dominion over c3; c2 is a monotheist. Cf. cevni, ceikri, nalceikri, selcei, nonselcei, sorselcei, ceirsenpi.
lujvo j2 is a monopole with end j1.
lujvo x1 is a unicorn. Refers specifically to animals of the unicorn species, not the result of removing a horn from a two-horned animal.
lujvo s1 is the single, unambiguous meaning of s2 recognized/accepted by s3; x2=s2 is unambiguous/explicit according to x3=s3.
lujvo c2 dies (non-agentively) from cause c3. from zi'o and catra
lujvo k1 is k2 (quantifier, default: one) potfuls in quantity. Cf. patxu, klani.
fu'ivla p1 is a double boiler/bain-marie containing p2 made of p3
lujvo x1 miscarries after being pregnant with x2
cmavo GOI restrictive relative phrase marker: which is associated with ...; loosest associative/possessive.
cmavo rafsi: pev UI3c marks a construct as figurative (non-literal/metaphorical) speech/text.
cmavo PEhE marks the following connective as joining termsets.
cmavo UI2 evidential: I opine (subjective claim). See also jinvi.
cmavo PEhO forethought flag for mathematical expression (mex) Polish (forethought) operator.
lujvo x1 are friends (of each other, distributively) This is the jvajvo version of simpe'o. cf pendo and simxu
cmavo CAI attitudinal: attitudinal question; how do you feel about it? with what intensity?.
lujvo x1=f1=p1 is baffled/befuddled/perplexed/flummoxed by subject x2=p2; x1=f1=p1 is stuck on problem x2=p2.
lujvo p1=c1 thinks thought c2=p2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept). Verbal or near-verbal expression of a thought; internal monologue. Made from pensi + cusku.
lujvo x1=p1 thinks back to origin/earlier state x3 about p2 (abstraction). Cf. pensi, xruti, morji.
lujvo g1 (agent) spreads p1 over/into p2 from p3. Cf. preja, gasnu, tcena, fatri, muvdu.
gismu rafsi: ple x1 is paper from source x2. Sheet of paper (= plekarda if shape is important, plebo'o). See also karni, papri, prina.
lujvo x1 is a lemon of variety x2. Cf. pelxu, nimre, ri'ornimre, najnimre, branimre, nimre.
lujvo x1 is an apricot [fruit] of species/variety x2 Cf. smela
gismu rafsi: pel x1 is yellow/golden [color adjective]. See also skari, blabi, xekri, kandi, carmi, narju, solji.

gismu rafsi: pem x1 is a poem/verse about plot/theme/subject/pattern x2 by author x3 for intended audience x4. x2 may be a convention rather than a subject. See also prosa, rimni, rilti, finti, lisri, sanga.
fu'ivla x1 is a limerick about subject/theme x2 by author x3. Cf. pemci, pemcrxaiku, pemcrsoneto.
fu'ivla x1 is a sonnet about subject/theme x2 by author x3. Cf. pemci, pemcrxaiku, pemcrlimriki.
fu'ivla x1 is a haiku about subject/theme x2 by author x3. Cf. pemci, pemcrsoneto, pemcrlimriki.
lujvo pa1 is a verse of poem pe1 about subject pe2 by author pe3 for intended audience pe4. Cf. pemci, pagbu, vlali'i, vlagri.
gismu rafsi: peb x1 is a pen using ink x2 applied by process x3. See also ciska, pinsi, xinmo, pimlu.
gismu rafsi: pec pe'u x1 (agent) touches x2 with x3 [a locus on x1 or an instrument] at x4 [a locus on x2]. See also ganse, darxi, jgari, penmi, jorne, satre, mosra, zgana.
gismu rafsi: ped pe'o x1 is/acts as a friend of/to x2 (experiencer); x2 befriends x1. See also bradi, xendo, nelci, prami, bradi.
lujvo g1 introduces p1 to p2 at/in location p3. Cf. penmi, gasnu.
lujvo g1 is a group meeting showing common property g2 at/in location p3.
gismu rafsi: pen pe'i x1 meets/encounters x2 at/in location x3. See also jorne, jikca, pencu.

gismu rafsi: pes pei x1 thinks/considers/cogitates/reasons/is pensive about/reflects upon subject/concept x2. Also: x1 is thoughtful (one sense); x2 is mental (one sense)/intellectual (one sense) (= selpei). See also cmavo list pe'i, jijnu, menli, morji, sidbo, jinvi, se nabmi, minra, lanli, besna, saske, skami.
gismu rafsi: per x1 is a pear [fruit] of species/strain x2. See also grute.
fu'ivla x1 is a peach of variety x2 see also flaume, rutrprunu
fu'ivla x1 is a persimmon/ebony of species/variety x2.
fu'ivla x1 reflects Peruvian culture/nationality in aspect x2. Cf. peRUV, ketco, gento, brazo, tcokumte.
lujvo p1=k1 is considerate of p2=k2. Cf. pensi, kurji.
lujvo pr1 is cognition (process of thought) with inputs pr2=pe2, outputs pr3=pe3, passing through stages pr4. Cf. puvypei, nunpei, selpei.
lujvo s1=p1 hypothesizes s2=p2 to audience s3 about subject/concept x4=p2. Cf. pensi, stidi, je'urja'o.

gismu rafsi: pex x1 is paste/pulp/dough/mash/mud/slurry [soft, smooth-textured, moist solid] of composition x2. x2: composition including x2, which need not be complete specification. See also marxa, kliti, tarla.

gismu rafsi: pet x1 is 10^{15} of x2 in dimension/aspect x3 (default is units). See also grake, mitre, snidu, stero, delno, molro, kelvo, xampo, gradu, litce, merli, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro

lujvo x1=p1=c1 is a noodle/pasta/boiled dough eaten by x2=c2 made out of x3=p2 (normally grain(s) or legume(s)) which is boiled in x4=f1 (normally water) at temperature x5=f2 and pressure x6=f3 See also febjukpa, grupesxu. luvjo from pesxu, febvi, cidja. Not very jvajvo, but it works.
gismu rafsi: pez x1 is a leaf of plant x2; x1 is foliage of x2. See also tricu, papri, spati.
lujvo x1 is chlorophyll of type x2; x1 is chlorophyllous with type x2
lujvo t1 is a deciduous tree of species t2. Cf. ze'erpezytricu.
lujvo x1 is a quantity of sorrel of subspecies x2. Cf. xruba, pezli.
cmavo rafsi: piz PA3 digit/number: radix (number base) point; default decimal.
cmavo VUhU4 n-ary mathematical operator: operands are vectors to be treated as matrix rows.
cmavo PA3 digit/number:separates digits for base >16, not current standard, or variable (e.g. time, date).
cmavo VUhU1 n-ary mathematical operator: times; multiplication operator; [(((a * b) * c) * ...)].
cmavo BAI pilno modal, 1st place used by ...
cmavo rafsi: piv JOI non-logical connective: cross product; Cartesian product of sets.
lujvo l1 is vaginal/penile fluid/secretion of p2. Cf. glevi'i, pinjyjdu.

gismu rafsi: pic x1 is a trillionth [10^{-12}] of x2 in dimension/aspect x3 (default is units). Cf. grake, mitre, snidu, stero, delno, molro, kelvo, xampo, gradu, litce, merli, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, kilto, megdo, mikri, milti, nanvi, petso, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.
cmavo cluster PA* number: too much of.
lujvo x1 is a hornbill of species x2.
lujvo g1 takes into custody/imprisons p1 as a prisoner/captive of p2 restrained/held/confined by means/force p3. Cf. pinfu, gasnu.
cmavo cluster PA* number: approximately all of.
gismu x1 is a pin/peg (needle-shaped tool) for fastening to/piercing x2, of material/properties x3. See also jesni, nivji, fenso, dinko, tutci.
lujvo s1 is philosophy with methodology s2.

gismu x1 begs/pleads/supplicates/entreats/implores/beseeches/prays [asks with humility] x2 for x3. Also importune, petition, plea, solicit; x2 benefactor, patron; x3 boon, favor, gift, alms. See also cpedu which is more general as to manner, pindi.
lujvo c1=p3 (agent) comments/remarks on/observes c2=p1 about subject x3=p2 to audience x4=c3=p4 via expressive medium x5=c5. Cf. zgana, ga'a, za'a, retsku.
gismu x1 is a ticket entitling x2 to entitlement/privilege x3 (event/state) under conditions x4. See also jaspu.
gismu rafsi: pi'i x1 is the product/total/result of factors/multiplicands (x2 and x3) x2 multiplied by x3. See also mekso, sumji, rapli, jalge.
gismu rafsi: pil pi'a x1 is a crust/rind/peel/skin/hide/outer cover of x2. (cf. grute, calku, skapi (pilka as a general term includes skapi), gacri)

gismu rafsi: pli x1 uses/employs x2 [tool, apparatus, machine, agent, acting entity, material] for purpose x3. Also utilize; x2 is useful/used productively by x1 to do x3 (= selpli for reordered places); hire/employ (= le'ipli, lejyplicu'a). (cf. tutci, cabra, minji, gasnu, zukte for x2, cmavo list pi'o, sazri, jibri)
lujvo d1=p2 has the same feathers/plumage as d2, the feathers/plumage being p1. Cf. pimlu, dunli.
gismu rafsi: pim pi'u x1 is a/the feather/plume(s)/plumage [body-part] of animal/species x2. See also cipni, nalci, rebla, kerfa, penbi.
cmavo cluster PA* number: too little of.
cmavo cluster PA* half. synonym fi'ure; see also xadba
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert .5 to probability selbri; event x1 has a 50/50 chance under cond. x2.
gismu x1 is a/the urine/piss/pee of x2. See also vikmi, xasne, kalci, mabla, festi.
lujvo x1 is a candirú of species/variety x2. syn. kandiru, finprvandeli; see also latfi'e
gismu rafsi: pid x1 is poor/indigent/impoverished/lacking in goods/possessions/property x2. x2 is scanty/meager/lacking for x1. See also ricfu, claxu, nitcu, pikci.
lujvo x1 is a flute. Cf. flani, pijne, flanrdizi, zgica'a.
gismu rafsi: pif x1 is a prisoner/captive of x2, restrained/held/confined by means/force x3. See also zifre, kavbu, rinju, ralte, fanta, cilce.

gismu x1 is a/the clitoris/penis [projecting reproductive organ; body-part] of x2. Normally context eliminates need for specificity; otherwise: penis (= nakpinji), clitoris (= fetpinji). See also cinse, gletu, vibna, plibu, vlagi, mabla, ganti.
lujvo c1 is bukkake onto c2 from c3=p2. Use nunpinjycarvi for the event. Cf. glevi'i, glefi'a.
lujvo g1 is a penis sheath. Cf. pinji, gacri.
lujvo j1 is smegma of p2. Includes male and female smegma. Cf. glevi'i, pinca, karlakse, lakse.
lujvo v1 circumcises/removes foreskin from p2=s2=v3. Cf. pinji, skapi, vimcu. See also pinjyskapi. Also: v1 is a mohel.
lujvo s1 is the foreskin of p2=s2. Cf. pinji, skapi. See also pinjykapyvi'u.

gismu rafsi: pik x1 (text) is a comment/remark/observation about subject x2 expressed by x3 to audience x4. Also: x3 comments/remarks/says x1 about x2 (= terselpinka for reordered places). See also jinvi, cusku, zgana, lanli, bacru, ciska.
lujvo x1 is a row/rank of table/chart x2. see also rajypau
fu'ivla x1 is a seal/sea lion/otary/walrus of genus/species x2. seal: kermipri pinpedi; sea lion: kerja'o pinpedi; see also mabru, odbenu

gismu rafsi: pis x1 is a pencil/crayon/stylus applying lead/marking material x2, frame/support [of material] x3. Also writing brush; x1 stimulates substrate medium x2 to display marks; explicitly denoting a standard lead pencil (= tabypinsi). (cf. ciska, penbi (unlike the English equivalents, pinsi is the more general term over penbi), burcu, bakri)
lujvo s1=p1 prostrates him/herself/itself before s2. Cf. pinta, sinma.
gismu rafsi: pin x1 is flat/level/horizontal in gravity/frame of reference x2. See also sraji, plita, xutla.
lujvo p1=t1 is a plain/flatland at location t2
lujvo v1 lies on v2=p1. Cf. vreta, pinta, surla, sipna.
gismu rafsi: pix x1 (agent) drinks/imbibes beverage/drink/liquid refreshment x2 from/out-of container/source x3. See also cidja, citka, taske, tunlo, xaksu, barja, birje.
lujvo x1 is a row vector of dimension x2 with coordinates x3, x4, ... See also rajnacmei
lujvo c1=p1 somersaults over c2 in direction c3 to p2 from p3. Cf. plipe, carna.
lujvo k1=p1 skips/hops to k2=p2 from k3=p3 via route k4. Cf. plipe, klama.
gismu rafsi: pi'o x1 is a piano/harpsichord/synthesizer/organ; a keyboard musical instrument. See also zgike.
fu'ivla x1 is a piano. Cf. pipno, zgica'a.
lujvo x1 is piano concerto number x2 in key x3 composed by x4 performed by/at x5( event). Cf. zgike, nolzgi, konceto zei pagbu, konceto, pipnrpiano, jgitrviolino zei konceto, simfoni, zgifi'i.
lujvo p1=b1 is a frog of species b2. Cf. plipe, banfi.
lujvo x1 is a grasshopper of order/species/breed x2. from mao'ste
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: convert .2 = 1/5 to portion selbri; x1 is 1/5 of mass/totality x2.
lujvo f1=p3 paints picture f2=p1 in style/art form l1 representing/showing p2=f4 on medium p4 from pixra larcu finti c.f. cintypu'i
cmavo cluster MOI* quantified selbri: converts all-of to portion selbri; x1 is the whole portion of mass x2.
cmavo cluster PA* number: almost all of.
cmavo cluster ROI* tense interval modifier: often; objectively quantified tense; defaults as time tense.
cmavo cluster PA* number: a little of.
cmavo cluster ROI* tense interval modifier: rarely; objectively quantified tense; defaults as time tense.
cmavo cluster PA* number: at least some of.
lujvo m1 is m2 square kilometers on side / facing m3 by standard m4.
lujvo n1 is a pizza with topping/ingredients n2. Cf. iptsa, cidjrpitsa, nabypalne.

gismu rafsi: pir xra x1 is a picture/illustration representing/showing x2, made by artist x3 in medium x4. Also (adjective:) x1 is pictorial/illustrative; drawing (= xraselci'a), x1 draws x2 (= xraci'a/xraci'a), image (= xratai), photo (= kacmyxra), take a photo (= kacmyterxra, kacmyxragau, kacmyxrazu'e); sculpture, relief (= blixra). See also ciska, cinta, prina, mupli, barna, skina.

lujvo j1=p2 is a policy by p1 policy maker regarding j3 subject of policy, j1 is political Made out of platu, javni. Politics as an activity may be "nu plajva" and political science may be "plajva saske"
gismu x1 is plump/fat/obese [excessively thick/bulbous/swollen] by standard x2. See also cinla, rotsu, barda, punli, grasu.
fu'ivla x1 is a plantain (small plant with flower spike) of species x2. see also jupybadna
fu'ivla x1 is a geranium of species/variety x2.
fu'ivla x1 is a sycamore (Platanus) of species x2.
fu'ivla x1 is a plaice of species x2. Cf. mlafi'e.

gismu rafsi: pla x1 (agent) plans/designs/plots plan/arrangement/plot/[schematic] x2 for state/process x3. Also invents/organizes; x2 design, scheme; the structure or layout of an object would be represented as a state in x3. See also cartu.

gismu rafsi: lej le'i x1 pays/compensates/remunerates/[rewards] payment x2 to recipient/payee x3 for goods/services x4. Also x4 commodities; x4 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event, or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= posle'i, posyvelyle'i for unambiguous semantics); rent (= jerle'i, lejyjbera). (cf. canja, cnemu, friti, kargu, vecnu, jdima, prali, jerna, sfasa, dunda, jinga, dapma; see note at jdima on cost/price/value distinction, cirko, dirba)
lujvo k1 is a journal/periodical/magazine/[newspaper] printed on paper with content k2 published by k3 for audience k4. Cf. karni, pelji, snukarni.
lujvo s1 is a cigarette made of s2 by s3.
gismu rafsi: pib x1 is a/the pubic area/external genitalia [body-part] of x2. See also cinse, gletu, pinji, vibna, vlagi, ganti, mabla.
lujvo c1 is the user-name/pseudonym/pen-name of c2=p1 for use with/by resource c3=p2 for purpose p3. Cf. pilno, cmene, cmisau, cmeveigau, japyvla.
lujvo c1 (agent) allows the use of p2 for use x3=p3 under conditions x4=c3.
lujvo c1=p1 adopts/selects/chooses/accepts c2=p2 out of alternatives c3 for purpose p3. Cf. pilno, cuxna, nelrai.
lujvo x1 is able to use x2 for purpose x3 under conditions x4.
gismu x1 is a planet revolving around x2 with planetary characteristics x3, orbital parameters x4. See also lunra, mluni, terdi, solri, munje.
lujvo c1=p1 is an asteroid/planetoid revolving around p2 with characteristics p3 and orbital parameters p4. Cf. plini, cmalu, cmaplini, jdikyplini.
lujvo k1 is the equator of planet x2=p1 (default Earth) revolving around p2 from plini xadba korbi c.f. plinyxadba jedjipli'i
lujvo x1 is a hemisphere of planet x2 (default Earth) revolving around p2 from plini xadba c.f. bolxadba

gismu rafsi: pip pi'e x1 (agent/object) leaps/jumps/springs/bounds to x2 from x3 reaching height x4 propelled by x5. Place structure parallels klama; hence x4 may be a route-like expression. See also bajra, stapa, cpare, lafti.
lujvo r1=p1 applies r2=p2 to r3=p3. Cf. pilno.
gismu x1 is an apple [fruit] of species/strain x2. See also grute.
lujvo x1 is an apple tree of tree species x2.

gismu rafsi: pit x1 is a plane [2-dimensional shape/form] defined by points x2 (set); x1 is flat/[smooth]. Also: x1 is even/planar/level. (x2 is a set of points at least sufficient to define the plane); See also xutla, sefta, tapla, karda, boxfo, pinta.
lujvo v1 is a log/record of data v2 (nu/du'u) about v3=p1's use of resource p2 for purpose p3 recorded in medium v4. Cf. pilno, vreji, cmisau, cmeveigau.
gismu rafsi: lix x1 (agent) plows/furrows/tills [cuts into and turns up] x2 with tool x3 propelled by x4. See also kakpa, sraku, katna, skuro.
lujvo x1=p2 is useful/good for x2=p1 by the standard of being usable for purpose p3. x3 is "usable". See alse selplika'e. Made from pilno + xamgu.
lujvo v1 is a useful word meaning/causing v2=x1=p2, a meaning which is useful to x2=p1 for purpose p3, in language v3
lujvo x1 is a frill-necked lizard (Chlamydosaurus) of species x2. Cf. respa.
lujvo pi1=po2 is a staple for holding together pi2, made of pi3
gismu rafsi: luj x1 is complex/complicated/involved in aspect/property x2 (ka) by standard x3. Also tangled, confused. See also cfipu, banli, sampu, jgena.
gismu rafsi: puk pu'a x1 (event/state) seems pleasant to/pleases x2 under conditions x3. See also rigni, cmavo list pu'a, melbi, nelci, prami.

gismu rafsi: lut lu'a x1 is a route/path/way/course/track to x2 from x3 via/defined by points including x4 (set). A route merely connects origin/destination, but need not be improved in any way; (x4 is a set of points at least sufficient to constrain the route relevantly). (cf. litru, naxle, tcana, dargu, klaji, ve klama; tadji, zukte for means to a goal, klama, pagre)
cmavo GOI restrictive relative phrase marker: which is specific to ...; normal possessive physical/legal.
cmavo GOI restrictive relative phrase marker: which belongs to ... ; inalienable possession.
lujvo x1=p1=d1 wants to own/possess/have x2=p2 for purpose x3=d3, wanting to own/possess/have it by right/custom/law x4=p3. d2 is the abstraction of x1 having x2.
cmavo BAI porsi modal, 1st place (in order) sequentially; in the sequence ...
cmavo UI3b discursive: uniquely, only, solely: the only relevant case. See also pamei, mulno, frica.
fu'ivla x1 reflects Polish culture/nationality/language in aspect x2. Cf. bangrpolska, slovo.
cmavo GOI restrictive appositive phrase marker: which is the same thing as.
cmavo NOI restrictive relative clause; attaches subordinate bridi with identifying information to a sumti.
fu'ivla x1 is a Pokémon/Pocket Monster of species x2. Cf. daskycizda'u, crida.
fu'ivla x1 is a halibut of species x2. syn. finprxipoglosu; Cf. flundero, mlafi'e.

gismu rafsi: plo x1 (force) folds/creases x2 at locus/loci/forming crease(s)/bend(s) x3. For agentive folding (= plogau, plozu'e); use cardinal-value sumti in x3, or rapli, to indicate multiple folds. See also korcu, cinje, boxfo, boxna.
gismu rafsi: pol x1 reflects Polynesian/Oceanian (geographic region) culture/nationality/languages in aspect x2. See also sralo, daplu, xamsi.
lujvo p1=b1 is the Japanese language used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote). Cf. ponjo, bangu, banjupunu.
lujvo p1=g1 is Japan. Cf. gugdejupu, ponjo, gugde.
lujvo l1 is the Shinto religion with beliefs/practices/tenets including l3 from ponjo lijda
gismu rafsi: pon po'o x1 reflects Japanese culture/nationality/language in aspect x2. See also xazdo, daplu.

gismu rafsi: pos po'e x1 possesses/owns/has x2 under law/custom x3; x1 is owner/proprietor of x2 under x3. (x3 is generally more important to the concept than commonly accepted for the English equivalent, since the concept is broader when unconstrained, and the nature/interpretation of possession/ownership is very culturally dependent); See also ckini, ralte, jitro, steci, srana, tutra, turni, zivle.
lujvo s1 is the sound of p1 breaking/shattering/cracking/splintering into pieces p2. Cf. porpi, sance.
lujvo g1 causes p1 to break/fracture/shatter/[split/splinter/crack] into pieces p2. Cf. gasnu, porpi.
gismu rafsi: pop po'i x1 breaks/fractures/shatters/[splits/splinters/cracks] into pieces x2. See also xrani, spofu, se katna.

gismu rafsi: por poi x1 [ordered set] is sequenced/ordered/listed by comparison/rules x2 on unordered set x3. Also (adjective:) x1 is serial. (sets are completely specified); See also cmavo list po'i, lidne, liste, cmima.
gismu rafsi: pot x1 reflects Portuguese culture/nationality/language in aspect x2. See also brazo.
lujvo Group of agents p3=z1 sequentially perform/take turns doing z2 in order p2 for purpose z3. Cf. porsi, zukte.
lujvo f1 is capital stock distributed among shareholders p1=f2 issued by company/corporation/firm p2 . Cf. ponse, fatri, posterfai, posyselfai, fairprali.
lujvo f3 is a/are share/shares distributed among f2=p1, issued by company/corporation/firm f1=p2 under law p3. Cf. ponse, fatri, posfai, posyselfai.
lujvo x1=p1 claims ownership of x2=p2 in condition p3. Cf. xusra, ponse.

lujvo d1 is the price of possessing/owning object d2=p2 for potential owner d3=p1 from vendor d4 under law/custom p3 ponse+jdima. This variant of jdima is pedantically semantic distinction between the price of "ownership" of an object rather than the price of the object itself.
lujvo f2=p1 is a/are a/the shareholder(s) of company/corporation/firm f1=p2 with shares/portions f3 under law p3. From ponse, fatri. Cf. posfai, posterfai.
lujvo p1=b1 is the Portuguese language used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote). Cf. porto, bangu, razbau, banpu'oru.
lujvo j1 is capital (factors of production) used to create goods/services j2=c2. cf. cupra, zbasu, jdini.

gismu rafsi: pal x1 is a profit/gain/benefit/advantage to x2 accruing/resulting from activity/process x3. Also (fe) x2 profits from x3 (= selterprali for reordered places); x1 may be a specific object, a commodity (mass), an event, or a property; pedantically, for objects/commodities, this is sumti-raising from ownership of the object/commodity (= selposprali for unambiguous semantics). See also vecnu, cnemu, pleji, jinga, canja, sfasa, jerna, jdima, dunda, zivle.

gismu rafsi: pam pa'i x1 loves/feels strong affectionate devotion towards x2 (object/state). Also: x1 is loving towards x2, x1 is a lover of x2 (one sense), x2 is beloved by x1 (= selpa'i for reordered places). See also cinmo, xebni, nelci, djica, sinma, pluka, kurji, pendo, speni.
gismu rafsi: pa'e x1 is perfect/ideal/archetypical/faultless/flawless/un-improvable in property/aspect x2 (ka). Also without defect/error. See also manfo, curve, traji, cfila, mulno.
lujvo b1 is a passenger ship for carrying b2, propleed by p3. Cf. prenu, bloti, beiblo, ni'ablo.
lujvo x1 is a biography of x2, written/created/composed by x3.

lujvo c1 (quoted word(s)) is a/the (proper) name identifying an individual person [not necessarily human] c2=p1 to/used-by namer/name-user c3 (person). Personal name usually today comprises a given name bestowed at birth or at a young age plus a surname, but may vary culturally. Naming convention (=cmene cacyjva). See also cmene and prenu.
lujvo d1 is a profile of person d2=p1 gathered by method d3. Cf. prenu, datni.
gismu rafsi: pej pe'a x1 spreads/expands over/into x2 from initial state x3. See also tcena, kuspe, ranji, fatri, muvdu, benji.
gismu rafsi: pre x1 is a person/people (noun) [not necessarily human]; x1 displays personality/a persona. See also nanmu, ninmu, remna, zukte, sevzi.
gismu rafsi: ret rei x1 (quoted text) is a question/query about subject x2 by questioner x3 to audience x4. See also nabmi, danfu, ciksi, frati, spuda, cpedu.
lujvo v1 is a passenger aircraft for carrying v2=p1, propelled by v3. Cf. prenu, vinji.
lujvo j1 is a human right for z1=p1 to do z2 (event/state). Cf. prenu, zifre, javni, zi'ejva, rarzi'ejva, nunzi'e, kamyzi'e.
lujvo g1 (agent) prints p1 onto p2 using p3 (tool/method). Cf. prina, fukpi.
gismu rafsi: pij x1 is wise/sage about matter x2 (abstraction) to observer x3. See also bebna.
lujvo m1=p3 is a printer/printing machine for printing p1 on surface p2. Cf. prina, minji.
gismu rafsi: pri x1 is a print/impression/image on/in surface x2 of/made by/using tool/press/implement/object x3. See also cukta, papri, pelji, pixra, ciska, danre, barna.
gismu x1 is to the right/right-hand side of x2 which faces/in-frame-of-reference x3. Also: x3 is the standard of orientation for x2. See also cmavo list ri'u, mlana, crane, trixe, farna, zunle.
lujvo xa1=z1 is a/the right hand of xa2=z2, which faces/in-frame-of-reference z3. Cf. zulxa'e.
fu'ivla x1 is a racoon of species/breed x2. Cf. mlatu, gerku, lorxu, cribe, labno, mabru.
lujvo k1=f1 is incapable of opposing f2 (person/force/mass) about f3 (abstract) underconditions k3 (event/state). Cf. fapro, kakne, tolvri.

gismu rafsi: ros ro'a x1 is prose about plot/theme/subject x2 by author x3 for intended audience x4. Non-poetic written text, without intentional rhyme or meter; x2 may be a convention rather than a subject. See also cfika, lisri, cukta, pemci, finti.
fu'ivla x1 is a proton in quantum state x2.

gismu rafsi: ruc ru'e x1 is a process with inputs x2, outputs/results x3, passing through steps/stages x4. x2 resource (= selru'e, but also ru'etci, (ru'er-/ruc- or selru'e-/selruc- modifying:) selxaksu, selsabji, livla). See also cmavo list pu'e, farvi, tadji, grute, tcini.
lujvo x1 predicts/foretells/anticipates to x2 fact(s) x3 (du'u) about subject x4 by epistemology x5. See also djuno, jungau
lujvo p1=l1 is preceding p2=l2 in sequence l3. bavla'i
lujvo n1=l1=p1 is the night before p2=l2 at location n3. Cf. nicte, purlamdei, bavlamcte.
lujvo d1=p1=l1 is yesterday; d1=p1=l1 is the day preceding p2=l2, day standard d3.
lujvo n1=p1=l1 is yesteryear; n1=p1=l1 is the year preceding p2=l2 by year standard n3.
gismu rafsi: pun (adjective:) x1 is elastic/springy. See also ckabu, tcena.
lujvo pun1 prepones/moves forward pun2 to before pur2. Cf. purci, punji, bavypunji.

lujvo x1 is a prokaryote of species/defining property x2. Protokaryots are a group of organisms that lack a cell nucleus. P. consists of two domains, bacteria and archaea.See also microorganism (one cellular organism;=jurme) and eukaryote.
lujvo s1 is the ex-wife/husband of s2 under law/custom/tradition/system/convention s3. Cf. bavyspe.
gismu rafsi: rux ru'i x1 is spiritual/pertains to the soul in nature [either energy or being]; x1 is ghostly/ethereal. Also soul (= ruxse'i). See also censa, lijda, mucti, xadni.
cmavo PU time tense relation/direction: did [selbri]; before/prior to [sumti]; default past tense.
cmavo BAI pluka modal, 1st place pleased by ...
cmavo BAI pruce modal, 1st place (in manner 1) by process ...
cmavo rafsi: pus CAhA modal aspect: can and has; demonstrated potential.
cmavo ZAhO interval event contour: in anticipation of ...; until ... ; inchoative ----| |.
cmavo rafsi: puv NU1 abstractor: process (event) abstractor; x1 is process of [bridi] proceeding in stages x2.
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: was going to; (tense/modal).
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: past actuality; modal aspect.
cmavo cluster ZAhO* time tense: was then; (tense/modal).
lujvo k1 is a gardener attending to garden p1 belonging to p2, growing plants p3. Cf. purdi, kuji, cagypre, tercange.
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: before and after; (tense/modal).
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: before and during; (tense/modal).
lujvo b1=p2 is toad of species b2 see also pipybanfi
gismu rafsi: puc pu'e x1 is dust/precipitate [suspensible solid] from x2 in medium/on surface x3. See also te zalvi, danmo, purmo, sligu.

gismu x1 is a police officer/[enforcer/vigilante] enforcing law(s)/rule(s)/order x2. Police officer, as an agent of authority (= ca'irpulji, ka'irpulji), as part of a police force (= puljysoi, as part of puljyselsoi); military police (= jempulji, bilpulji). See also catni, sonci, bilni, flalu, bandu, jemna, zekri, krati.
gismu x1 is a pulley [tool] for performing action/function x2 rotating on axle x3. See also tutci, xislu, vraga.
lujvo l1 (agent) dusts l2 with l4 from purmo lumci
lujvo v1 contains powder of material p2. Cf. purmo, vasru.
gismu rafsi: puj pu'i x1 (agent) puts/places/sets x2 on/at surface/locus x3. See also cpacu, lebna, cpana, batke, setca.
gismu rafsi: pul x1 is a swelling/protrusion/convexity [shape/form] at/in/on x2, of material x3. (adjective:) x1 is swollen. See also balji, cmana, plana.
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: had earlier been; (tense/modal).

gismu rafsi: pur pru x1 is in the past of/earlier than/before x2 in time sequence; x1 is former; x2 is latter. Time ordering only (use lidne otherwise); aorist in that x1 may overlap in time with x2 as long as it starts before, x1 starts before x2 but is continuing during x2 (= cfaprucabna); non-aorist before, i.e. x1 is over/ended before x2 starts (= fampru), x1 is completed before x2 starts (= mulpru). See also lidne, balvi, cabna, farna.
gismu rafsi: pud x1 is a garden/tended/cultivated field of family/community/farmer x2 growing plants/crop x3. Orchard (= ricpurdi). See also foldi, cange, panka.
lujvo x1 is the last time/previous time that x2 happened. See purci, lamji, krefu, bavlamke'u, purlamdei
gismu rafsi: pum pu'o x1 is a powder of material x2. Flour (= grupu'o, xripu'o). See also pulce, zalvi.
lujvo p1=z1 previews z2 by means z3 under condition z4. Cf. purci, zgana.
lujvo x1 is adolescence by standard x2
lujvo x1 is stellar evolution Cf. tarci, kesyske
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: a medium time before; (tense/modal).
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: for a medium length interval some time in the past; (tense/modal).
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: for a short interval some time in the past; (tense/modal).
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: for a long interval some time in the past; (tense/modal).
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: a short time before; (tense/modal).
cmavo cluster PU* time tense: a long time before; (tense/modal).
cmavo KOhA5 pro-sumti: a recent sumti before the last one, as determined by back-counting rules.
cmavo BAI srana modal, 1st place pertained to by ... (generally more specific).
lujvo x1 is a relative clause attached to argument x2 with predicate relation x3 among arguments x4. See also noi, poi, voi
cmavo PA3 digit/number: repeating digits (of a decimal) follow.
lujvo p1=r2 are the retained earnings of company/corporation/firm/partnership p2=r1 resulting from business activity p3. From ralte, prali. Cf. fairprali.
cmavo BAI krasi modal, 1st place from source/origin/starting point ...
lujvo g1 maintains g2=r1 (event/state) over interval r2. Cf. ranji, gasnu.
lujvo x1 is the integral of x2 with respect to x3 over x4. See also ri'o
cmavo RAhO flag GOhA to indicate pro-assignment context updating for all pro-assigns in referenced bridi.
cmavo UI3 discursive: chiefly - equally - incidentally. See also ralju, vajni.
cmavo cluster UI*3 discursive: chiefly - equally - incidentally.
cmavo cluster UI*3 discursive: chiefly - equally - incidentally.
lujvo r1=b1 is the Arabic language used by b2 to express/communicate b3 (si'o/du'u, not quote). from xrabo bangu c.f. misrybau
lujvo x1 is a dromedary/Arabian camel of breed x2. Cf. kumte, zdokumte, tcokumte, mabru.
gismu x1 (action/activity/behavior) is sane/rational by standard x2. See also fenki.
gismu x1 is a rabbit/hare/[doe] of species/breed x2. See also mabru, kerlo.
lujvo x1 admits/accepts/acknowledges/allows/concedes/recognizes that x2 is true about x3 on grounds/under compelling evidence x4 Cf. randa, jinvi, fitytu'i, cpazau, zarcpa.

gismu rafsi: ra'o x1 is x2 radian(s) [metric unit] in angular measure (default is 1) by standard x3. Measured in degrees (julra'o); right ascension astronomical measurement. (= cacryra'o). See also jganu, kilto, centi, decti, dekto, femti, gigdo, gocti, gotro, gutci, litce, megdo, mikri, milti, minli, nanvi, petso, picti, terto, xatsi, xecto, xexso, zepti, zetro.
lujvo x1=r1=c1 abandons / gives up x2=r2=c2 under condition x3=r3=c3 Cf. randa, curmi, fesli'a, tolcpa.
gismu rafsi: raf x1 is an affix/suffix/prefix/combining-form for word/concept x2, form/properties x3, language x4. See also valsi, lujvo, pagbu.
lujvo x1 is the morphology of language x2 according to methodology x3. see also vlaturge'a, taiske
fu'ivla x1 is a Malpighian tubule [excretory organ] of insect x2. see also rutrmalpigi

gismu rafsi: rav x1 is located across/on the other side of gap/boundary x2 from x3; x1 is opposite (fi) x3. Also: x1 is over there (across/beyond zo'e); directly across/beyond a boundary/gap, generally at the shortest plausible distance on the other side of the boundary. See also dukti, kuspe, bancu, kruca, cripu, pagre.
cmavo BAI traji modal, 1st place with superlative ...
lujvo x1 is a column vector of dimension x2 with coordinates x3, x4, ... See also pinynacmei

lujvo s1=rs1 is a vertical rock face / rock surface of rock / mountain rs2 on side rs3 with edges rs4, vertical in reference frame/gravity s2. Technically necessary ke (or bo) dropped. Cf. sraji, roksfe, fenra, cmana, farlu.
lujvo x1 is tall according to standard x2. Cf. sraji, clani, rajyclamau, rajyclarai, claselxadni.
lujvo z1=c1=s1 is taller than z2 by amount z4. Cf. sraji, clani, zmadu, rajycla, rajyclarai.
lujvo t1=c1=s1 is the tallest among set/range t4. Cf. sraji, clani, traji, rajycla, rajyclamau.
lujvo x1 is a column/file of table/chart x2. see also pinpau, kamju
lujvo se1=sr1 is a ladder / vertical stairway for climbing structure se2 with steps se3, vertical in reference frame sr2. Made from sraji + serti.
lujvo c1 carves inscription/text c2 on to c3=s2 using c4=s1. Cf. sraku, ciska.
gismu x1 reflects Iraqi culture/nationality in aspect x2. See also xrabo.

gismu rafsi: ra'u x1 (object/person/event/situation) troubles/disturbs x2 (person) causing problem(s) x3. Also afflicts, is disruptive to, troublesome; x1/x3 are a care to x2, x2 is troubled by/cares about x1/x3 (= selra'u for reordered places). See also dicra, fanza, zunti, kurji, xanka.
gismu rafsi: rac x1 is delicate/fragile/subtle/refined in property x2 (ka). Easily damaged or rendered less pleasing/pure/effective. See also jdari, ranti, tsali, milxe, kukte.

gismu rafsi: ral x1 is principal/chief/leader/main/[staple], most significant among x2 (set) in property x3 (ka). Staple (= ralselpra); general/admiral/president/principal leader (= ralja'a, ralterbe'e; use additional terms to distinguish among these); also primary, prime, (adverb:) chiefly, principally, mainly; (x2 is complete specification of set). See also vajni, te bende, minde, lidne, jatna, jitro, gidva, midju.

lujvo x1 is a/the capital of x2. Cf. ralju, tcadu. More general than trutca. May be the financial (e.g. New York in USA), industrial (e.g. Sao Paulo in Brazil) or religious (e.g. Mecca in Saudi Arabia) capital of its polity but not necessarily the seat of government.
gismu rafsi: ra'e x1 retains/keeps/holds x2 in its possession. See also cirko, rinju, ponse, jgari, pinfu, stali, curmi.
lujvo r1 is the frequency of the carrier wave of signal b1. Cf. ralju, boxna.
fu'ivla x1 is a rambutan (Nephelium lappaceum) of breed x2
fu'ivla x1 is the Ramadan/Ramazan of year x2. Cf. ramadan.
lujvo b1=r1 is velvet made from material b2. Cf. ranti, bukpu.
gismu rafsi: rad x1 yields/gives way/surrenders to x2 (force/agent) under conditions x3. See also jdari, renvi, ranti, se bapli.
gismu rafsi: rag x1 is a/the body organ [body-part] of body/species x2 performing function x3. Also sweetmeat (= ragdja). See also besna, livga.
fu'ivla x1 is an orangutan of variety x2. see also remsmismani
gismu rafsi: ra'i x1 (event/state) continues/persists over interval x2; x1 (property - ka) is continuous over x2. See also temci, kuspe, renvi, cedra, citsi, manfo, vitci, cukla, fliba, preja, tcena.

gismu rafsi: ram x1 is a myth/legend, a culturally significant story about x2 in mythos x3 of culture x4. Also: x1 is mythical/fairy tale; used adjectivally for non-humanoid creatures (= ramda'u) of story/myth/legend/religion, e.g. dragon; fairy tale (= veryranmi). See also lijda, lisri, crida.
lujvo d1=m1=r1 is a/the soft palate of m2.
fu'ivla x1 is a dragon of species/breed x2 in mythos x3 of culture x4
gismu x1 is a quantity of/contains/is made of bronze of composition including x2. See also jinme, tunka, lastu.
gismu rafsi: ran x1 is soft/malleable/moldable/yielding to force x2 in conditions x3. See also ralci, jdari, lakse, randa, gradu.
gismu rafsi: rax x1 is ironic(al)/contrary to expectation x2 in state/property/aspect x3. See also dukti, frica, cizra.
lujvo z1=c1 (experiencer) increases in skill / expertise at z2=c2 by amount z3 by means of repeating action r1 r2 times. Made from rapli + certu + zenba.
lujvo x1 is a remake/re-invention of x2
gismu rafsi: rap x1 [action] repeats/is repeated for a total of x2 (quantity) occurrences. Practice (= rapyzu'e, rapxelcli, rapyzukmo'i). See also cmavo list roi, cafne, krefu, fukpi, pilji, xruti.
lujvo c1 repeats c2 (sedu'u/text/lu'e concept) for audience c3 via expressive medium c4, r2 times (default: one). Cf. rapli, cusku, refsku.
lujvo x1 is a shuttle between x2 and x3, traveling along route x4, carrying passengers x5.
lujvo d1 beats/hits repeatedly d2 using d3 at locus d4, r2 times. Cf. rapli, darxi.
lujvo b1 is a natural language spoken by community b2 to express b3. As opposed to constructed spoken languages. Cf. runbau
lujvo x1 is the natural logarithm of x2. See also te'o

lujvo x1=j1 thinks/knows by instinct/feels that x2=j2 [opinion] (du'u) is true about subject/issue x3=j3 From rarna and jinvi. Drawing conclusions without a proper reasoning, using 'gut feelings' or preconscious thoughts.

lujvo k1=r1 (NU) is a natural right of k2 (individual/mass) by standard k3. Rights which are not contingent upon the laws, customs, or beliefs of a particular society or polity, thus necessarily universal; usually contrasted to legal rights (flakrali), which are culturally and politically relative. Cf. krali.
